        private void TheMinesOfMoria()
        {
            AddHtml("To-the-West-door-TMoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>It has been years since there was news of Balin's expedition to Moria, but in recent months there have been rumors of growing darkness there. You traveled to the Mines to investigate these tidings. Upon reaching the Doors of Durin, you are surprised to find a foul&ndash;smelling pool at its feet, and a fell creature blocking your way.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Each player adds 1 resource to each of his heroes' resource pools. Add The Watcher to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("To-the-West-door-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>While this stage has at least 5 progress on it, The Watcher is considered to be engaged with each player and attacks each player in turn order during the combat phase. (Deal and resolve a shadow card for each attack.)</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When The Watcher is defeated, flip it over and add Chamber of Mazarbul to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'>This stage cannot be defeated while The Watcher is in play.</p>");
            AddHtml("Journey-in-the-Black-Pit-A-Presence-in-the-Dark-TMoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>Once inside the mine it becomes obvious that the rumors were true: evil things move through the darkness all around you. With the way behind you blocked by that horrible creature, your only option is to press forward.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team searches the top 5 cards of the encounter deck for a card with cost 1 or less (2 or less instead if there are two or more players), sets it aside, and shuffles the encounter deck. Reveal the set aside card. Its 'when revealed' effects cannot be canceled.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Journey-in-the-Black-Pit-A-Presence-in-the-Dark-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of the staging step, the opposing team looks at the top 2 cards of the encounter deck, puts 1 on the bottom, and puts the other back on top.</p>");
            AddHtml("Journey-in-the-Black-Pit-The-Long-Dark-of-Moria-TMoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>Once inside the mine it becomes obvious that the rumors were true: evil things move through the darkness all around you. With the way behind you blocked by that horrible creature, your only option is to press forward.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team searches the top 5 cards of the encounter deck for a card with cost 1 or less (2 or less instead if there are two or more players), sets it aside, and shuffles the encounter deck. Reveal the set aside card. Its 'when revealed' effects cannot be canceled.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Journey-in-the-Black-Pit-The-Long-Dark-of-Moria-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team searches the encounter deck and discard pile for one different 0 cost location per player and adds them to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Journey-in-the-Black-Pit-Narrow-Paths-TMoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>Once inside the mine it becomes obvious that the rumors were true: evil things move through the darkness all around you. With the way behind you blocked by that horrible creature, your only option is to press forward.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team chooses an attachment controlled by each player and places them faceup under this stage as guarded objectives with blank text boxes. Players cannot play or put into play any attachment that shares a title with an attachment guarded by this stage. When this stage is defeated, return each guarded attachment to its owner's hand.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Journey-in-the-Black-Pit-Narrow-Paths-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team searches the encounter deck and discard pile for one different 0 cost location per player and adds them to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Search-for-the-Chamber-Drums-in-the-Deep-TMoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>Your journey through Moria has been marked by all manner of terrible hazards, but you've discovered no sign of Balin's company. You hope that you might find some record of the Dwarven colony in the Chamber of Mazarbul.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team searches the top 5 cards of the encounter deck for a card with cost 2 or less (cost 3 or less instead if there are two or more players), sets it aside, and shuffles the encounter deck. Reveal the set aside card. Its 'when revealed' effects cannot be canceled.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Search-for-the-Chamber-Drums-in-the-Deep-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>Enemies cannot take damage while Chamber of Mazarbul is in the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team searches the encounter deck and discard pile for an enemy and adds it to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'>This stage cannot be defeated while an enemy is in play. When this stage is defeated, the players win the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Search-for-the-Chamber-The-Fate-of-Balin-TMoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>Your journey through Moria has been marked by all manner of terrible hazards, but you've discovered no sign of Balin's company. You hope that you might find some record of the Dwarven colony in the Chamber of Mazarbul.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team searches the top 5 cards of the encounter deck for a card with cost 2 or less (cost 3 or less instead if there are two or more players), sets it aside, and shuffles the encounter deck. Reveal the set aside card. Its 'when revealed' effects cannot be canceled.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Search-for-the-Chamber-The-Fate-of-Balin-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of the staging step, the first player must choose: either reveal an additional encounter card this phase, or no more than 5 progress can be placed here this phase.</p><p class='main-text'>This stage cannot be defeated while Chamber of Mazarbul is in play. When this stage is defeated, the players win the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Search-for-the-Chamber-Continuing-Eastward-TMoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>Your journey through Moria has been marked by all manner of terrible hazards, but you've discovered no sign of Balin's company. You hope that you might find some record of the Dwarven colony in the Chamber of Mazarbul.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team searches the top 5 cards of the encounter deck for a card with cost 2 or less (cost 3 or less instead if there are two or more players), sets it aside, and shuffles the encounter deck. Reveal the set aside card. Its 'when revealed' effects cannot be canceled.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Search-for-the-Chamber-Continuing-Eastward-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>Each location in the staging area gets +1 {Threat} and +3 quest points.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When the active location is explored, reveal the top card of the encounter deck.</p><p class='main-text'>This stage cannot be defeated while Chamber of Mazarbul is in play. When this stage is defeated, the players win the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Watcher-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>Cannot be optionally engaged.</p><p class='main-text'>The Watcher gets +2 {Threat} and +4 hit points per player.</p>");
            AddHtml("Chamber-of-Mazarbul-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>X is 1 more than the stage number of the main quest.</p><p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>The players cannot travel here unless they are at stage 3B.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Each player discards 1 random card from his hand.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Savage-Werewolf-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Savage Werewolf is dealt a shadow card with no shadow effect, it makes an additional attack after this one. (Do not deal it a shadow card.)</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy makes an additional attack against you after this one.</p>");
            AddHtml("Many-pillared-Hall-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>Many-pillared Hall gets +1 {Threat} for each copy of Many-pillared Hall in the staging area.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Discard an attachment from the defending character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Shadow-of-Fear-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team attached Shadow of Fear to a hero. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text: &quot;Treat attached hero's text box as if it were blank, except for Traits.&quot;)</p>");
            AddHtml("Deep-dweller-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Return each engaged Spider enemy to the staging area.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} (+2 {Attack} instead if it is a Spider).</p>");
            AddHtml("Darkened-Stairway-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Darkened Stairway is in the staging area, it gains:<b>&quot;Forced:</b> After a 'when revealed' effect is canceled, reveal the top card of the encounter deck.&quot;</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Discard the top card of the encounter deck. If that card is a treachery, resolve its 'when revealed' effect.</p>");
            AddHtml("We-Cannot-Get-Out-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Until the end of the phase, add X{Threat} to the staging area, where X is the number of characters controlled by the player with the most characters.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Assign X damage among characters you control, where X is the number of enemies engaged with you.</p>");
            AddHtml("Spider-Broodling-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Spider Broodling engages you, remove 2 progress from the main quest.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} If this attack destroys a character, remove 2 progress from the main quest.</p>");
            AddHtml("Spider-Burrow-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Spider Burrow is in the staging area, each Spider enemy gets +1 {Defense}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Spider Burrow is explored, the opposing team searches the encounter deck and discard pile for a Spider enemy with cost 1 or less and adds it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Grabbed-by-Spiders-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Remove X characters from the quest, where X is the number of Spider enemies in play. If there are no Spider enemies in play, Grabbed by Spiders gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Defending character cannot ready until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Moria-Bats-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Shuffle Moria Bats into the enocunter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ancient-Guardroom-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>Ancient Guardroom gets +1 {Threat} for each resource on it.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After an event is played, place 1 resource here.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Assign X damage among characters in play, where X is Ancient Guardroom's{Threat}</p>");
            AddHtml("Denizen-of-the-Deep-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team attaches Denizen of the Deep to a non-unique enemy and returns it to the staging area. If there are no non-unique enemies in play, Denizens of the Deep gains surge. (Counts as Condition attachment with the text: &quot;Attached enemy gets +1 {Threat} +1 {Attack} +1 {Defense} and is immune to player card effects.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Werewolf-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>Werewolf gets -10 engagement cost while there is an active location.</p>");
            AddHtml("Fouled-Well-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Fouled Well is in the staging area, characters cannot be readied by player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Each player exhausts a character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Cave-In-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Return the active location to the staging area. Each player assigns X damage among characters he controls, where X is the{Threat} of that location. If no location is returned to the staging area this way, Cave In gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack destroys a character, return the active location to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Hive-Guardian-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Hive Guardian attacks and destroys an ally, return Hive Guardian to the staging area.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Return attacking enemy to the staging area after this attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Abandoned-Mines-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Abandoned Mines is in the staging area, progress cannot be placed here.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If attacking enemy was engaged this round, it cannot take damage this phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Sudden-Pitfall-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team chooses and discards an ally. If no ally was discarded this way, Sudden Pitfall gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Either discard an ally you control, or attacking enemy cannot take damage this phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Web-spinner-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Either no more than 4 progress can be placed on the current quest this phase, or Web-spinner gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack destroys a character, return attacking enemy to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Cobwebbed-Cavern-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Remove 2 progress from the main quest.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Remove 2 progress from the main quest.</p>");
            AddHtml("Foul-Air-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The first player must choose: either deal 1 damage to each character committed to the quest, or raise each player's threat by 1 and end the quest phase without resolving the quest.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Deal 1 damage to the defending character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Brood-Mother-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have non-objective player card attachments or take non-combat damage.</p><p class='main-text'>While Brood Mother is in the staging area, no more than 5 progress can be placed on the main quest each round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Lightless-Passage-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Lightless Passage is in the staging area, no more than 1 progress can be placed on each location in the staging area each round.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Each player discards 1 random card from his hand.</p>");
            AddHtml("Lurking-Malice-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Discard each resource from each hero's resource pool. Add 1 to the total{Threat} in the staging area for each resource discarded this way. If no resources were discarded this way, Lurking Malice gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Discard a resource from the resource pool of a hero you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Great-Cave-troll-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have non-objective player card attachments.</p><p class='main-text'>While Great Cave-troll is in the staging area, it gains:<b>&quot;Forced:</b> At the end of the encounter phase, raise each player's threat by 2.&quot;</p>");
            AddHtml("Zigil-Mineshaft-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Quest Action:</b> Raise each player's threat by 1 to reduce the total{Threat} of Zigil Mineshaft by 1 until the end of the phase. The first player may trigger this effect.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dark-and-Dreadful-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player discards 1 random card from his hand. Until the end of the phase, add X{Threat} to the staging area, where X is the total cost of the discarded cards.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Discard 1 random card from your hand.</p>");
            AddHtml("Goblin-Follower-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>Goblin Follower cannot be optionally engaged.</p><p class='main-text'>While Goblin Follower is in the staging area, it gains:<b>&quot;Forced:</b> After an enemy engages a player, Goblin Follower engages that player.</p>");
            AddHtml("Stairs-of-Nain-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Stairs of N in is in the staging area, the first treachery revealed each round gains surge and its 'when revealed' effects cannot be canceled.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Stairs of N in is explored, raise each player's threat by 4.</p>");
            AddHtml("Hidden-Threat-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team searches the top 5 cards of the encounter deck for a card with cost X or less, where X is the stage number of the main quest, and places that card facedown under the main quest. After the next time the players quest successfully, reveal that card.</p>");
            AddHtml("Goblin-Warlord-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have non-objective player card attachments or take non-combat damage</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Goblin Warlord enters play, the opposing team searches the encounter deck and discard pile for a 0-cost Goblin enemy and adds it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dwarven-Forge-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Dwarven Forge is the active location, it gains:<b>&quot;Response:</b> After Dwarven Forge is explored, each player draws 1 card.&quot;</p>");
            AddHtml("Signs-of-Conflict-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each enemy and location in the staging area gets +1 {Threat} until the end of the phase.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} (+2 {Attack} instead if you are engaged with another enemy).</p>");
            AddHtml("Goblin-Archer-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Goblin Archer is in the staging area, it gains:<b>&quot;Forced:</b> At the end of the encounter phase, assign X damage among characters in play, where X is the number of enemies in play.&quot;</p>");
            AddHtml("Narrow-Fissure-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Narrow Fissure is in the staging area, characters cannot be healed by player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Each player deals 1 damage to a hero he controls.</p>");
            AddHtml("Crumbling-Ruin-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player assigns X damage among characters he controls, where X is the number of characters he controls.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Exhaust a character you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Goblin-Sneak-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team searches the top 5 cards of the encounter deck for a Goblin enemy with cost 1 or less and adds it to the staging area.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack}</p>");
            AddHtml("Plundered-Armoury-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Discard the top card of the encounter deck. If that card is an enemy, add it to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("They-Are-Coming-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team searches the encounter deck and discard pile for a different 0-cost enemy per player and adds them to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The opposing team shuffles an enemy from the encounter discard pile into the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Swarming-Goblins-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Return each copy of Swarming Goblins in the encounter discard pile to the staging area.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If the attacking enemy is a Goblin put Swarming Goblins into play engaged with you.</p>");
            AddHtml("Goblin-Tunnels-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Goblin Tunnels is in the staging area, each Goblin enemy gets +1 {Attack}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Goblin Tunnels is explored, the opposing team searches the encounter deck and discard pile for a Goblin enemy with cost 1 or less and adds it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Massing-in-the-Deep-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each engaged enemy makes an attack. If no attacks were made this way, Massing in the Deep gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Each enemy engaged with you gets +1 {Attack}</p>");
            AddHtml("Bilbo-Baggins-TMoM", "<p class='main-text'>The first player draws 1 additional card in the resource phase.</p>");

            AddHtml("To-the-West-door-TMoM-PRM", "<p class='flavor-text'>It has been years since there was news of Balin's expedition to Moria, but in recent months there have been rumors of growing darkness there. You traveled to the Mines to investigate these tidings. Upon reaching the Doors of Durin, you are surprised to find a foul&ndash;smelling pool at its feet, and a fell creature blocking your way.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Each player adds 1 resource to each of his heroes' resource pools. Add The Watcher to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("To-the-West-door-TMoM-PRM", "<p class='main-text'>While this stage has at least 5 progress on it, The Watcher is considered to be engaged with each player and attacks each player in turn order during the combat phase. (Deal and resolve a shadow card for each attack.)</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When The Watcher is defeated, flip it over and add Chamber of Mazarbul to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'>This stage cannot be defeated while The Watcher is in play.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Watcher-TMoM-PRM", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>Cannot be optionally engaged.</p><p class='main-text'>The Watcher gets +2 {Threat} and +4 hit points per player.</p>");
            AddHtml("Chamber-of-Mazarbul-TMoM-PRM", "<p class='main-text'>X is 1 more than the stage number of the main quest.</p><p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>The players cannot travel here unless they are at stage 3B.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Each player discards 1 random card from his hand.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Many-pillared-Hall-TMoM-PRM", "<p class='main-text'>Many-pillared Hall gets +1 {Threat} for each copy of Many-pillared Hall in the staging area.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Discard an attachment from the defending character.</p>");
        }

        private void EscapeFromKhazadDum()
        {
            AddHtml("Gandalf-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>Play with the top card of your deck faceup. Once per phase, you may play the top card of your deck as if it was in your hand. When playing a card this way, Gandalf is considered to have the printed{sphere:Leadership}{sphere:Lore}{sphere:Tactics} and{sphere:Spirit} icons.</p>");
            AddHtml("Elrond-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>You may spend resources from Elrond's resource pool to pay for{sphere:Spirit}{sphere:Leadership} and{sphere:Tactics} allies.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a character is healed by another card effect, heal 1 damage on it.</p>");
            AddHtml("Arwen-Undomiel-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Discard a card from your hand to add 1 resource to a Noldor hero's resource pool, or to Aragorn's resource pool. (Limit once per round.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Beregond-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'>Lower the cost to play Weapon and Armor attachments on Beregond by 2.</p>");
            AddHtml("Sam-Gamgee-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After you engage an enemy with a higher engagement cost than your threat, ready Sam Gamgee. He gets +1 {Willpower} +1 {Attack} and +1 {Defense} until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Out-of-the-Depths-EfKD", "<p class='flavor-text'>You entered Moria with the hope of finding Mithril, but you have become lost underground instead. Below the ancient mansions of the Dwarves, untold dangers lurk in the darkness.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Add Dark Pit to the staging area. The opposing team searches the encounter deck for one different 0-cost enemy or location per player and adds them to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Out-of-the-Depths-EfKD", "<p class='flavor-text'>Surrounded by utter black and running low on supplies, you must find your way out of Khazad&ndash;d–m before it's too late.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Dark Pit is explored, flip it over and set Durin's Bane aside, out of play. Each player searches the top 5 cards of his deck for a card, adds it to his hand, and shuffles his deck.</p><p class='main-text'>This stage cannot be defeated while Dark Pit is in play.</p>");
            AddHtml("Search-for-an-Exit-Old-One-Lair-EfKD", "<p class='flavor-text'>The Mines of Moria are vast beyond your imagination. Though you feel that you are making progress, one wrong turn could mean disaster.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team searches the top 5 cards of the encounter deck for a card with cost 1 or less (cost 2 or less instead if there are two or more players), sets it aside, and shuffles the encounter deck. Reveal the set aside card. It's 'when revealed' effects cannot be canceled.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Search-for-an-Exit-Old-One-Lair-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team searchs the encounter deck and discard pile for an enemy with cost 2 or less, adds it to the staging area, and places a resources on it. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p><p class='main-text'>The enemy with a resource on it is immune to player card effects, and progress cannot be placed on this stage while that enemy is in play.</p>");
            AddHtml("Search-for-an-Exit-A-Wrong-Turn-EfKD", "<p class='flavor-text'>The Mines of Moria are vast beyond your imagination. Though you feel that you are making progress, one wrong turn could mean disaster.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team searches the top 5 cards of the encounter deck for a card with cost 1 or less (cost 2 or less instead if there are two or more players), sets it aside, and shuffles the encounter deck. Reveal the set aside card. It's 'when revealed' effects cannot be canceled.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Search-for-an-Exit-A-Wrong-Turn-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player chooses 1 card in his hand and shuffles the rest into his deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Search-for-an-Exit-A-Way-Up-EfKD", "<p class='flavor-text'>The Mines of Moria are vast beyond your imagination. Though you feel that you are making progress, one wrong turn could mean disaster.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team searches the top 5 cards of the encounter deck for a card with cost 1 or less (cost 2 or less instead if there are two or more players), sets it aside, and shuffles the encounter deck. Reveal the set aside card. It's 'when revealed' effects cannot be canceled.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Search-for-an-Exit-A-Way-Up-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>Add the active location's{Threat} to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'>During the travel phase, the players must travel, if able.</p>");
            AddHtml("Nearing-the-Gate-The-Bridge-of-Khazad-d–m-EfKD", "<p class='flavor-text'>Your spirits rise as you are drawing near to the East Gate of Moria. But then a huge, dark shape rises in front of you and bursts into flames: a Balrog! Durin's Bane blocks your escape.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add the set-aside Durin's Bane to the staging area. It cannot take damage this round. If there is more than 1 player, it makes an immediate attack against the first player.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Nearing-the-Gate-The-Bridge-of-Khazad-d–m-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>No more than 5 progress can be placed here each round.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of the quest phase, Durin's Bane makes an attack against the first player. Any undefended or excess damage dealt by this attack must be placed here.</p><p class='main-text'>If this stage has damage on it equal to or greater than its quest points, the players lose the game. If this stage is defeated the players win the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Nearing-the-Gate-Last-Lord-of-Moria-EfKD", "<p class='flavor-text'>Your spirits rise as you are drawing near to the East Gate of Moria. But then a huge, dark shape rises in front of you and bursts into flames: a Balrog! Durin's Bane blocks your escape.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add the set-aside Durin's Bane to the staging area. It cannot take damage this round. If there is more than 1 player, it makes an immediate attack against the first player.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Nearing-the-Gate-Last-Lord-of-Moria-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>Durin's Bane engages the first player.</p><p class='main-text'>Durin's Bane cannot take more than X damage per round, where X is the number of progress tokens on this stage.</p><p class='main-text'>This stage cannot be defeated while Durin's Bane is in play. If the players defeat this stage, they win the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Nearing-the-Gate-The-Rear-Guard-EfKD", "<p class='flavor-text'>Your spirits rise as you are drawing near to the East Gate of Moria. But then a huge, dark shape rises in front of you and bursts into flames: a Balrog! Durin's Bane blocks your escape.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add the set-aside Durin's Bane to the staging area. It cannot take damage this round. If there is more than 1 player, it makes an immediate attack against the first player.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Nearing-the-Gate-The-Rear-Guard-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>Each player's threat cannot be reduced by player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>Durin's Bane is considered to be engaged with each player and attacks each player in turn order during the combat phase. (Deal and resolve a shadow card for each attack.)</p><p class='main-text'>If the players defeat this stage, they win the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dark-Pit-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> The opposing team searches the top 5 cards of the encounter deck for a card with cost 1 or less (cost 2 or less instead if there are 2 or more players), sets it aside, and shuffles the encounter deck. Reveal the set aside card. Its 'when revealed' effects cannot be canceled.</p>");
            AddHtml("Durin's-Bane-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>Immuned to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>Cannot be optionally engaged.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Durin's Bane attacks and destroys a character you control, raise your threat by 2 and heal 2 damage from Durin's Bane.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Black-Bats-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Eithe raise each player's threat by 2, or reveal an additional encounter card.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Either raise your threat by 2, or this attack is considered undefended.</p>");
            AddHtml("Nest-of-Vermin-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>While Nest of Vermin is in the staging area, each Creature enemy gets +1 {Threat}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Nest of Vermin is explored, the opposing team searches the encounter deck and discard pile for a Creature enemy with cost 1 or less and adds it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Swarm-of-Bats-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each character gets -1{Willpower} until the end of the phase.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Each character you control gets -1{Attack} and -1{Defense} until the end of the phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Cave-Spider-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Cave Spider attacks, either remove 2 progress from the main quest, or Cave Spider gets +2 {Attack} for this attack.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Either remove 2 progress from the main quest or attacking enemy gets +2 {Attack}</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Mountain's-Roots-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>X is 1 more than the stage number of the main quest.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Each player discards the top X cards of his deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Watchful-Eyes-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team attaches Watchful Eyes to a hero. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text: &quot;Limit 1 per hero.<b>Forced:</b> If attached hero is exhausted at the end of the combat phase, reveal 1 card from the encounter deck.&quot;)</p>");
            AddHtml("Cave-troll-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have non-objective player card attachments.</p><p class='main-text'>Allies cannot be declared as attackers or defenders against Cave-troll.</p>");
            AddHtml("Twisting-Passage-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Discard the top card of the encounter deck. If that card is a location, add it to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Undisturbed-Bones-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach to the main quest. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text,<b>&quot;Forced:</b> When a 'when revealed' effect would be canceled, discard Undisturbed Bones instead.&quot;)</p>");
            AddHtml("Old-Stone-troll-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have non-objective player card attachments.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Old Stone-troll attachs and destroys a character you control, raise your threat by 1 for each excess point of damage dealt.</p>");
            AddHtml("Frightful-Den-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>While Frightful Den is in the staging area, each Troll enemy gets -10 engagement cost.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Frightful Den is explored, the opposing team searches the encounter deck and discard pile for a Troll enemy with cost 1 or less and adds it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Deep-Deep-Dark-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must choose: either raise your threat by 1 for each character you control, or discard a character you control.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Raise your threat by 1 for each enemy engaged with you.</p>");
            AddHtml("Rock-Adder-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>Players cannot declare defenders against Rock Adder.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack is undefended, attacking enemy gets +2 {Attack}</p>");
            AddHtml("Bottomless-Chasm-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>When faced with the option to travel, the player must choose Bottomless Chasm, if able.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +2 {Defense} until the end of the phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Lost-and-Alone-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team chooses a questing charactert controlled by each player and removes them from the quest.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Defending character cannot ready until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Hobgoblin-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Hobgobling engages a player, it cannot take damage until the end of the round.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy cannot take damage this phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Western-Hall-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Discard the top card of the encounter deck. Raise each player's threat by X, where X is that card's printed{Threat}</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack destroys a character, reveal the top card of the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("New-Devilry-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Until the end of the round, treat each character's text box as if it were blank, except for Traits.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Until the end of the phase, treat the defending character's text box as blank, except for Traits.</p>");
            AddHtml("Unspeakable-Thing-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Unspeakable Thing attacks you, discard the top card of your deck. Unspeakable thing gets +X{Attack} for this attack, where X is the discarded card's printed cost.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack}</p>");
            AddHtml("Lightless-Grotto-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>While Lightless Grotto is in the staging area, non-unique enemies in the staging area cannot take damage.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> The first player chooses an enemy in the staging area and engages it.</p>");
            AddHtml("Many-Roads-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team searches the encounter deck and discard pile for a different 0-cost location per player and adds them to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The opposing team shuffles a location from the encounter discard pile into the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Shadow-Dweller-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have non-objective player card attachments or take non-combat damage.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Shadow Dweller attacks you, discard the top card of your deck and assign X damage among character you control, where X is the discarded card's cost.</p>");
            AddHtml("Branching-Paths-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>Branching Paths gets +1 {Threat} for each location in the staging area. (Limit +3{Threat}</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack}</p>");
            AddHtml("Fatigue-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player exhausts a character he controls. Until the end of the round, characters cannot be readied by player card effects.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Remove the defending character from the attack. A different defending character may be declared.</p>");
            AddHtml("Elder-Nameless-Thing-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot be optionally engaged.</p><p class='main-text'>While Elder Nameless Thing is in the staging area, it gains:<b>&quot;Forced:</b> After players have committed characters to the quest, Elder Nameless Thing makes an attack against the first player.</p>");
            AddHtml("Silent-Caverns-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>While Silent Caverns is in the staging area, each player's threat cannot be reduced by more than 1 each round.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Raise each player's threat by 2.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dark-Places-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Raise each player's threat by X, where X is the threat of the active location. If there is no active location, Dark Places gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +X{Attack} where X is the stage number of the main quest.</p>");
            AddHtml("Orc-Horn-Blower-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of the combat phase, deal each engaged enemy an additional shadow card.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Deal attacking enemy 2 additional shadow cards.</p>");
            AddHtml("Goblin-Dungeon-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team chooses an ally, discards all tokens from it, and places it faceup as a guarded objective. When Goblin Dungeon is explored, return that ally to its owner's control exhausted.</p>");
            AddHtml("Deep-Fissure-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player deals 1 damage to a questing character he controls and removes that character from the quest.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Deal 1 damage to a character you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Black-Uruks-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>While Black Uruks is attacking, it gets +1 {Attack} for each shadow card dealt for this attack.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The opposing team searches the top 5 cards of the encounter deck for a card and deals it to attacking enemy as a shadow card.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dreadful-Gap-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>While Dreadful Gap is in the staging area, progress cannot be placed on other locations in the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> The opposing team chooses a card in the encounter discard pile and shuffles it into the encounter deck.</p>{victory:3}");
            AddHtml("Orcish-Howls-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Exhaust X characters, where X is the number of Uruk enemies in play. If there are no Uruk enemies in play, Orcish Howls gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} (+2 {Attack} instead if it is an Uruk).</p>");
            AddHtml("Orc-Raiders-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Orc Raider engages a player, deal it a shadow card.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} Deal it an additional shadow card.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Great-Bridge-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>While The Great Bridge is in the staging area, no more than 1 character can be declared as an attacker against each enemy.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When The Great Bridge is explored, reveal 1 encounter card per player.</p>");
            AddHtml("Vast-and-Intricate-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team attaches Vast and Intricate to a non-unique location in the staging area. If there are no non-unique locations in the staging area, Vast and Intricate gains surge. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text: &quot;Attached location gets +2 {Threat} and is immune to player card effects.&quot;)</p>");
            AddHtml("Chieftain-of-the-Pit-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have non-objective player card attachments or take non-combat damage.</p><p class='main-text'>Shadow effects cannot be canceled.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Chieftain of the Pit attacks, deal it an additional shadow card.</p>");
            AddHtml("Forked-Passage-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>While Forked Passage is in the staging area, raise each player's threat by 1 additional point during the refresh phase.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Raise each player's threat by 1.</p>");
            AddHtml("Chance-Encounter-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The highest{Attack} enemy in the staging area makes an attack against the first player. If no attack is made this way, Chance Encounter gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If attacking enemy is unique, it makes an additional attack against you after this one.</p>");
            AddHtml("Nameless-Thing-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Nameless Thing enters play, the first player attaches the top card of his deck to it faceup as a guarded attached. Nameless Thing gets +X{Threat} +X{Attack} and +X{Defense} where X is that card's printed cost. When Nameless Thing leaves play, discard that card.</p>");
            AddHtml("Mithril-Lode-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'>While Mitril Lode is the active location, it gains:<b>&quot;Response:</b> When Mithril Lode is explored, each player adds 1 resource to the resource pool of a hero he controls.</p>");
            AddHtml("A-Foe-Beyond-EfKD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team chooses an attachment controlled by a player and discards it. If no attachment is discarded this way, A Foe Beyond gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Discard an attachment you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Search-for-an-Exit-A-Way-Up-EfKD-PRM", "<p class='flavor-text'>The Mines of Moria are vast beyond your imagination. Though you feel that you are making progress, one wrong turn could mean disaster.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The opposing team searches the top 5 cards of the encounter deck for a card with cost 1 or less (cost 2 or less instead if there are two or more players), sets it aside, and shuffles the encounter deck. Reveal the set aside card. It's 'when revealed' effects cannot be canceled.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Search-for-an-Exit-A-Way-Up-EfKD-PRM", "<p class='main-text'>Add the active location's{Threat} to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'>During the travel phase, the players must travel, if able.</p>");
            AddHtml("Durin's-Bane-EfKD-PRM", "<p class='main-text'>Immuned to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>Cannot be optionally engaged.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Durin's Bane attacks and destroys a character you control, raise your threat by 2 and heal 2 damage from Durin's Bane.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Black-Bats-EfKD-PRM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Eithe raise each player's threat by 2, or reveal an additional encounter card.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Either raise your threat by 2, or this attack is considered undefended.</p>");
            AddHtml("Lightless-Grotto-EfKD-PRM", "<p class='main-text'>While Lightless Grotto is in the staging area, non-unique enemies in the staging area cannot take damage.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> The first player chooses an enemy in the staging area and engages it.</p>");
        }

        private void TheHuntForTheDreadnaught()
        {
            AddHtml("Easy-Mode-THftD", "<p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b></p><p class='main-text'> Players prepare their fleet.</p><p class='main-text'> Prepare the Corsair deck.</p><p class='main-text'> Set the following enemies aside: all 7 unique enemies (including the Dreadnaught), 2 copies of Black Sails, and 1 copy of Corsair Warship.</p><p class='main-text'> Add the Cobas Haven loction to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p><p class='main-text'> Add 1 resource to each hero's resource pool.</p><p class='main-text'> Flip this card over and place it next to the quest deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Easy-Mode-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Each player draws 1 additional card during the resource phase.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Quest Action:</b> Deal 10 damage to a non-unique enemy engaged with a player in any group. (Group limit once per game.)</p><p class='main-text'>If a player controls no ship-objective, that player is eliminated from the game.</p><p class='flavor-text'>And looking thither they cried in dismay; for black against the glittering stream they beheld a fleet of borne up on the wind: dromunds, and ships of great draught with many oars, and with black sails bellying in the breeze.<br>&ndash;The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Standard-Mode-THftD", "<p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b></p><p class='main-text'> Players prepare their fleet.</p><p class='main-text'> Prepare the Corsair deck.</p><p class='main-text'> Set the following enemies aside: all 7 unique enemies (including the Dreadnaught).</p><p class='main-text'> Shuffle the encounter deck and discard cards from the top until 2 locations are discarded (3 locations instead if there are 3 or more players). Add those locations to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'> Flip this card over and place it next to the quest deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Standard-Mode-THftD", "<p class='main-text'><b>Quest Action:</b> Deal 10 damage to a non-unique enemy engaged with a player in any group. (Group limit once per game.)</p><p class='main-text'>If a player controls no ship-objective, that player is eliminated from the game.</p><p class='flavor-text'>And looking thither they cried in dismay; for black against the glittering stream they beheld a fleet of borne up on the wind: dromunds, and ships of great draught with many oars, and with black sails bellying in the breeze.<br>&ndash;The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Hard-Mode-THftD", "<p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b></p><p class='main-text'> Players prepare their fleet.</p><p class='main-text'> Prepare the Corsair deck.</p><p class='main-text'> Set the following enemies aside: all 7 unique enemies (including the Dreadnaught).</p><p class='main-text'> Add 3 Tolfalas Landing locations to the staging area (3 Tolfalas Landing locations and 2 Wicked Cove locations if there are 3 or more players). Shuffle the encounter deck.</p><p class='main-text'> Flip this card over and place it next to the quest deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Hard-Mode-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Each player's threat cannot be reduced by more than 1 each round.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After a character is healed or readied by a player card effect, its controller raises their threat by 1.</p><p class='main-text'>If a player controls no ship-objective, that player is eliminated from the game.</p><p class='flavor-text'>And looking thither they cried in dismay; for black against the glittering stream they beheld a fleet of borne up on the wind: dromunds, and ships of great draught with many oars, and with black sails bellying in the breeze.<br>&ndash;The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Searching-the-High-Seas-THftD", "<p class='flavor-text'>The vicious Corsairs of Umbar have been pillaging the Gondorian coastline for months, and rumors are swirling that they've built the most devastating and gigantic ship ever known: The Dreadnaught. Many are suspicious of such extraordinary reports but, if true, the massive enemy is unlike any you've faced before. It will take an equally&ndash;colossal effort to take down such a potent foe. No others can bear such a difficult task, so it's up to the heroes to assemble a formidable fleet, and then scour the seas for the mighty warship.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Searching-the-High-Seas-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>*This stage has a global quest point value of 8 per player among all groups.</p><p class='main-text'>No more than 5 progress per player can be placed on this stage each round.</p><p class='main-text'>The players can only advance at the end of the quest phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Destroy-the-Dreadnaught-THftD", "<p class='flavor-text'>In the distance, you see a ship like no other: dozens of ominous black sails tower above the churning sea and prow of a fearsome serpent's head slices through the waves at an alarming speed. The rumors are true. You are awestruck at the extraordinary size and imtimidating presence of the Dreadnaught. You resolve to sink the menacing behemoth at all costs.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add the set-aside Dreadnaught enemy to the staging area, Elite side faceup.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Destroy-the-Dreadnaught-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>No more than 5 progress per player can be placed on this stage each round.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Remove 5 progress per player from this stage to choose any group to shuffle 1 set aside Gondorian Warship card into their encounter deck.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> When the Dreadnaught attacks you, raise your threat by 4 to cancel the attack.</p><p class='main-text'>When the Dreadnaught is destroyed, the players win the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Eithiliant-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'>Each hero you control gets +1 {Willpower}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Choose a hero you control. Until the end of the game, that hero gains the printed Traits of another hero you control.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The Eithiliant, or &quot;The Rainbow Spearpoint,&quot;, is an extremely swift elvent schooner featuring a swan motif.</p>");
            AddHtml("Eithiliant-Upgraded-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'>Each hero you control gets +2 {Willpower}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Eithiliant flips, shuffle up to 6 cards from your discard pile into your deck. Place 6 progress on a location in any group.</p>");
            AddHtml("Golden-Wing-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Ranged. Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'>Each hero you control gets +1 hit point.</p><p class='main-text'>Reduce your threat by 3. Choose a hero you control. Until the end of the game, that hero gains ranged.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The Golden Wing is equipped with a massive ballista.</p>");
            AddHtml("Golden-Wing-Upgraded-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Ranged. Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'>Each hero you control gains +2 hit points and gains ranged.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Golden Wing flips, deal 6 damage to an enemy in any group.</p>");
            AddHtml("Pride-of-Lebennin-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'>Each hero you control gets +1 {Defense}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When you draw your starting hand, draw 5 additional cards, then shuffle 5 cards from your hand into your deck. You cannot take a mulligan.</p>");
            AddHtml("Pride-of-Lebennin-Upgraded-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'>Each hero you control gets +2 {Defense}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Pride of Lebennin flips, heal 2 damage from a character. Choose up to 2 cards from the encounter discard pile and add them to the victory display.</p>");
            AddHtml("Silent-Mist-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'>Your starting hand size is 8 cards.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Play an event from your hand with a cost 3 or more, reducing its cost by 1.</p><p class='flavor-text'>An exquisite work of elven craftsmanship, the number Silent Mist bear the symbol of the Star of E„rendil on its foresail.</p>");
            AddHtml("Silent-Mist-Upgraded-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Silent Mist flips, choose up to 2 events from your discard pile and/or your collection and add them to your hand (following deckbuilding rules).</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Play an event from your hand with cost 3 or more, reducing its cost by 2.</p>");
            AddHtml("Swan-Ship-of-Dol-Amroth-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Add 1 resource to each of your heroes' resource pools.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Spend 2 resources to ready a character. (Limit once per round.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>The wealth of Gondor financed the construction of impressive ships which inspired all who sailed them.</p>");
            AddHtml("Swan-Ship-of-Dol-Amroth-Upgraded-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Swan Ship of Dol Amroth flips, add 2 resources to a hero's resource pool. Ready a card.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Spend 1 resource to ready a card. (Limit once per round.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Twilight's-Call-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'>The first card you play each round does not require a resource match.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Play an ally or attachment from your hand. (Limit once per round.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>Exceptionally agile for its size. Twilight's Call is adept at launching surprise attacks as daylight fades.</p>");
            AddHtml("Twilight's-Call-Upgraded-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'>Each card you play does not require a resource match.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Twilight's Call flips, draw 3 cards.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Play an ally or attachment from your hand.</p>");
            AddHtml("Gondorian-Warship-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Ranged. Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Choose a player. That player gains control of Gondorian Warship.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Gondorian Warship is destroyed, set it aside, out of play.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Deal 5 damage to attacking enemy.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dreadnaught-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Archery 1{PerPlayer} Immune to player card effects. Cannot take more than 5{PerPlayer} damage each round.</p><p class='main-text'>*The Dreadnaught has global hit point value (15 hit points for each player among all groups).</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round if the Dreadnaught has less than half of its starting hit pints, flip it over.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Able to fight numerous ships at once with its ramming prow and bllistae, the Dreadnaught's potency is truly unparalleled.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dreadnaught-Damaged-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Massive}. Immune to player card effects. Cannot take more than 5 {PerPlayer} damage each round.</p><p class='main-text'>*The Dreadnaught has a global hit point value of 15 per player among all groups.</p><p class='main-text'>Forced: After the Dreadnaught flips, each player puts 1 set-aside unique {trait:Corsair.@Corsair} enemy into play at random engaged with them.</p><p class='flavor-text'>With the Dreadnaught weakened and in peril, its enraged crew begins boarding your ship in a final attempt to sieze victory.</p>{victory:99}");
            AddHtml("Captain-of-the-Haven-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. {keyword:Pillage 8.}</p><p class='main-text'>Engaged player cannot attack the Dreadnaught.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the combat phase, if engaged player has no cards in their deck, that player is eliminated from the game.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Commander-of-the-Dreadnaught-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>Engaged player cannot attack the Dreadnaught.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Commander of the Dreadnaught attacks you, the Dreadnaught attacks you.</p><p class='flavor-text'>If the Dreadnaught is fated to go under, its commander will surely try to take his foes down with it.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Descendant-of-Castamir-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>Engaged player cannot attack the Dreadnaught.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Descendant of Castamir engages you, put the top 2 cards of the Corsair deck into play engaged with you and deal each of them 1 shadow card.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Hydraken-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player cards effects.</p><p class='main-text'>Engaged player cannot attack the Dreadnaught.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Hydraken attacks, he makes an additional attack. Deal him 2 additional shadow cards for this attack and engaged player raises their threat by 4. (Limit once per round.)</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Ophidian-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. No more than 1 character can attack Ophidian each round.</p><p class='main-text'>Engaged player cannot attack the Dreadnaught.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When a character defends against Ophidian, deal 2 damage to that character.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Varjax-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Archery 3. Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>Engaged player cannot attack the Dreadnaught.</p><p class='main-text'>For each point of excess combat damage dealt by Varjax, defending player deals 1 damage to a Ship they control.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Brash-Corsair-THftD", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When engaged player exhausts a Ship objective, Brash Corsair attacks that player.</p><p class='flavor-text'>'The Corsair of Umbar!' men shouted. 'The Corsairs of Umbar! Look! The Corsairs of Umbar are coming!'<br>&ndash;The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Corsair-Plunderer-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Pillage 2. (After this enemy attacks you, discard the top 2 cards of your deck.)</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After an event card is discarded from your deck by Corsair Plunderer's Pillage keyword, discard an attachment you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Daring-Buccaneer-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Pillage 3. <i>(After this enemy attacks you, discard the top 3 cards of your deck.)</i></p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After an event card is discarded from your deck by Daring Buccaneer's Pillage keyword, deal 1 damage to a character you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Fierce-Marauder-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Pillage 3. (After this enemy attacks you, discard the top 3 cards of your deck.)</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After an event card is discarded from your deck by Fierce Marauder's Pillage keyword, discard 1 resource from the resource pool of a hero you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Southron-Sailor-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>While Southron Sailor is engaged with you, each Ship enemy engaged with you contributes its{Threat} to the total{Threat} in the staging area.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&quot;There is a great fleet drawing near to the mouths of the Anduin, manned by the corsairs of Umbar in the South.&quot;<br>&ndash;Beregond, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Umbar-Captain-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Engaged player cannot attack Ship enemies.</p><p class='flavor-text'>...the strength of the rebels in Umbar was a great peril to Gondor...<br>&ndash;The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Black-Sails-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Boarding 2.} Cannot have attachments.</p><p class='main-text'>While Black Sails is in the staging area, it gains Archery 3.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If attacking enemy is a Ship return it to the staging area after this attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Corsair-Skiff-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Surge.} Cannot have attachments.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Corsair Skiff engages you from the staging area, eithe raise your threat by 3 or it gains Bording 1.</p>");
            AddHtml("Corsair-Skirmisher-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Boarding 1.} Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Corsair Skirmisher is destroyed as an enemy, the engaged player may discard allies they control with a total of at least 3{Willpower} to take control of Corsair Skirmisher as a ship-objective with{Willpower} equal to its{Threat} (It loses the ship-enemy card type and gaines the ship-objective card type).</p>");
            AddHtml("Corsair-Warship-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Boarding 3.} Cannot have attachments.</p><p class='main-text'>While Corsair Warship is in the staging area, it cannot be damaged and gains Archery 4.</p><p class='flavor-text'>...ships of great draught with many oars, and with black sails bellying in the breeze.<br>&ndash;The Return of the King</p>{victory:6}");
            AddHtml("Ramming-Ship-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have attachments.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Ramming Ship engages you, it gets +4{Attack} until the end of the round.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Put the top card of the Corsair deck into play engaged with you and deal it 1 shadow card.</p>");
            AddHtml("Slave-Ship-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Boarding 1.} Cannot have attachments.</p><p class='main-text'>For each point of damage that is dealt to a Ship objective by Slave Ship's attack, deal 1 point of damage to a non-Ship character controlled by the defending player, as well.</p>");
            AddHtml("War-Galley-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Archery 2.} {keyword:Boarding 1.} Cannot have attachments.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When War Galley engages you from the staging area, either raise your threat by 4 or it gains Boarding 1.</p>");
            AddHtml("Sea-Monster-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Ship objectives may attack and defend against Sea Monster.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Deal 4 damage to the Ship enemy or Ship objective with the fewest remaining hit points.</p>");
            AddHtml("Belfalas-Shipyard-THftD", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Belfalas Shipyard is explored as the active location, the players as a group spend 5 resources to heal 5 damage from a Ship objective in any group. Ready that Ship and flip it to its Upgraded side.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} and gains Pillage 3.</p>");
            AddHtml("Cobas-Haven-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>While Cobas Haven is the active location, reduce the Boading value on each Ship enemy by 1.</p><p class='flavor-text'>But beyond, in the great fief of Belfalas, dwelt Prince Imrahil in his castle of Dol Amroth by the sea.<br>&ndash;The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Isle-of-Fortune-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Isle of Fortune enters play with 1 resource per player on it.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After a Ship enemy enters play, discard 1 resource from Isle of Fortune.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> When Isle of Fortune is explored as the active location, move each resource on it to a hero's resource pool.</p>");
            AddHtml("Mouths-of-Anduin-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>While Mouths of Anduin is in the staging area, is gains:<b>&quot;Forced:</b> After a 'when revealed' effect is canceled, reveal the top card of the encounter deck.&quot;</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack is undefended, reveal the top card of the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Tolfalas-Landing-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>While Tofalas Landing is in the staging area, it gains:<b>&quot;Forced:</b> After a player draws any number of cards from a player card effect, that player raises their threat by that number.&quot;</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Raise your threat by 1 (3 instead if you have 5 or more cards in hand).</p>");
            AddHtml("Wicked-Cove-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Each location in the staging area is immune to player card effects.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Until the end of the round, attacking enemy is immune to player card effects and gets +2 {Defense}</p>");
            AddHtml("Ballista-Barrage-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Doomed 1. (Raise each players threat by 1.)</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Until the end of the round, each Ship enemy gains Archery 2.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Assign 2 damage among characters you control (3 damage instead if there are 10 or more cards in your discard pile).</p>");
            AddHtml("Boarding-Party-THftD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player puts the top card of the Corsair deck into play engaged with them.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} (+2 {Attack} instead if you control an exhausted Ship objective).</p>");
            AddHtml("Grappled-THftD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach to a Ship objective. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text: &quot;Attached objective cannot ready.<b>Action:</b> Exhaust 3 characters to discard Grappled!&quot;)</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If defending character is a Ship attach Grappled! to it.</p>");
            AddHtml("Out-of-the-Mist-THftD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The enemy with the highest engagement cost engages the first player and attacks them. If no attack is made this way, Out of the Mist gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Either raise your threat by 4 or attacking enemy makes an additional attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Overworked-THftD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Until the end of the round, treat the text box of each non-Ship ally as blank, except for Traits. If a player controls 7 or more allies, Overworked gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} (+3{Attack} instead if you control 7 or more allies).</p>");
            AddHtml("Taking-on-Water-THftD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach to a Ship objective. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text:<b>&quot;Forced:</b> When attached objective exhausts, deal 2 damage to it.<b>Action:</b> Exhaust 3 characters to discard Taking on Water.&quot;)</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If defending character is a Ship attach Taking on Water to it.</p>");
            AddHtml("Violent-Tempest-THftD", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Deal 1 damage to each enemy. Each player assigns X among characters they control. X is the number of exhausted characters they control.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Deal 1 damage to the defending character.</p>");
            AddHtml("A-Perilous-Voyage-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Your minimum deck size is 100 cards.</p><p class='main-text'>Your threat cannot be reduced by player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust this card and raise your threat by 1 to look at the top 2 cards of your deck, draw 1, and place the other on the bottom of your deck.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When you would be eliminated by reaching your threat elimination level, flip this card over instead.</p>");
            AddHtml2("A-Perilous-Voyage-THftD", "<p class='main-text'>Your threat cannot be reduced by non-contract player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>Heroes you control do not exhaust to quest.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When this card is flipped to this side, reduce your threat by 10. Search your deck for a card and either add it to your hand or play it, reducing its cost by 3. Shuffle your deck.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Thus came Aragorn... borne upon a wind from the Sea to the kingdom of Gondor...<br>&ndash;The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Passage-Through-Mirkwood-Nightmare-PTMN", "<p class='main-text'>You are playing Nightmare mode.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> During setup, each player reveals 1 card from the encounter deck and adds it to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Passage-Through-Mirkwood-Nightmare-PTMN", "<p class='main-text'>Begin with the standard quest deck and encounter deck for the Passage Through Mirkwood scenario found in the LOTR LCG core set.</p><p class='main-text'>Remove the following cards, in the specified quantities, from the standard encounter deck:</p><p class='main-text'>Ungoliant's Spawn x1</p><p class='main-text'>Black Forest Bats x1</p><p class='main-text'>Forest Spider x3</p><p class='main-text'>Dol Guldur Orcs x3</p><p class='main-text'>Old Forest Road x1</p><p class='main-text'>Forest Gate x2</p><p class='main-text'>Mountains of Mirkwood x3</p><p class='main-text'>Caught in a Web x2</p><p class='main-text'>Then, shuffle the encounter cards in this Nightmare Deck into the remainder of the standard Passage Through Mirkwood encounter deck.</p><p class='main-text'>Finally, flip this setup card over and place it next to the quest deck. Its effect remains active throughout the game, which is now ready to begin.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ungoliant's-Spawn-PTMN", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Until the end of the phase, each character currently committed to the quest gets -2{Willpower} and is discarded if its{Willpower} is 0.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Raise defending player's threat by 5. (Raise defending player's threat by 10 instead if undefended.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Ungoliant's-Brood-PTMN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After you engage Ungoliant's Brood, your cards cannot ready for the remainder of the round.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack is undefended, exhaust all characters you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Forest-Flies-PTMN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After you engage Forest Flies, deal 1 damage to each exhausted character you control.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If attacking enemy is an Insect deal it 2 additional shadow cards.</p>");
            AddHtml("Spiders-of-Mirkwood-PTMN", "<p class='main-text'>While it is engaged with you, Spiders of Mirkwood gets +1 for each exhausted character you control.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Choose and exhaust 1 character you control. If this attack is undefended, also deal that character 2 damage.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Spider's-Web-PTMN", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The player with the highest threat exhausts all heroes he controls. Then, attach this card to one of that player's heroes. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text, &quot;Each time attached hero readies, deal it 1 damage.&quot;)</p>");
            AddHtml("Backtrack-PTMN", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The topmost enemy or location card in the encounter discard pile is returned to the staging area.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Deal and resolve the topmost Shadow effect in the encounter discard pile for this attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Abandoned-Camp-PTMN", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Abandoned Camp leaves play, each player must deal 2 damage to each exhausted character he controls.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack is undefended, discard all attachment cards players control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Glade-of-the-Spawn-PTMN", "<p class='main-text'>While Glade of the Spawn is the active location, it gains:<b>&quot;Forced:</b> After a Spider enemy enters play, each player must choose and exhaust 1 character he controls.&quot;</p><p class='flavor-text'>...black even for that forest, like a patch of midnight that had never been cleared away. &ndash;The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("Journey-Along-the-Anduin-Nightmare-JAtAN", "<p class='main-text'>You are playing Nightmare mode.</p><p class='main-text'>All Troll enemies gain the text: &quot;Cannot have attachments.&quot;</p><p class='main-text'>If the encounter deck is empty (at any time), shuffle the encounter discard pile back into the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Journey-Along-the-Anduin-Nightmare-JAtAN", "<p class='main-text'>Begin with the standard quest deck and encounter deck for the Journey Along the Anduin scenario found in the LOTR LCG core set.</p><p class='main-text'>Remove the following cards, in the specified quantities, from the standard encounter deck:</p><p class='main-text'>3x Evil Storm</p><p class='main-text'>2x Treacherous Fog</p><p class='main-text'>2x Banks of the Anduin</p><p class='main-text'>3x Dol Guldur Orcs</p><p class='main-text'>2x Enchanted Stream</p><p class='main-text'>2x Despair</p><p class='main-text'>3x Misty Mountain Goblins</p><p class='main-text'>2x Necromancer's Pass</p><p class='main-text'>Then, shuffle the encounter cards in this Nightmare Deck into the remainder of the standard Journey Along the Anduin encounter deck.</p><p class='main-text'>Finally, flip this setup card over and place it next to the quest deck. Its effects remain active throughout the game, which is now ready to begin.</p>");
            AddHtml("Marshland-Outlaws-JAtAN", "<p class='main-text'>If you are engaged with this enemy, you cannot attack or deal damage (through effects) to enemies with a title other than Marshland Outlaws.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Raise your threat by X. X is the amount of damage dealt by this attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Anduin-Troll-Spawn-JAtAN", "<p class='main-text'>If there is no Hill Troll in play, Anduin Troll Spawn gains surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of the combat phase, Anduin Troll Spawn engages a player engaged with a Hill Troll.</p>");
            AddHtml("Brown-Water-Rats-JAtAN", "<p class='main-text'>Brown Water Rats cannot be damaged.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> If the players are on stage 3 and all remaining enemies have the printed Rat trait, discard Brown Water Rats from play.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy cannot be damaged this round.</p>");
            AddHtml("A-Flooded-Ford-JAtAN", "<p class='main-text'>Each card revealed by the encounter deck gains doomed X. X is the number of progress tokens on this card.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack is undefended, put A Flooded Ford into the staging area with 1 progress token on it.</p>");
            AddHtml("Gladden-Marshlands-JAtAN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Deal 1 damage to a hero you control to reduce Gladden Marshlands{Threat} by 1 until the end of the phase. Any player may trigger this effect.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Each enemy engaged with the defender player gets +1 {Attack} until the end of the phase. (+2 {Attack} instead if this attack is undefended.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Pursuit-on-the-Shore-JAtAN", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Search the victory display and encounter discard pile for the enemy with the most hit points. Return that enemy to the staging area. If no enemy is returned by this effect, Pursuit on the Shore gains surge. (Cannot be canceled.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Troll-Attack-JAtAN", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> All engaged Troll enemies attack. If no Troll enemies are engaged, Troll{Attack} gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If attacking enemy is a Troll resolve this attack against each player.{Attack} is undefended against each player not engaged with this enemy.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Smoking-Blood-JAtAN", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Remove all damage from all enemies. Then, each player raises his threat by the amount of just removed from his engaged enemies. If no damage is removed by this effect, Smoking Blood gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Move all damage on this enemy to the defending character. (If undefended, move the damage to the hero damaged by this attack.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Escape-from-Dol-Guldur-Nightmare-EFDGN", "<p class='main-text'>You are playing Nightmare mode.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When stage 1B is revealed, the number of random heroes captured is determined by the number of players, as follows: 1-2 players = 1 hero captured, 3 players = 2 heroes captured, 4 players = 3 heroes captured. All captured heroes are turned face down and considered &quot;the prisoner,&quot; cannot be used, cannot be damaged, and do not collect resources until they are rescued, (A single player cannot have more than 1 hero captured by this effect.)</p>");
            AddHtml2("Escape-from-Dol-Guldur-Nightmare-EFDGN", "<p class='main-text'>Begin with the standard quest deck and encounter deck for the Escape from Dol Guldur scenario found in the LOTR LCG core set.</p><p class='main-text'>Remove the following cards, in the specified quantities, from the standard encounter deck:</p><p class='main-text'>2x Dol Guldur Orcs</p><p class='main-text'>2x Enchanted Stream</p><p class='main-text'>1x Great Forest Web</p><p class='main-text'>3x Mountains of Mirkwood</p><p class='main-text'>2x Caught in a Web</p><p class='main-text'>1x The Necromancer's Reach</p><p class='main-text'>1x Necromancer's Pass</p><p class='main-text'>2x Under the Shadow</p><p class='main-text'>2x Tower Gate</p><p class='main-text'>1x Iron Shackles</p><p class='main-text'>Then, shuffle the encounter cards in this Nightmare Deck into the remainder of the standard Escape from Dol Guldur encounter deck.</p><p class='main-text'>Finally, flip this setup card over and place it next to the quest deck. Its effects remain active throughout the game, which is now ready to begin.</p>");
            AddHtml("Torture-Master-EFDGN", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add 1 resource token to each Dol Guldur location in play.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Any hero damaged but not defeated by this attack is turned face down, as a &quot;prisoner.&quot; Then, if the players are on stage 3, return to stage 2B of the quest.</p>");
            AddHtml("Crazed-Captive-EFDGN", "<p class='main-text'>Doomed 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> If Crazed Captive is defeated, raise each players threat by 7.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If attacking enemy is not defeated this phase, raise defending player's threat by 7 at the end of the phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Spider-of-Dol-Guldur-EFDGN", "<p class='main-text'>If there are any unclaimed objectives in play, Spider of Dol Guldur gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +3{Attack} for each unclaimed objective in play.</p>");
            AddHtml("Torture-Chamber-EFDGN", "<p class='main-text'>If Torture Chamber has 4 or more resource tokens on it, all &quot;prisoners&quot; were killed, and the players have lost the game.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of each round, place 1 resource token on each Dol Guldur location in play.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dungeon-Labyrinth-EFDGN", "<p class='main-text'>Dungeon Labyrinth gets +1 {Threat} and +1 quest point for each resource token on it</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of each round, place 1 resource token on Dungeon Labyrinth for each player in the game.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&quot;Some here will remember that many years ago I myself dared to pass the doors of the Necromancer in Dol Guldur...&quot; &ndash;Gandalf, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Sentinel-of-Shadow-EFDGN", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The staging area gets +X{Threat} until the end of the phase, where X is twice the number of players in the game. If the players quest unsuccessfully this phase, put the Nazgûl of Dol Guldur into play (from any out of play area), engaged with the first player. (Cannot be canceled.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Catacomb-Inspection-EFDGN", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add 1 resource token to each Dol Guldur location in play.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If there is a Dol Guldur location in the staging area, move 1 resource token from each of your heroes' resource pools to that location. (Resolve this effect for each Dol Guldur location.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Dark-Interrogation-EFDGN", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must choose and discard cards from hand until he has only 2 cards in hand. (Each player with 2 or fewer cards in hand must instead reveal 1 card from the encounter deck.)</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Discard each card you control that has at least 1 copy of itself in your discard pile. (If this attack is undefended, each player must resolve this effect.)</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Hunt-for-Gollum-Nightmare-THfGN", "<p class='main-text'>You are playing Nightmare mode.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the refresh phase, choose an unclaimed Clue card not attached to a Mordor enemy and attach it to a Mordor enemy, if able. (If it was guarded, detach the encounter guarding it first. The newly attached Mordor enemy is now guarding it.)</p><p class='main-text'>If at any point there are four or more Clue cards attached to Mordor enemies, the players lose the game.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&quot;Through Mirkwood and back again it led them, though they never caught him.&quot;<br>&ndash;Gandalf, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Hunt-for-Gollum-Nightmare-THfGN", "<p class='main-text'>Begin with the standard quest deck and encounter deck for The Hunt for Gollum scenario.</p><p class='main-text'>Remove the following cards, in the specified quantities, from the standard encounter deck:</p><p class='main-text'>2x River Ninglor</p><p class='main-text'>1x The Eaves of Mirkwood</p><p class='main-text'>2x False Lead</p><p class='main-text'>2x Misty Mountain Goblins</p><p class='main-text'>2x Banks of the Anduin</p><p class='main-text'>3x Gladden Fields</p><p class='main-text'>3x Eastern Crows</p><p class='main-text'>2x Treacherous Fog</p><p class='main-text'>3x Evil Storm</p><p class='main-text'>Then, shuffle the encounter cards in this Nightmare Deck into the remainder of the standard The Hunt for Gollum encounter deck.</p><p class='main-text'>Finally, flip this setup card over and place it next to the quest deck. Its effect remains active throughout the game, which is now ready to begin.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ravenous-Hawk-THfGN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When a card effect instructs a player to &quot;look&quot; at cards in the encounter deck and Ravenous Hawk is among those cards, that player must put Ravenous Hawk into play engaged with him. (This does not satisfy the Forced effect of stage 1B or 2B).</p>");
            AddHtml("Hunting-Warg-THfGN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of the refresh phase, if Hunting Warg entered play this round, search the encounter deck and discard pile for 1 copy of Hunters from Mordor and add it to the staging area, if able. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&quot;...where the warg howls, there also the orc prowls.&quot;<br>&ndash;Aragorn, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Watched-Path-THfGN", "<p class='main-text'>Each player who does not control at least 1 Clue card cannot draw cards through card effects.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If you do not control at least 1 Clue card, discard all cards from your hand.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&quot;The Road is watched, but we should have to cross it...&quot;<br>&ndash;Aragorn, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Hunter's-Lookout-THfGN", "<p class='main-text'>Each Mordor enemy with at least 1 Clue card attached gets +2 {Defense}</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Defense} for each Clue card in play until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dark-Pools-THfGN", "<p class='main-text'>Progress cannot be placed on Dark Pools while it is in the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Dark Pools becomes the active location, each player must discard an ally with the highest printed cost among the allies he controls.</p><p class='flavor-text'>'And there in the dark pools amid the Gladden Fields,'he said, 'the Ring passed out of knowledge and legend...'<br>&ndash;The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Enemy's-Trail-THfGN", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Search the encounter discard pile for a Clue card and attach it to a Mordor enemy in play, if able. If no card is attached by this effect, The Enemy's Trail gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Search the encounter discard pile for a Clue card and attach it to a Mordor enemy in play, if able.</p>");
            AddHtml("Restless-Hunters-THfGN", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The first player chooses a Clue card attached to a hero and attaches it to a Mordor enemy in play, if able.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Damage from this attack must be applied to a hero you control with a Clue card attached, if able.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Trail-Goes-Cold-THfGN", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach to the active location and remove all progress from that location. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text:&quot;Limit 1 per location. Attached location contributes its{Threat} during the quest phase as if it were in the staging area.&quot;)</p><p class='main-text'>If The Trail Goes Cold does not attach to a location as a result of this effect, it gains surge.</p>");
        }

        private void TheDarkOfMirkwood()
        {
            AddHtml("Spiders-of-Mirkwood-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>While it is engaged with you, Spiders of Mirkwood gets +1 {Attack} for each exhausted character you control.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Choose and exhaust 1 character you control. If this attack was undefended, also deal that character 2 damage.</p>");
            AddHtml("Great-Spider-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Gret Spider engages you, exhaust a character you control.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Deal 1 damage to an exhausted character you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Eaves-of-Mirkwood-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>While The Eaves of Mirkwood is the active location, encounter card effects cannot be canceled.</p><p class='flavor-text'>By the afternoon they had reached the eaves of Mirkwood, and were resting almost beneath the great overhanging boughs of its outer trees.<br>&ndash;The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("Tangled-Grove-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>X is the number of locations in the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Each player must discard 1 random card from his hand to travel here.</p>");
            AddHtml("Forest-Gate-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After you travel to Forest Gate the first player draws 2 cards.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Soon the light in the gate was like a little bright hole far behind, and the quiet was so deep that their feet seemed to thump along while the trees leaned over them and listened.<br>&ndash;The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("Spider-Den-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Quest Action:</b> Search the encounter deck and discard pile for a Spider enemy and put it into play engaged with you to discard Spider Den. (Any player may trigger this effect.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Goblin-Trail-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Reveal the top card of the encounter deck to travel here.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> When Goblin Trail leaves play as an explored location, place 6 progress on the current quest.</p>{victory:3}");
            AddHtml("Driven-by-Shadow-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each enemy and each location currently in the staging area gets +1 {Threat} until the end of the phase. If there are no cards in the staging area, Driven by Shadow gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Choose and discard 1 attachment from the defending character. (If this attack is undefended, discard all attachments you control.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Surprising-Speed-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player returns 1 enemy engaged with him to the staging area. If no enemy was returned to the staging area this way, Surprising Speed gains surge and doomed 1.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} Return attacking enemy to the staging area after this attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Caught-in-a-Web-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The player with the highest threat level attached this card to one of his heroes. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text: &quot;Attached hero does not ready during the refresh phase unless you pay 2 resources from that hero's pool.&quot;)</p>");
            AddHtml("Goblin-Troop-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have attachments.</p><p class='main-text'>While Goblin Troop is engaged with you, each other Goblin enemy engaged with you gets +1 {Attack} and +1 {Defense}</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +2 {Attack}</p>");
            AddHtml("Goblin-Sniper-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>During the encounter phase, players cannot optionally engage Goblin Sniper if there are other enemies in the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> If Goblin Sniper is in the staging area at the end of the combat phase, each player deals 1 point of damage to 1 character he controls.</p>");
            AddHtml("Goblin-Runners-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy makes an additional attack immediately after this one. (Deal a new shadow card for that attack.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Goblintown-Scavengers-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Discard the top card of each player's deck. Until the end of the phase, increase Goblintown Savengers'{Threat} by the total printed cost of all cards discarded in this way.</p>");
            AddHtml("Goblins-are-Upon-You-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must search the encounter deck and discard pile for a Goblin enemy and put it into play, engaged with him. Then, shuffle the encounter deck. (This effect cannot be canceled.)</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} for each Goblin enemy engaged with you.</p>");
            AddHtml("Eyes-in-the-Dark-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>Doomed 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must choose: Either raise your threat by 1 for each questing character you control, or discard a questing character you control.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack is undefended, discard an ally you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Goblin-Chieftain-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>X is the stage number of the quest.</p><p class='main-text'>Cannot take damage. Cannot have attachments.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Goblin Chieftain attacks, either remove X progress from the quest, or return it to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Cracked-Pillar-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Cracked Pillar is in the staging area, it gains: &quot;The first player may declare an attack against Cracked Pillar during the combat phase as if it was an enemy engaged with him. Use Cracked Pillar's{Threat} as its{Defense} during this attack.&quot;</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Remove 4 damage from Cracked Pillar to travel here.</p>");
            AddHtml("Cave-Torch-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero. Restricted.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhause Cave Torch to place up to 3 progress tokens on a Dark location.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Cave Torch exhausts, discard the top card of the encounter deck. If that card is an enemy, add it to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Great-Cave-troll-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have attachments.</p><p class='main-text'>For each point of excess combat damage dealt by Great Cave-troll (damage that is dealt beyond the remaining hit points of the character damaged by its attack) remove 1 progress from the current quest.</p>");
            AddHtml("Cavern-Warg-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> When Cavern Warg attacks you, exhaust Cave Torch to cancel the attack and return Cavern Warg to the staging area.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack destroys a character, return attacking enemy to the staging area after this attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Goblin-Tunnels-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Goblin Tunnels is in the staging area, it gains:<b>&quot;Forced:</b> After a Goblin is revealed from the encounter deck, remove a progress token from the current quest card.&quot;</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} (+3{Attack} instead if attacking enemy is a Goblin.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Lightless-Passage-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Players must exhaust a Cave Torch to travel here.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Cancel all combat damage dealt to attacking enemy.</p>");
            AddHtml("Branching-Paths-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Branching Paths is in the staging area, each Dark location gets +1 {Threat}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Branching Paths leaves play as an explored location, look at the top 3 cards of the encounter deck. Players must choose 1 of those to reveal and add to the staging area, moving the other 2 to the bottom of the deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Collapsed-Mine-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Collapsed Mine is in the staging area, no more than 4 progress can be placed on the quest each round.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Raise your threat by 1 for each point of damage dealt by this attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Goblin-Dungeon-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Reveal the top card of the encounter deck to travel here.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Goblin Dungeon leaves play as an explored location, the first player searches the top 5 cards of his deck for an ally and puts it into play under his control. Shuffle the rest of the searched cards back into his deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Crumbling-Ruin-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must exhaust a character and discard the top card of his deck, if able. If the printed cost of the discarded card is equal to or higher than the remaining hit points of the exhausted character, discard the exhausted character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Lost-in-the-Dark-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The player who controls Cave Torch must choose: Either exhaust Cave Torch, or progress cannot be placed on the quest until the end of the phase. (Progress can still be placed on the active location.)</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Deal 1 damage to the defending character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Watchful-Eyes-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The first player attaches Watchful Eyes to one of his heroes. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text: &quot;Limit 1 per hero.<b>Forced:</b> If attached hero is exhausted at the end of the combat phase, reveal 1 card from the encounter deck and add it to the staging area.&quot;)</p>");
            AddHtml("After-the-Raid-TDoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>Marauding Goblins have raided a woodman village on the eaves of Mirkwood forest. The Goblins killed the guards and took many of the villages captive. Those left behind beg you to rescue their loved ones.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Search the encounter deck for 1 copy of The Eaves of Mirkwood and Goblin Troop. Add The Eaves of Mirkwood to the staging area and set Goblin Troop aside, out of play. Shuffle of the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("After-the-Raid-TDoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>You swear an oath to the survivors that you will rescue the captured woodmen and bring justice to the Goblins who attacked them, then you enter Mirkwood forest to find their trail.</p>");
            AddHtml("Mirkwood-Forest-TDoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>The Goblins' trail leads you deeper into the dark forest of Mirkwood. The enemy has a significant lead, but the sign of their passing is easy to follow. You may yet overtake them if you press on.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Mirkwood-Forest-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player searches the encounter deck and discard pile for a Forest location and adds it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck. This stage cannot be defeated unless at least 1 copy of Goblin Trail is in the vitory display.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Rearguard-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The first player adds the set-aside Goblin Troop to the staging area. Each other player searches the encounter deck and discard pile for a Goblin enemy and adds it to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Rearguard-TDoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>The Goblins are aware of your pursuit and form a rearguard to confront you while the others retreat to their secret hideaway. You must defeat this troop before you can continue your chanse.</p><p class='main-text'>This stage cannot be defeated while Goblin Troop is in play. When this stage is defeated, the heroes discover the trail to the Goblins' secret lair and the players win the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Dark-of-Nibin-Dum-TDoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>You have pursued the Goblins that attacked a woodman village to the mountains of Mirkwood. The trail leads over a steep ridge where you discover the forgotten Dwarf home of Nibin&ndash;D–m. You light a torch and enter in.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Search the encounter deck for Goblin Chieftain, Cracked Pillar, and Cave Torch. Set Goblin Chieftain and Cracked Pillar aside, out of play. The first player attached Cave Torch to one of his heroes. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Dark-of-Nibin-Dum-TDoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>The Dwarves abandonded Nibin&ndash;D–m after an earthquake collapsed part of the mine, but it seems these Goblins have since adopted it as their home. The flickering light of your torch reveals a network of dark passages and you set about searching for signs of the enemy.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player searches the encounter deck for a different location and adds it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Surprise-Attack-TDoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>As you search the caves of Nibin&ndash;D–m you are ambushed by Goblins!</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add Goblin Chieftain to the staging area. Each player searches the encounter deck and discard pile for a different enemy of his choice and adds it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Surprise-Attack-TDoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>The Goblins are led by a large chieftain who whips them into a frenzy. His soldiers attack you with reckless savagery and you struggle to gain the upper hand.</p><p class='main-text'>During the encounter phase, treat each enemy's engagement cost as if it were 0.</p><p class='main-text'>The stage gets +4 quest points for each enemy in play.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Chasm-TDoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>The Goblins retreat down a dark tunnel, and you chase them into a large hall of many pillars. A wide chasm runs the width of the hall and the Goblins race across on a large plank. Their chieftain casts the plan into the depths of the chasm and disappeats, leaving you stranded on the other side.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Set Goblin Chieftain aside, out of play. Add Cracked Pillar to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Chasm-TDoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>As you search for a way across, you see that one tall pillar near the edge of the chasm has cracked where it meets the ceiling. If you topple the pillar, it could serve to bridge the gap.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> Reveal an additional encounter card during the quest phase.</p><p class='main-text'>Progress cannot be placed on Cracked Pillar while it is in the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'>After Cracked Pillar leaves play as an explored location, advance to stage 4A.</p>");
            AddHtml("Oathkeepers-TDoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>You've made it across the chasm and resumed the chase. The Goblins rally around their chieftain outside the dungeons where the woodmen villagers are being held. You must defeat the big Goblin if you are to fulfill your oath and rescue the captives.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add Goblin Chieftain to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Oathkeepers-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>While there are at least 8 progress tokens on this stage, Goblin Chieftain loses the text: &quot;Cannot take damage.&quot;</p><p class='main-text'>This stage cannot be defeated while Goblin Chieftain is in play. When this stage is defeated, the heroes rescue the captives, fulfilling their oaths, and the players win the game!</p>");
            AddHtml("Crumbling-Stairs-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>While {self} is in the staging area, progress cannot be placed on it.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When {self} leaves play as an explored location, discard the top card of the encounter deck. If the discarded card is a location, put it into play as the active location.</p>");
            AddHtml("Wild-Wargs-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After {self} engages you, discard the top card of the encounter deck. If that card is a {trait:Goblin.@Goblin} enemy, put it into play engaged with you.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&ldquo;Where the Warg howls, there the Orc prowls.&rdquo;</p>");
            AddHtml("Obsidian-Arrows-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Deal 2 damage to a character you control.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Deal 1 damage to a character you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Abandoned-Camp-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After the players travel to {self}, the first player discards the top card of their deck, If that card is any ally, put it into play under their control.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Discard the top card of the encounter deck. If that card is an enemy, add it to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Stalking-Goblin-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After {self} engages you, search the encounter deck, discard pile, and your collection (in that order) for a Goblin Sniper and add it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Add {self} to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Shiny-Distraction-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Surge.} {keyword:Doomed 1.}</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player may add 1 resource to each of their heroes' pools. Each player that does raises their threat by 5.</p>");
            AddHtml("Guilty-Conscience-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Surge.}</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach to the hero with the highest threat cost. (Counts as an {trait:Adaptation.@Adaptation} attachment with the text: &ldquo;<b>Forced:</b> Raise your threat by 2 at the end of the round. <b>Action:</b> Spend 2 resources from attached hero's pool to discard this card.&rdquo;)</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Fervor-of-Lore-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Setup.} Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gains the {sphere:Lore} resource icon.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Choose and discard 3 cards from your hand to heal all damage from a hero. (Limit once per campaign. Record in the Campaign Log when used.)</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Might-of-Tactics-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Setup.} Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gains the {sphere:Tactics} resource icon.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Deal 1 damage to the attached hero to deal 3 damage to an enemy engaged with you. (Limit once per campaign. Record in the Campaign Log when used.)</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Power-of-Spirit-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Setup.} Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gains the {sphere:Spirit} resource icon.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust the attached hero to place 3 progress on a location. (Limit once per campaign. Record in Campaign Log when used.)</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Secret-of-Leadership-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Setup.} Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gains the {sphere:Leadership} resource icon.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Spend 1 resource the attached hero's recource pool to ready a hero. (Limit once per campaign. Record in Campaign Log when used.)</p>");
            AddHtml("No-Time-to-Waste-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>When playing this card, choose one:</p><p class='main-text'><b>Quest Action:</b> Remove {self} from the game and from the Campaign Pool to reduce each player's threat by 3. Reveal the top card of the encounter deck.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Quest Action:</b> Draw 1 card.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ranger-Sense-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>When playing this card, choose one:</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Remove {self} from the game and from the Campaign Pool to look at the top 4 cards of your deck. Add 1 to your hand and put the rest back in any order.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Draw 1 card.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Oath-Campaign-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>You are playing Campaign Mode.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Each player chooses 1 Adaptation boon attachment and attaches it to one of their heroes. Shuffle the Stalking Goblin burden enemy into the encounter deck. Add Stalking Goblin and each attached Adaptation to the Campaign Pool.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of each round, place 1 resource token here.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Oath-Campaign-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Resolution:</b> If there are 6 or more resource tokens here, the thought of the captured villagers suffering weighs heavily on you. Add the Guilty Conscience treachery burden to the Campaign Pool.</p><p class='flavor-text'>You have defeated the enemy rearguard, but the rest have escaped into the Mountains of Mirkwood with their prisoners. You must track the goblins to their hold if you are to fulfill your oath.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Caves-of-Nibin-Dum-Campaign-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'>You are playing Campaign Mode.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Each player adds a copy of the &ldquo;No Time to Waste!&rdquo; boon to their hand after drawing their starting hand (including taking a mulligan). Add each copy of &ldquo;No Time to Waste!&rdquo; in a player's hand to the Campaign Pool. Shuffle the Shiny Distraction burden into the encounter deck and add it to the Campaign Pool.</p><p class='flavor-text'>That, of course, is the dangerous part about caves: you don't know how far they go back...<br>&ndash;The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Caves-of-Nibin-Dum-Campaign-TDoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Resolution:</b> Check the final threat of the player with the highest threat: If it is under 40, you have rescued a retired Ranger who shares his wisdom with you. Each player may add 1 copy of Ranger Sense to their deck and to the Campaign Pool. At the start of your next campaign, each player may also shuffle 1 copy of Ranger Sense into their deck and add it to the Campaign Pool.</p><p class='flavor-text'>You have rescued the captives and fulfilled your oath. What Goblins remain flee in terror of your wrath, and your return journey is untroubled. The villagers who survived thank you endlessly for returning them to their village. They invited you to stay and live among them in honor, but your allegiance is to other lords and many journeys still await you. After a good night's rest, you depart in the morning.</p>");
        }

        private void FirstAge()
        {
            AddHtml("Hunting-of-the-Wolf-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Corruption</p><p class='main-text'>When a character takes Corruption place a progress token on it. If a character ever has Corruption greater than its willpower, it has become Corrupted. A Corrupted character loses the &quot;ally&quot; or &quot;hero&quot; card type and gains the &quot;enemy&quot; trait, immediately engaging the player that used to control it. The{Willpower} of the Corrupted character becomes its{Threat} and its engagement cost is 0.</p><p class='main-text'>Relentless</p><p class='main-text'>An enemy with Relentless cannot have its attack canceled or be prevented from attacking by any player card effect.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Hunting-of-the-Wolf-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Carcharoth Deck</p><p class='main-text'>During the quest phase, reveal the top card of the Carcharoth deck after characters have commited to the quest and before staging. Place this card in the staging area and discard any previous copies of Carcharoth into a separate discard pile for the Carcharoth deck. Transfer any damage and attachments to the new version of Carcharoth. If the Carcharoth deck is empty when you need to reveal a card from this deck, shuffle the discard pile for the Carcharoth deck to form a new Carcharoth deck.</p><p class='main-text'>Hunt</p><p class='main-text'>When a location with the Hunt keyword is explored as the active location, add it to the victory display. During the encounter phase, players may discard 5 Hunt points worth of locations from the victory display to engage Carcharoth. The players may decide which player will engage with Carcharoth.</p><p class='main-text'>Carcharoth Combat</p><p class='main-text'>When Carcharoth attacks a location, subtract the threat of the location from Carcharoth's attack. The difference is the number of damage tokens placed on the location. If a location receives damage equal to its quest points, it is considered to be destroyed and is discarded. If Carcharoth attacks the active location, the first player may declare a defender. Note that Carcharoth the Red Maw attacks twice during the combat phase. Choose a random location for each attack. He may attack the same location twice if it is chosen twice.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Isle-of-Werewolves-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Corruption</p><p class='main-text'>When a character takes Corruption place a progress token on it. If a character ever has Corruption greater than its willpower, it has become Corrupted. A Corrupted character loses the &quot;ally&quot; or &quot;hero&quot; card type and gains the &quot;enemy&quot; trait, immediately engaging the player that used to control it. The{Willpower} of the Corrupted character becomes its{Threat} and its engagement cost is 0.</p><p class='main-text'>Relentless</p><p class='main-text'>An enemy with Relentless cannot have its attack canceled or be prevented from attacking by any player card effect.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Isle-of-Werewolves-FA", "<p class='main-text'>The Pit Area</p><p class='main-text'>Stage 2A instructs players to create a pit area. The pit area is a new play area, separate from the staging area, that represents the captives and their battle for survival against the Devouring Werewolf sent by Sauron. THe pit area consists of stage 2 of the quest deck, The Pits of Sauron, as well as Finrod Felagund and Eyes in the Dark objectives. The players decide on one hero to be placed in the pit area as captive. The player that controls that hero immediately chooses a hero to replace this captive, adjusting his starting threat to reflect this change.</p><p class='main-text'>Heroes in the pit area are immune to player card effects and cannot leave the pit area except through specific quest and encounter card effects. The captive hero cannot quest and does not collect resources. In addition, players cannot play attachments or allies into the pit area.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Seat-of-Morgoth-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Corruption</p><p class='main-text'>When a character takes Corruption place a progress token on it. If a character ever has Corruption greater than its willpower, it has become Corrupted. A Corrupted character loses the &quot;ally&quot; or &quot;hero&quot; card type and gains the &quot;enemy&quot; trait, immediately engaging the player that used to control it. The{Willpower} of the Corrupted character becomes its{Threat} and its engagement cost is 0.</p><p class='main-text'>Relentless</p><p class='main-text'>An enemy with Relentless cannot have its attack canceled or be prevented from attacking by any player card effect.</p><p class='main-text'>Whenever an amount of progress is placed on the active enemy, the first player must pass a Sneak test. The first player may discard any number of cards from their hand, adding up the costs of those cards. Then, the top card of the encounter deck is discarded. Compare the cost of the discarded player cards against the threat value of the discarded encounter card. If the cost is greater than or equal to the threat value, then the Sneak attempt passes. If the cost is less than the threat value, the the Sneak attempt fails. If a Sneak attempt fails, the active enemy immediately engages the first player. Progress that was placed on the active location or quest is not affected. When engaged with an enemy with the Sneak keyword, players may cancel all progress and instead place an equivalent number of damage tokens on enemies with the Sneak keyword instead.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Seat-of-Morgoth-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Sneak</p><p class='main-text'>During the travel phase, the players may choose an enemy in the staging area with the Sneak keyword to be the &quot;active enemy&quot;. This follows the decision to travel. The active enemy no longer contributes its threat to the staging area. Players must still make engagement checks against it, however.</p><p class='main-text'>During quest resolution, progress tokens are placed first on the active enemy, then the active location, and finally on the quest stage. If a number of progress tokens equal to the active enemy's threat is placed on it, that enemy is discarded.</p>");
            AddHtml("Finrod-Felagund-FA", "<p class='main-text'>While Finrod Felagund is in play, each Edain character gets +1 {Willpower}</p>");
            AddHtml("Fingon-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust Fingon to remove 1 Corruption from a character in play. (Limit once per round.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Luthien-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust Lúthien and pay 2 resources from her pool to place an enemy facedown (4 resources instead if the enemy is unique). That enemy is considered to be out of play for all purposes (except victory and advancement conditions) until the end of the phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Earendil-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After E„rendil commits to the quest, shuffle the encounter deck and discard the top card. If it is a treachery, deal 1 damage to E„rendil. Otherwise, reduce your threat by 1 and draw 1 card.</p>");
            AddHtml("Haleth-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Haleth gets +1 {Willpower} for each enemy engaged with you.</p><p class='main-text'>If Haleth did not commit to the quest this round, she may use{Willpower} instead of{Defense} when defending.</p>");
            AddHtml("Feanor-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Place 1 Corruption on F‰anor to place 3 progress tokens on the quest. (Limit once per round).</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Place 1 Corruption on F‰anor to play an attachment from any sphere of influence for no cost.</p>");
            AddHtml("Thingol-FA", "<p class='main-text'>While at least 1 character with the House of F‰anor trait is in play, Thingol's{Willpower} is treated as 1 for the purposes of<b>Corruption.Setup:</b> Choose 10 different cards from your deck and shuffle them into a separate Menegroth deck. After an enemy engages you, draw 1 card from the Menegroth deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Turin-Turambar-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Raise your threat by 1 to give Túrin Turambar +1 {Attack} until the end of the round.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Túrin Turambar is dealt any amount of damage, discard a character you control to cancel that damage. (Limit once per phase.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Fingolfin-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Raise your threat by 3 to choose an enemy in play. Engage the chosen enemy. Until the end of the round, Fingolfin does not exhaust to defend against the chosen enemy.</p>");
            AddHtml("Hurin-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Húrin gets +1 {Attack} for each enemy engaged with you.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ecthelion-FA", "<p class='main-text'>When Ecthelion attacks alone, the defending enemy does not count its{Defense}</p>");
            AddHtml("Cirdan-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Círdan gets +1 {Defense} for each attached character.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Planning Action:</b> Attach a character to Círdan. This character is considered to be out of play. At the end of the round, heal 3 damage on that character and put it back into play. (Limit twice per round.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Turgon-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After raising your threat, name an encounter card type. Look at the top card of the encounter deck. If it matches the type you named, draw 1 card. If not, shuffle the encounter deck. (Limit once per phase.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Idril-Celebrindal-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After the active location is explored, return 1 ally of X cost from your discard pile to your hand. X is the{Threat} of the active location.</p>");
            AddHtml("Melian-FA", "<p class='main-text'>At the end of the round, discard Melian from play.</p><p class='main-text'>Melian cannot attack or defend.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After you play Melian from hand, choose a player and (choose 1): enemies do not make engagement checks against the chosen player until the end of the round, enemies cannot attack the chosen player this round, or the chosen player may look at the top 3 cards of the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Eol-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Place 1 Corruption on E”l to search the top 15 cards of your deck for an attachment and add it to your hand.</p>");
            AddHtml("Celegorm-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Celegorm gets +1 {Attack} for each non-unique location in the staging area.Action: Place 1 Corruption on Celegorm to search the top 10 cards of the encounter deck for a location and add it to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Maglor-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> When a Corruption token would be placed on a character you control by the encounter deck, exhaust Maglor to place that Corruption token on Maglor instead.</p>");
            AddHtml("Caranthir-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a treachery is revealed and resolved, attach that card facedown to Caranthir. That attachment gains the Fury trait. (Limit once per round.)</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Attach a Fury attachment to an enemy engaged with you. That enemy gets +1 {Attack} and -1{Defense}</p>");
            AddHtml("Maeglin-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After the active location is explored, add 1 resource to a hero's resource pool (2 resources instead if you place 1 Corruption on that hero).</p>");
            AddHtml("Maedhros-FA", "<p class='main-text'>While Maedhros has no Corruption on him, all Noldor characters get +1 {Willpower}</p><p class='main-text'>While Maedhros has at least 1 Corruption on him, all characters with the House of F‰anor trait get +1 {Attack}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Place 1 Corruption on Maedhros</p>");
            AddHtml("Mablung-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Mablung commits to a quest, choose a character. That character gets +1 {Willpower} and +1 {Defense} until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Orodreth-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a unique character with the House of Finarfin trait leaves play, put Orodreth into play from your hand.</p>");
            AddHtml("Chieftain-of-Men-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After your threat is raised by an encounter card effect, discard Chieftain of Men from play to cancel that effect.</p>");
            AddHtml("Thorondor-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have restricted attachments.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After you play Thorondor from hand, put a character from any player's discard pile into play under its owner's control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Gondolin-Guard-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Sentinel.</p>");
            AddHtml("Huan-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Huan gets +5{Attack} until the end of the phase. At the end of the phase in which you trigger this effect, discard Huan. (Limit once per round.)</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Attach Huan to Beren or Lúthien. (Counts as a Mount attachment with the text: &quot;While attached hero is committed to the quest, deal 2 damage to each enemy revealed during staging&quot;</p>");
            AddHtml("Aredhel-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After the active location is explored, discard the top card of your deck. If it is an ally, take it into your hand.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dwarf-of-the-Blue-Mountains-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Dwarf of the Blue Mountains gets +1 hit point for each unique attachment you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Telchar-the-Smith-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust Telchar the Smith to choose an Armor or Weapon attachment in play. Until the end of the round, if the chosen attachment is Armor it gains: &quot;Attached character gets +1 {Defense} Until the end of the round, if the chosen attachment is a Weapon it gains: &quot;Attached character gets +1 {Attack}</p>");
            AddHtml("Green-elf-Ranger-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Ranged.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Quest Action:</b> Exhaust Green-elf Ranger to choose enemy or location. The next encounter card of the chosen type that is added to the staging area gets -3{Threat} until the end of the phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Daeron-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust Daeron to draw 2 cards. Then discard 1 card from your hand.</p>");
            AddHtml("Elwing-FA", "<p class='main-text'>While E„rendil is in play, Elwing gains:<b>&quot;Response:</b> After Elwing is destroyed, you may immediately put her back into play for 1{sphere:Spirit} resource. (Limit once per round.)&quot;</p>");
            AddHtml("Huor-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Huor may be assigned damage from undefended attacks.</p>");
            AddHtml("Beor-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Attach B‰or facedown to a character with the House of Finarfin trait. (Counts as a Vassal attachment with the text: &quot;Attached character gets +2 {Willpower}</p>");
            AddHtml("Hador-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Discard Hador to reveal the top 5 cards of your deck. Put up to 2 revealed allies with the Edain trait into play, if able. Shuffle all other revealed cards back into your deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Barahir-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a shadow card is revealed, exhaust Barahir to add his{Defense} to the{Defense} of the defending character until the end of the phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Morwen-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Raise your threat by 1 to give Morwen +1 {Willpower} until the end of the round. (Limit twice per round.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Tuor-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust Tuor to choose a player. That player looks at the top 3 cards of his deck. He may discard 1 to discard the top card of the encounter deck, returning the remaining cards to the top of his deck in any order.</p>");
            AddHtml("Finduilas-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> Damage from undefended attacks must be assigned to Finduilas. After Finduilas leaves play, raise your threat by 2.</p>");
            AddHtml("Azaghal-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Azaghâl is destroyed as the result of an enemy attack, deal 3 damage to the attacking enemy.</p>");
            AddHtml("Curufin-FA", "<p class='main-text'>While F‰anor is in play, Curufin gains:<b>&quot;Action:</b> Place 1 Corruption on Curufin. Until the end of the round, Curufin's{Willpower}{Attack} and{Defense} are equal to the printed{Willpower}{Attack} and{Defense} of F‰anor.&quot;</p>");
            AddHtml("High-Kingship-of-the-Noldor-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a Noldor hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust High Kingship of the Noldor to add 2 resources to attached hero's resource pool.</p>");
            AddHtml("Elf-friend-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to an Edain hero.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gains the Noldor trait.</p>");
            AddHtml("Shadowy-Cloak-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to Lúthien.</p><p class='main-text'>Resources on Shadowy Cloak can only be used to pay for Lúthien's ability.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust Shadowy Cloak to either add 1 resource to Shadowy Cloak or ready Lúthien.</p>");
            AddHtml("Vingilot-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero with the Half-elven trait.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust Vingilot to use the attached hero's{Willpower} instead of{Defense} (or{Attack} if attached hero is E„rendil) until the end of the phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Harp-of-Fingon-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero with the House of Fingolfin trait.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a Corruption token is removed from play, exhaust Harp of Fingon to add 1 resource to the attached hero's resource pool.</p>");
            AddHtml("Oath-of-Friendship-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero. Limit 2 in play.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Move any number of resources from the attached hero's resource pool to the resource pool of another hero with Oath of Friendship attached.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After you play Oath of Friendship, you may immediately search your deck for another copy of Oath of Friendship and add it to your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Oath-of-Vengeance-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero. Limit 1 per hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a character you control is destroyed, place 1 resource on Oath of Vengeance.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Spend 1 resource from Oath of Vengeance to give attached hero +1 {Willpower} or +1 {Attack} until the end of the phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Oath-of-Feanor-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a character with the House of F‰anor trait. Limit 1 per character.</p><p class='main-text'>Corruption on the attached character cannot be removed.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Planning Action:</b> Exhaust Oath of F‰anor to switch the printed{Attack} and{Willpower} of the attached character until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Oath-of-Silence-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero. Limit 1 per hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> Discard one card from your hand at the end of each round.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Oath of Silence is attached to a hero you control, search your deck for 2 cards and add them to your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Haudh-en-Ndengin-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a location in play.</p><p class='main-text'>While Haudh-en-Ndengin has at least one facedown attachment, the{Threat} of the attached location is reduced to<b>0.Response:</b> After a character is destroyed, attach that card facedown to Haudh-en-Ndengin.</p>");
            AddHtml("Hidden-House-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a location in play.</p><p class='main-text'>While the attached location is the active location, enemies do not make engagement checks.</p>");
            AddHtml("Solitary-Outlaw-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Limit 1 per hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Attach to a hero. This hero must be the only hero you control.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gets +2 {Willpower} +2 {Attack} +2 {Defense} +2 hit points and does not exhaust to quest.</p>");
            AddHtml("Nauglamir-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Lower the cost to play Nauglamír by 1 for each Dwarf in play. Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'>Each hero you control gets +1 {Willpower} +1 {Attack} and +1 {Defense}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the start of the combat phase, discard a resource from the attached hero's resource pool for each Dwarf in play. Any Dwarf for which you did not discard a resource immediately becomes corrupted.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ard-galen-Horse-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a Noldor hero. Limit 1 per hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust Ard-galen Horse to place 1 progress token on each location in the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Galvorn-Armor-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a Mastery hero. Limit 1 per hero.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gets +1 {Defense} Attached hero gets an additional +1 {Defense} for each Corruption on the attached hero.</p>");
            AddHtml("Poisoned-Javelin-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a Mastery character. Restricted.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After attached character damages an enemy, attach Poisoned Javelin to that enemy.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of each round, if Poisoned Javelin is attached to an enemy, deal 2 damage to that enemy. You may place 1 Corruption on a hero you control to increase this to 4 damage.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ring-of-Barahir-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to an Edain hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Discard Ring of Barahir to put a unique Noldor ally into play from your hand.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ringil-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero with the House of Fingolfin trait. Restricted.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gets +1 {Attack} (+2 {Attack} if Fingolfin).</p><p class='main-text'>If the attached hero is Fingolfin, Ringil gains:<b>&quot;Response:</b> After the attached character attacks alone, cancel all damage from the attack and reduce your threat by that amount instead.&quot;</p>");
            AddHtml("Rochallor-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to Fingolfin.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Combat Action:</b> Choose an enemy in the staging area. Exhaust Rochallor and the attached hero to make an attack on that enemy. The attached hero gets +1 {Attack} (+2 {Attack} if the enemy is unique).</p>");
            AddHtml("Blue-Shield-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero with the House of Fingolfin trait. Restricted.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gets +1 {Defense} (+2 {Defense} if the attached hero is Fingolfin).</p>");
            AddHtml("Dragon-helm-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero with the House of Hador trait. Restricted.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After attached hero is damaged, exhaust Dragon-helm and raise your threat by 3 to cancel all damage from that attack.</p><p class='main-text'>If attached hero is Túrin, Dragon-helm gains,<b>&quot;Response:</b> After an enemy engages with you, it gets -1{Attack} and -1{Defense} until the end of the round.&quot;</p>");
            AddHtml("Gurthang-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero with a printed Mastery resource icon. Restricted.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gets +1 {Attack}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After attached hero damages an enemy, shuffle the encounter deck and discard the top card. If it is a treachery, cancel all damage from the attack and discard a hero. Otherwise, the enemy is destroyed.</p>");
            AddHtml("Mormegil-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to Túrin Turambar. Limit 1 Name in play.</p><p class='main-text'>Túrin Turambar gains a{sphere:Tactics} resource icon.</p><p class='main-text'>All enemies get -1{Threat} and -10 engagement cost.</p>");
            AddHtml("Nimphelos-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Pay 1 resource from attached hero's resource pool to give attached hero +1 {Willpower} until the end of the phase. (Limit three times per phase.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Strength-of-Men-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust an ally with the Edain trait. Add the{Willpower}{Attack} and{Defense} of that ally to all characters with the Noldor trait you control until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Erchamion-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a character is destroyed, put that character back into play under its owner's control. Attach Erchamion to that character. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text: 'The attached character gets -1{Attack} and -1{Defense}</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Day-Has-Come-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Until the end of the phase, all Noldor characters get +1 {Willpower}</p>");
            AddHtml("Song-of-Luthien-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> If you control Lúthien or a unique Maia character, reduce each player's threat by 3.</p>");
            AddHtml("Song-of-Staying-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a treachery with doomed or surge is revealed, cancel the effects of all keywords on that treachery.</p>");
            AddHtml("Arts-of-Felagund-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Quest Action:</b> Until the end of the phase, each enemy revealed during staging is discarded and replaced with the next encounter card instead. Add this card to the victory display.</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Passed-in-Peace-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a character with the Edain trait leaves play, play Passed in Peace to draw 2 cards.</p>");
            AddHtml("Leaguer-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust characters with X points of total{Defense} to choose enemies with up to X points of total{Attack} Those enemies cannot attack this round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Madness-of-Rage-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Choose a character you control. Until the end of the phase, that character gets +3{Attack} and must attack alone.</p>");
            AddHtml("Hour-of-Need-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> If at least X enemies are engaged with players (X being equal to twice the number of players), each player may put 1 ally into play from his hand, if able.</p>");
            AddHtml("A-Great-Doom-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a player card is drawn or an encounter card is revealed (including a shadow effect), shuffle that card back into its deck and draw a new card.</p>");
            AddHtml("Fire-of-Life-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a character with the House of F‰anor trait is damaged, cancel 1 point of that damage and attach Fire of Life to that character. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text: &quot;Limit 1 per character. Attached character gets +1 {Attack}</p>");
            AddHtml("Defied-and-Mocked-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Choose an ally. That ally can be assigned damage from undefended attacks until the end of the phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dreadful-Death-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a corrupted character destroys a hero or ally, remove all Corruption from that character and place it under your control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dark-Heart-of-the-Smith-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Place 1 Corruption on a character with a unique Weapon attached. All damage dealt by that character is doubled this round. Only 1 copy of Dark Heart of the Smith may be played on a character each round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Undismayed-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a character is destroyed by an enemy attack, put that character back into play. That character gets +3{Attack} and is discarded at the end of the phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Feast-of-Reuniting-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> All characters gain ranged and sentinel until the end of the phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Banners-and-Horns-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a unique ally you control enters play, choose any non-unique enemy in play. That enemy gets -X{Attack} and -X{Defense} until the end of the round. (X is equal to the cost of that ally.)</p>");
            AddHtml("No-Better-Hope-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust a hero you control to discard a corrupted character from play.</p>");
            AddHtml("Hold-to-the-Oath-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Each character with an attached Oath gets +1 {Willpower} +1 {Attack} and +1 {Defense} until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Beren-FA", "<p class='main-text'>While Beren is committed to the quest, he gains:<b>'Response:</b> After an encounter card with at least 3{Threat} is revealed from the encounter deck, add 1 resource to Beren's resource pool.'</p>");
            AddHtml("Manwe's-Pity-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a unique Noldor ally you control is destroyed by an enemy attack, immediately put into play another copy of that ally from your hand.</p>");
            AddHtml("Secrets-of-Craft-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Choose a player. That player draws 1 card for each Item attachment you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dreams-from-Ulmo-FA", "<p class='main-text'>If the active location is a River or Water location, reduce the cost to play Dreams from Ulmo by 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Choose one character you control. Shuffle the encounter deck and look at its top card. Until the end of the phase, the chosen character gets +X{Willpower} X is equal to the revealed card's{Threat}</p>");
            AddHtml("Friendship-of-Ulmo-FA", "<p class='main-text'>If the active location is a River or Water location, reduce the cost to play Friendship of Ulmo by 2.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Reveal all shadow cards in play. Then, choose two shadow cards from different enemies and switch them.</p>");
            AddHtml("Strengthen-the-Watch-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Encounter Action:</b> Exhaust a character. All enemies that engaged you this phase get -1{Attack} until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Secret-Toil-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust 2 heroes you control to reveal the top 5 cards of your deck. Choose one attachment or ally and put it into play for no cost. Shuffle all other revealed cards back into your deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("And-Yet-A-Warning-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After you attack and destroy an enemy, choose one: add 1 resource to the resource pool of a hero you control, draw 1 card, or lower your threat by 1.</p>");
            AddHtml("Song-of-Gladness-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Play only if there are no enemies engaged with you.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Reduce your threat by 3.</p>");
            AddHtml("Flame-Light-Flee-Night-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Play only if you control a hero with the Edain trait.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Search your deck for a character with the Edain trait and put it into play. That character does not exhaust to quest, attack, or defend until the end of the round. Discard that character at the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Open-Battle-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Doomed 2.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Each player may search his deck for a Weapon or Armor attachment and add it to his hand.</p>");
            AddHtml("Day-Shall-Come-Again-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a character you control destroys an enemy, ready that character. That character gets +1 {Attack} until the end of the round. You may pay 1{sphere:Tactics} resource to return Day Shall Come Again to your hand.</p>");
            AddHtml("Song-of-Wizardry-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must discard the top card of his deck and place Corruption among his characters equal to its cost.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Place 1 Corruption on the defending character if it is an ally.</p>");
            AddHtml("Weight-of-Horror-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach to the hero with the highest{Willpower} (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text: 'The attached hero must spend 1 resource from his pool to commit to the quest. Limit 1 per hero.')</p>");
            AddHtml("Lord-of-Werewolves-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must search the encounter deck and discard pile for one enemy with the Werewolf trait and add it to the staging area.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The attacking enemy returns to the staging area after this attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Master-of-Shadows-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach to the current quest stage. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text: 'Each enemy is dealt an additional shadow card at the beginning of the combat phase.')</p>");
            AddHtml("No-Living-Creature-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must choose one: raise your threat by 1 for each character you control or place 1 Corruption on each character you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Foul-Vapour-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each character in play gets -X{Attack} and -X{Defense} until the end of the round. X is the number of enemies with the Werewolf trait engaged with the controlling player. If there are no engaged enemies with the Werewolf trait, Foul Vapour gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The defending character gets -1{Defense} until the end of the phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Deep-Pit-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Deep Pit is explored, the first player chooses one: add 1 resource to Eyes in the Dark or move one hero to the pit area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Gates-of-Tol-in-Gaurhoth-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>The first enemy with the Werewolf trait revealed each turn gains surge.</p>");
            AddHtml("Walls-of-Stone-FA", "<p class='main-text'>While Walls of Stone is in the staging area, progress cannot be placed on the current quest stage.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If a character is destroyed by this attack, remove 5 progress tokens from the quest.</p>");
            AddHtml("High-Tower-FA", "<p class='main-text'>While High Tower is the active location, all enemies get -20 engagement cost.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After High Tower is explored as the active location, remove one Condition attachment from play.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dark-Hills-FA", "<p class='main-text'>While Dark Hills is in play, players cannot use player card effects that allow them to look at cards in the encounter deck or player decks.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} for each shadow card it has been dealt.</p>");
            AddHtml("Vacant-Pit-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> Remove 1 resource from Eyes in the Dark at the end of the round.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack destroys a character, remove 1 resource from Eyes in the Dark.</p>");
            AddHtml("Bridge-to-the-Isle-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>While Bridge to the Isle is the active location, enemies with the Werewolf trait get +1 {Attack} and +1<b>Defense.Forced:</b> After Bridge to the Isle is explored, add Draugluin to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Eyes-in-the-Dark-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Place 8 resource tokens on Eyes in the Dark.At the end of each round, discard 1 resource token from Eyes in the Dark.</p><p class='main-text'>If there are no resource tokens to discard, remove Eyes in the Dark from play and put Devouring Werewolf into play in the pit area, engaged with the prisoners.</p>");
            AddHtml("Upon-the-Bridge-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Set aside Devouring Werewolf Draugluin, Bridge to the Isle and Wolf-Sauron. Create a pit area with stage 2A and follow the setup instructions on that card.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Upon-the-Bridge-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add Bridge to the Isle to the staging area. Reveal X encounter cards where X equals the number of players in the game minus 1.</p><p class='main-text'>When this stage is completed, advance to stage 3A. This stage cannot be completed until Draugluin is in the victory display.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Pits-of-Sauron-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Search the encounter deck for Finrod Felagund and Eyes in the Dark and add both to the pit area. Choose one hero to be placed in the pit area. That hero is captured. The controlling player may immediately replace the captured hero with another of his choice.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Pits-of-Sauron-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Heroes at this stage do not collect resources or commit to the quest and are immune to player card effects. Player cannot play or put into play allies or attachments into the pit area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> If the players quest unsuccessfully, remove 1 resource from Eyes in the Dark if able.</p><p class='main-text'>If the captured hero is destroyed, the players lose the game. If Devouring Werewolf is destroyed, discard this stage from play and return all characters to their owner's control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Tol-in-Gaurhoth-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add Wolf-Sauron to the staging area. Reveal 1 encounter card per player.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Tol-in-Gaurhoth-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After an enemy is revealed from the encounter deck, discard it instead of adding it to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Planning Action:</b> Exhaust a hero with X{Willpower} Wolf-Sauron gets -X{Defense} until the end of the round. (Limit once per round.)</p><p class='main-text'>If the players destroy Wolf-Sauron, they have rescued the prisoners and won the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Finrod-Felagund-Objective-Ally-FA", "<p class='main-text'>The first player gains control of Finrod Felagund.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Discard Finrod Felagund to deal 5 points of damage to an engaged enemy.</p>");
            AddHtml("Draugluin-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Relentless.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Draugluin is damaged by an attack, deal 1 damage to each character that participated in that attack.</p>{victory:3}");
            AddHtml("Wolf-Sauron-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Relentless.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Wolf-Sauron attacks, place 1 Corruption on a random ally controlled by the engaged player.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Ravenous-Werewolf-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Ravenous Werewolf gets +1 {Attack} for each damage token on characters you control.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +X{Attack} X is the number of damage tokens on the defending character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Thuringwethil-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Thuringwethil damages a character, remove an equal amount of damage from Thuringwethil.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Remove all damage from the attacking enemy.</p>");
            AddHtml("Monstrous-Bat-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Monstrous Bat deals damage to a character, raise its{Defense} by X until the end of the round, where X equals the amount of damage dealt.</p>");
            AddHtml("Guard-Wolf-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Choose one character committed to the quest and remove him from the quest. If Guard Wolf is not destroyed by the end of the round, that character does not ready during the refresh phase.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} (+2 {Attack} instead if the enemy is a Werewolf.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Hunting-Wolf-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Hunting Wolf engages a player, raise that player's threat by 3.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Raise the defending player's threat by 2.</p>");
            AddHtml("Crazed-Thrall-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> Reveal 1 encounter card at the end of the round.Forced: After Crazed Thrall is destroyed by an attack, place 1 Corruption on each participating character.Response: After questing successfully, cancel all progress and instead remove Crazed Thrall from play.</p>");
            AddHtml("Devouring-Werewolf-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Cannot leave the pit area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> Characters destroyed by Devouring Werewolf are removed from the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Doors-of-Angband-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Add Carcharoth to the staging area. Set Morgoth and all objectives and unique locations aside out of play. Set your threat equal to the number of heroes you control.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Doors-of-Angband-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> Skip the staging step during the quest phase. Instead, each player must discard the top card of his deck after committing characters to the quest. Add the cost of each discarded card to the total{Threat} in the staging area until the end of the phase.</p><p class='main-text'>If Carcharoth has 0 hit points, advance to stage 2 immediately.</p>");
            AddHtml("Descent-into-Darkness-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Remove Carcharoth from play. Add Pits of Angband, Thrall Quarters, and Tunnels of Shadow to the staging area. Each player must search the encounter deck and discard pile for 1 enemy and add it to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Descent-into-Darkness-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After the first Path location is explored, add Nethermost Hall to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After traveling to a unique location, players raise their threat by its{Threat}</p><p class='main-text'>The players cannot advance unless Nethermost Hall is in the victory display.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Greatest-Deed-FA", "");
            AddHtml2("The-Greatest-Deed-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add Morgoth to the staging area and attach Silmaril to him.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After questing successfully, you may place progress tokens on Morgoth as damage instead of placing them on the quest.</p><p class='main-text'>The players cannot advance to the next stage unless they control the Silmaril objective.</p>");
            AddHtml("To-See-the-Light-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Remove Morgoth from play. Add Carcharoth to the staging area, removing any damage that was previously placed.</p>");
            AddHtml2("To-See-the-Light-FA", "<p class='main-text'>All enemies lose the Sneak keyword.</p><p class='main-text'>If the players defeat this stage or Carcharoth has 0 hit points, the players have won the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Silmaril-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> If Morgoth has 0 hit points, exhaust a hero to claim<b>Silmaril.Action:</b> Exhaust Silmaril and attached hero to either return an enemy to the staging area or reduce its{Defense} to 0 until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Angband-Sword-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attached hero gains +5{Attack} Restricted.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gains an additional +1 {Attack} for each resource on Angband Sword.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Attach Angband Sword to a hero. Place 1 Corruption on that hero.Response: After attached hero deals damage, add 1 resource to Angband Sword.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dreadful-Garments-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Attach Dreadful Garments to a hero.Action: Exhaust Dreadful Garments to place 5 progress tokens on the active enemy.</p>");
            AddHtml("Element-of-Surprise-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Attach Element of Surprise to a hero.Combat<b>Action:</b> Exhaust Element of Surprise. Player attacks are made before enemy attacks during this phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Morgoth-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Indestructible.</p><p class='main-text'>Morgoth cannot leave the staging area and is considered to be engaged with each player.No Trap attachments can be attached to<b>Morgoth.Forced:</b> At the end of the round, each player must place 2 Corruption among characters he controls.</p>");
            AddHtml("Carcharoth-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Relentless. Indestructible. Cannot leave play.</p><p class='main-text'>X is 5 times the number of players.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> Players cannot reduce their threat while Carcharoth is in play.</p>");
            AddHtml("Balrog-of-Angband-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Sneak.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After an event is played, lower the engagement cost of Balrog of Angband by 20 and increase its{Threat} by 1 until the end of the round.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Discard all event cards from your hand.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Long-worm-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Sneak.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Long-worm engages a player, place 1 Corruption on the character with the lowest{Willpower} that he controls.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Fire-drake-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Sneak.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of the combat phase, deal 1 damage to each character controlled by the engaged player.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Deal 1 damage to each character controlled by the engaged player.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Gothmog-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Sneak.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Gothmog attacks, discard 1 attachment controlled by the defending player.</p>{victory:6}");
            AddHtml("Troll-of-Angband-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Sneak.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Troll of Angband attacks, raise the defending player's threat by 3.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Raise the defending player's threat by 3.</p>");
            AddHtml("Orc-Captain-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Sneak.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Orc Captain attacks, add the shadow card to the staging area if it is an enemy (ignoring any shadow effect).</p>");
            AddHtml("Angband-Orc-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Sneak. Doomed 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> While Angband Orc is engaged with a player, raise that player's threat by an additional 1 at the end of the round.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Add Angband Orc to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Pits-of-Angband-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>This location does not contribute its threat while it is in the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> The first enemy revealed each round gains surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Pits of Angband leaves play, add Angband Sword to the staging area.</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Thrall-Quarters-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. This location does not contribute its threat while it is in the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> While Thrall Quarters is the active location, add 1 to the{Threat} of discarded encounter cards when resolving a Sneak test.Response: After Thrall Quarters leaves play, add Dreadful Garments to the staging area.</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Tunnels-of-Shadow-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. This location does not contribute its threat while it is in the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> While Tunnels of Shadow is the active location, the encounter deck is shuffled before discarding cards for a Sneak test.Response: After Tunnels of Shadow leaves play, add Element of Surprise to the staging area.</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Labyrinthine-Stairs-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After putting any amount of progress on Labyrinthine Stairs, discard the top card of the encounter deck. If it is a location, add it to the staging area.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack destroys a character, return the active location to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Torturer's-Dungeon-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> If there is no active location and you have the option to travel, you must either travel to Torturer's Dungeon or place 1 Corruption on each hero.Travel: Each player must search the encounter deck and discard pile for an enemy and put it into play engaged with him.</p>");
            AddHtml("Echoing-Corridor-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of the staging step, players must raise their threat by the number of characters they committed to the quest while Echoing Corridor is the active location.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Raise the threat of the defending player by the{Threat} of the attacking enemy.</p>");
            AddHtml("Subterranean-Furnace-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> While Subterranean Furnace is the active location, each player must discard a random card from his hand at the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Trackless-Cavern-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Trackless Cavern leaves play, each player reduces his threat by 5.</p>");
            AddHtml("Orc-Armory-FA", "<p class='main-text'>While Orc Armory is the active location, all enemies lose the Sneak keyword.Response: After Orc Armory is explored as the active location, the first player attaches it to a hero. The attached hero gains +1 {Attack} and +1 {Defense}</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} and +1 {Defense} until the end of the phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Nethermost-Hall-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Nethermost Hall is explored as the active location, advance to stage 3.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Search the encounter deck and discard pile for Gothmog and add him to the staging area, if able.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} and +1 {Defense} until the end of the phase.</p>{victory:2}");
            AddHtml("Devouring-Spirit-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach to the enemy in play with the lowest{Threat} Attached enemy gets +1 {Threat} +1 {Attack} +1 {Defense} and +3 hit points. If there are no enemies in play, Devouring{sphere:Spirit} gains surge.</p>");
            AddHtml("Clumsy-Step-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Doomed 2.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Discard an additional encounter card when resolving Sneak tests this round. If there is no active enemy, Clumsy Step gains surge.</p>");
            AddHtml("Foolish-Ruckus-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Raise the{Threat} of the active enemy by 3 until the end of the phase. If there is no active enemy, raise the{Threat} of all enemies in the staging area by 1 until the end of the phase.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack destroys a character, raise the defending player's threat by 2.</p>");
            AddHtml("Filth-and-Desolation-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must either deal 1 damage to each character he committed to the quest or reduce the{Willpower} of each character he controls by 1 until the end of the round.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Exhaust a character that the defending player controls.</p>");
            AddHtml("Heroic-Diversion-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Doomed 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must either discard 1 character or raise his threat by 5.</p>");
            AddHtml("Evil-Lust-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach to a hero. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text: 'This hero must be declared as the defender against Morgoth (even if exhausted). Morgoth uses his{Threat} to attack and the attached hero uses his{Willpower} to defend. Limit 1 per hero.')</p>");
            AddHtml("Dark-Elf-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Place X Corruption on heroes you control to draw X cards. (X cannot be greater than the number of heroes you control.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Haladin-Woodsman-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a shadow effect resolves on an enemy engaged with you, Haladin Woodsman gets +1 {Attack} and +1 {Defense} until the end of the round. (Limit twice per round.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Aranruth-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero with a printed Mastery icon. Restricted.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust Aranrúth to give attached hero a{sphere:Leadership}{sphere:Lore}{sphere:Tactics} or{sphere:Spirit} icon until the end of the phase.</p><p class='main-text'>If attached hero is Thingol, Aranrúth gains, 'Attached hero gets +2 {Attack}</p>");
            AddHtml("Ride-Forth-in-the-Morning-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Place Carcharoth the Tormented and Gates of Menegroth aside, out of play. Shuffle all other copies of Carcharoth into a Carcharoth deck. Each player must search the encounter deck for 1 different location and add it to the staging area. Put the Beleg Strongbow objective ally into play.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Ride-Forth-in-the-Morning-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After a location is destroyed, place 1 damage on this quest stage. After the 10th damage is placed on this stage, advance to stage 3.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> If there is no location in play at the end of the round, the first player must search the encounter deck and discard pile for 1 location and add it to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'>Players cannot advance to stage 2 unless Carcharoth has at least 10 damage on him.</p>");
            AddHtml("At-Last-Upon-the-Wolf-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Remove Carcharoth from play and put the Carcharoth deck aside. Add Carcharoth the Tormented to the staging area. Remove half of the damage on Carcharoth (rounding up).</p>");
            AddHtml2("At-Last-Upon-the-Wolf-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Discard all Hunt locations from the victory display.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> If an ally is destroyed by Carcharoth, place 1 damage on this stage. After the 4th damage is placed on this stage, reset the quest deck to stage 1A and follow the setup instructions again.</p><p class='main-text'>If Carcharoth the Tormented is destroyed, you have recovered the Silmaril and won the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ruin-Upon-the-World-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Gates of Menegroth becomes the active location, moving any previous active location to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Ruin-Upon-the-World-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Siege.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> Reveal 1 additional encounter card from the encounter deck each quest phase.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Gates of Menegroth is explored as the active location, reset the quest deck to stage 1B.</p><p class='main-text'>If Gates of Menegroth is destroyed, the players lose the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Beleg-Strongbow-FA", "<p class='main-text'>The first player gains control of Beleg<b>Strongbow.Action:</b> Exhaust Beleg Strongbow to remove 2 damage from a location in play.</p>");
            AddHtml("Carcharoth-the-Red-Maw-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Indestructible. Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> While Carcharoth the Red Maw is in the staging area, he attacks a random location in play during the combat phase (the first player may declare a defender if it is the active location).</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> Caracharoth the Red Maw makes two attacks during the combat phase. (Deal a separate shadow card for each attack.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Carcharoth-the-Wolf-of-Angband-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Indestructible. Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> While Carcharoth the Wolf of Angband is in the staging area, he attacks a random location in play during the combat phase (the first player may declare a defender if it is the active location).</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add 1 damage to the current quest stage.</p>");
            AddHtml("Carcharoth-the-Devouring-Spirit-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Indestructible. Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> While Carcharoth the Devouring{sphere:Spirit} is in the staging area, he attacks a random location in play during the combat phase (the first player may declare a defender if it is the active location).</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Carcharoth the Devouring{sphere:Spirit} makes an immediate attack on the first player.</p>");
            AddHtml("Carcharoth-the-Tormented-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Relenthless. Cannot leave play.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> Carcharoth the Tormented engages the first player during the encounter phase.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After an attack by Carcharoth the Tormented resolves, discard one character the defending player controls.</p>");
            AddHtml("Taur-nu-Fuin-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Hunt 2.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Each player places the top card of his deck face down in front of him as if it just engaged him from the staging area. These cards are called 'Phantom' and act as enemies with: 3 hit points, 4{Attack} and 1{Defense}</p>");
            AddHtml("Pass-of-Anach-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Hunt 2.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Each player must discard 1 character he controls.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dimbar-Field-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Hunt 1.</p><p class='main-text'>While Dimbar Field is the active location, all heroes gain ranged.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Discard all allies in each player's hand.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The attacking enemy makes an additional attack after this one.</p>");
            AddHtml("Brethil-Dwelling-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Hunt 2.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Brethil Dwelling is destroyed, each player must deal 3 Corruption among heroes he controls.</p>");
            AddHtml("Eaves-of-Region-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Hunt 1.</p><p class='main-text'>While Eaves of Region is the active location, Carcharoth takes 1 damage at the end of the round.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Each player must discard 1 random card from his hand.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Either destroy a location in play or choose a new defender. (You may choose a location that is the target of this attack.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Banks-of-the-Esgalduin-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Hunt 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> If Banks of the Esgalduin is destroyed, remove 5 damage from<b>Carcharoth.Travel:</b> Each player must discard an attachment he controls.</p>");
            AddHtml("Neldoreth-Settlement-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Hunt 2.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> If Neldoreth Settlement is destroyed, deal 1 Corruption to each character in play.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If the defending character or location is destroyed, exhausted characters do not ready at the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Iant-Iaur-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Hunt 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Iant Iaur is destroyed, add 1 damage to the current quest stage.Response: After Iant Iaur is added to the victory display, remove 1 damage from the current quest stage.</p>");
            AddHtml("Gates-of-Menegroth-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> If Gates of Menegroth is destroyed, the players lose the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dark-Valley-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Hunt 3.</p><p class='main-text'>While Dark Valley is the active location, you may choose which Carcharoth is revealed at the beginning of the quest phase. Shuffle the Carcharoth deck.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Carcharoth makes an immediate attack against the first player.</p>");
            AddHtml("Evil-Days-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must either deal 1 damage to each location in play or deal 1 Corruption to each character he controls.</p>");
            AddHtml("Stood-Now-in-Wrath-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Discard Carcharoth and reveal and add the next card from the Carcharoth deck.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} (+3{Attack} instead if the attacking enemy has more than 5 damage on him.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Fled-in-Fear-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Remove all allies from the quest. Allies cannot be declared as attackers or defenders until the end of the round.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Allies cannot participate in an attack against the attacking enemy this round.</p>");
            AddHtml("A-Doom-Fulfilled-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach to Carcharoth as a Condition attachment with the text, 'After an attack against Carcharoth resolves, discard one character that participated in the attack and discard A Doom Fulfilled.'</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The attacking enemy cannot be damaged this turn unless the defending player discards one character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Flame-of-Anguish-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Remove 5 damage from Carcharoth and assign it to characters the first player controls. If Carcharoth has no damage, Flame of Anguish gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Remove 5 damage from the attacking enemy.</p>");
            AddHtml("Espied-from-Afar-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The players must either discard the location in the victory display with the highest Hunt value or prevent all exhausted characters from readying during the refresh phase this round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Devil's-Cunning-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Carcharoth makes an immediate attack on the player with the most {Willpower} committed to the quest.</p>");
            AddHtml2("At-Last-Upon-the-Wolf-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Discard all Hunt locations from the victory display.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> If an ally is destroyed by Carcharoth, place 1 damage on this stage. After the 4th damage is placed on this stage, reset the quest deck to stage 1A and follow the setup instructions again.</p><p class='main-text'>If Carcharoth the Tormented is destroyed, you have recovered the Silmaril and won the game.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Ride-Forth-in-the-Morning-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After a location is destroyed, place 1 damage on this quest stage. After the 10th damage is placed on this stage, advance to stage 3.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> If there is no location in play at the end of the round, the first player must search the encounter deck and discard pile for 1 location and add it to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'>Players cannot advance to stage 2 unless Carcharoth has at least 10 damage on him.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Ruin-Upon-the-World-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Siege.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> Reveal 1 additional encounter card from the encounter deck each quest phase.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Gates of Menegroth is explored as the active location, reset the quest deck to stage 1B.</p><p class='main-text'>If Gates of Menegroth is destroyed, the players lose the game.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Hunting-of-the-Wolf-Campaign-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Carcharoth Deck</p><p class='main-text'>During the quest phase, reveal the top card of the Carcharoth deck after characters have commited to the quest and before staging. Place this card in the staging area and discard any previous copies of Carcharoth into a separate discard pile for the Carcharoth deck. Transfer any damage and attachments to the new version of Carcharoth. If the Carcharoth deck is empty when you need to reveal a card from this deck, shuffle the discard pile for the Carcharoth deck to form a new Carcharoth deck.</p><p class='main-text'>Hunt</p><p class='main-text'>When a location with the Hunt keyword is explored as the active location, add it to the victory display. During the encounter phase, players may discard 5 Hunt points worth of locations from the victory display to engage Carcharoth. The players may decide which player will engage with Carcharoth.</p><p class='main-text'>Carcharoth Combat</p><p class='main-text'>When Carcharoth attacks a location, subtract the threat of the location from Carcharoth's attack. The difference is the number of damage tokens placed on the location. If a location receives damage equal to its quest points, it is considered to be destroyed and is discarded. If Carcharoth attacks the active location, the first player may declare a defender. Note that Carcharoth the Red Maw attacks twice during the combat phase. Choose a random location for each attack. He may attack the same location twice if it is chosen twice.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Pits-of-Sauron-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Heroes at this stage do not collect resources or commit to the quest and are immune to player card effects. Player cannot play or put into play allies or attachments into the pit area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> If the players quest unsuccessfully, remove 1 resource from Eyes in the Dark if able.</p><p class='main-text'>If the captured hero is destroyed, the players lose the game. If Devouring Werewolf is destroyed, discard this stage from play and return all characters to their owner's control.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Tol-in-Gaurhoth-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After an enemy is revealed from the encounter deck, discard it instead of adding it to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Planning</b><b>Action:</b> Exhaust a hero with X{Willpower} Wolf-Sauron gets -X{Defense} until the end of the round. (Limit once per round.)</p><p class='main-text'>If the players destroy Wolf-Sauron, they have rescued the prisoners and won the game.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Upon-the-Bridge-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add Bridge to the Isle to the staging area. Reveal X encounter cards where X equals the number of players in the game minus 1.</p><p class='main-text'>When this stage is completed, advance to stage 3A. This stage cannot be completed until Draugluin is in the victory display.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Isle-of-Werewolves-Campaign-FA", "<p class='main-text'>The Pit Area</p><p class='main-text'>Stage 2A instructs players to create a pit area. The pit area is a new play area, separate from the staging area, that represents the captives and their battle for survival against the Devouring Werewolf sent by Sauron. THe pit area consists of stage 2 of the quest deck, The Pits of Sauron, as well as Finrod Felagund and Eyes in the Dark objectives. The players decide on one hero to be placed in the pit area as captive. The player that controls that hero immediately chooses a hero to replace this captive, adjusting his starting threat to reflect this change.</p><p class='main-text'>Heroes in the pit area are immune to player card effects and cannot leave the pit area except through specific quest and encounter card effects. The captive hero cannot quest and does not collect resources. In addition, players cannot play attachments or allies into the pit area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Descent-into-Darkness-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After the first Path location is explored, add Nethermost Hall to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After traveling to a unique location, players raise their threat by its{Threat}</p><p class='main-text'>The players cannot advance unless Nethermost Hall is in the victory display.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Doors-of-Angband-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> Skip the staging step during the quest phase. Instead, each player must discard the top card of his deck after committing characters to the quest. Add the cost of each discarded card to the total{Threat} in the staging area until the end of the phase.</p><p class='main-text'>If Carcharoth has 0 hit points, advance to stage 2 immediately.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Greatest-Deed-FA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add Morgoth to the staging area and attach Silmaril to him.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After questing successfully, you may place progress tokens on Morgoth as damage instead of placing them on the quest.</p><p class='main-text'>The players cannot advance to the next stage unless they control the Silmaril objective.</p>");
            AddHtml2("To-See-the-Light-FA", "<p class='main-text'>All enemies lose the Sneak keyword.</p><p class='main-text'>If the players defeat this stage or Carcharoth has 0 hit points, the players have won the game.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Seat-of-Morgoth-Campaign-FA", "<p class='main-text'>Sneak</p><p class='main-text'>During the travel phase, the players may choose an enemy in the staging area with the Sneak keyword to be the 'active enemy'. This follows the decision to travel. The active enemy no longer contributes its threat to the staging area. Players must still make engagement checks against it, however.</p><p class='main-text'>During quest resolution, progress tokens are placed first on the active enemy, then the active location, and finally on the quest stage. If a number of progress tokens equal to the active enemy's threat is placed on it, that enemy is discarded.</p><p class='main-text'>Whenever an amount of progress is placed on the active enemy, the first player must pass a Sneak test. The first player may discard any number of cards from their hand, adding up the costs of those cards. Then, the top card of the encounter deck is discarded. Compare the cost of the discarded player cards against the threat value of the discarded encounter card. If the cost is greater than or equal to the threat value, then the Sneak attempt passes. If the cost is less than the threat value, the the Sneak attempt fails. If a Sneak attempt fails, the active enemy immediately engages the first player. Progress that was placed on the active location or quest is not affected.</p><p class='main-text'>When engaged with an enemy with the Sneak keyword, players may cancel all progress and instead place an equivalent number of damage tokens on enemies with the Sneak keyword instead.</p>");
        }

        private void TrialUponTheMarches()
        {
            AddHtml("Deeds-of-Daring-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>While Deeds of Darin is in the victory display, heroes gets +1 {Attack} when attacking alone.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After the players complete the attached quest, add Deeds of Daring to the victory display.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After an ally is declared as a defender or attacker, remove Deeds of Daring from play if it is not in the victory display.</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Mighty-in-Arms-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>While Mighty in Arms is in the victory display, each enemy gets -1 {Defense}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a player deals more than 5 damage to an enemy in a single round, add Mighty in Arms to the victory display.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After the players complete the attached quest, remove Mighty in Arms from play if it is not in the victory display.</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Orc-Raiding-Party-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Raid.} Cannot leave play unless destroyed.</p><p class='main-text'>While the current quest stage is Rescue the Settlement, Orc Raiding Party can only be engaged by quest card effects.</p><p class='flavor-text'>A few fought their way through and came to Brethil, but many were slain or captured; and the Orcs passed on to the homesteads, and sacked them and burned them.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Orc-Marauders-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Raid.}</p><p class='main-text'>While Orc Marauders is engaged with a player, that player cannot make optional engagements.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Return a different enemy engaged with the defending player to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Colossal-Orc-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Raid.}</p><p class='main-text'>Colossal Orc gets +1 {Threat} for each damage token on him.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} (+3{Attack} instead if the attacking enemy has at least 1 damage token.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Orc-Archer-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Archery 2.}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When resolving the archery keyword on this card, discard the top 2 cards of the first player's deck.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack deals damage, discard the top 2 cards of the first player's deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Orc-Follower-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Raid.}</p><p class='main-text'>X is twice the number of enemies engaged with you.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} (+2 {Attack} instead if there is more than 1 enemy engaged with the defending player.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Angband-Assassin-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Raid.}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Angband Assassin engages you, discard an ally you control, if able.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If the defending character is an ally, discard if after the attack resolves.</p>");
            AddHtml("Azrat-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Raid.} {keyword:Relentless.}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Azrat is damaged by an attack, discard the top card of the attacking player's deck. Reduce the damage by the cost of the discarded card and deal that damage to one attacking character instead.</p>");
            AddHtml("Orc-Burner-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Raid.}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Orc Burner engages a player, discard the top card of that player's deck and deal X damage to characters controlled by that player. X is the cost of the discarded card.</p>");
            AddHtml("Hidden-Grove-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>While Hidden Grove is the active location, the first player may declare one attack before enemy attacks are resolved.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Trigger all raid keywords on cards in play as if it were the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("March-Outpost-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>While March Outpost is the active location, engaged enemies do not trigger the raid keyword.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Each engaged enemy makes an immediate attack, if able.</p>");
            AddHtml("Raider-Camp-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Discard cards from the top of the encounter deck until X Orc enemies are discarded. X is the number of players. Add each enemy discarded this way to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Raider Camp leaves play as the active location, each player may return 1 card from his discard pile to his hand.</p>");
            AddHtml("Burning-Abode-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round, each player must discard the top card of his deck. If the discarded card is an ally, deal 1 Corruption to a hero controlled by that player.</p><p class='flavor-text'>...and the Orcs passwed on to the homesteads, and sacked and burned them.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("March-Road-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>While March Road is in the staging area, enemies use their{Attack} instead of their{Threat} when the raid keyword triggers.</p>");
            AddHtml("Crooked-Blades-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Surge.}</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Deal 1 damage to all characters with at least 1 damage.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} (+3{Attack} instead if the defending character has at least 1 damage.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Renewed-Grief-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The first player attaches Renewed Grief to a hero he controls. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text: &quot;Limit 1 per hero.<b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of each quest phase, either deal 1 Corruption to the attached hero or the attached hero gets -2{Willpower} -2{Attack} and -2{Defense} until the end of the round.&quot;)</p>");
            AddHtml("An-Ill-Fate-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must discard an ally from his hand, if able, and discard X cards from the top of his deck. X is the cost of the discarded ally. If any player did not discard an ally, An Ill Fate gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack destroys an ally, discard the top X cards of the defending player's deck. X is the cost of that ally.</p>");
            AddHtml("Mirth-of-Morgoth-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Remove a hero from the quest and place that hero in the staging area. Each enemy in the staging area makes an attack against that hero during the combat phase. That hero can only declare attack and defend against enemies in the staging area. This effect lasts until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Orcish-Mischief-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must discard an attachment from his hand. Orc enemies gets +X{Attack} until the end of the round. X is the attachment with the highest cost discarded in this way. If any player did not discard an attachment, Orcish Mischief gains surge.</p>");
            AddHtml("Orc-Infiltration-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Shuffle the enemy in play with the lowest{Threat} into the first player's deck. When that enemy is revealed, discarded, or drawn, it engages the first player and makes an immediate attack.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Suddenly a watchman gave a call, and leaping up they saw three hooded shapes, grey&ndash;clad, going stealthy among the stones.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Not-So-High-Is-Your-Destiny-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Add Not So High Is Your Destiny to the staging area. Each player must place 1 Corruption on the hero with the lowest{Willpower} he controls. The player who controls the hero with Curse of Morgoth attached must place 1 Corruption on that hero instead.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&quot;But you are overbold to speak so to the father of Lúthien. Not so high is your destiny, I think...&quot;<br>&ndash;Melian, The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Greatness-is-in-You-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>Permanent.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Attach to the hero with Curse of Morgoth attached.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Add Greatness Is In You to the victory display to ready the attached hero. That hero does not exhaust to attack or defend until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("For-Good-Or-For-Ill-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>Surge. Doomed 4.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Shuffle For Good Or For Ill into the encounter deck.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> If there are no Corruption tokens on the hero with Curse of Morgoth attached, cancel the effects of all keywords on this card. Otherwise, resolve keywords as normal.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&quot;...your fate is twined with that of the Elven&ndash;folk, for good or for ill. Beware of yourself, lest it be ill.&quot;<br>&ndash;Melian, The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Preparing-for-Battle-TUtM", "<p class='flavor-text'>While the Girdle of Melian has long protected Doriath, the marches are a contested region where the Elven&ndash;warriors of Thingol wage unceasing war against the Orcs of Morgoth. Since the disatrous Battle of Unnumbered Tears, the noose grows ever tighter. Every year, the Orcs grow more bold and seize upon any opportunity to waylay those who find themselves without guard or aid. Thingol has tasked you with joining the march&ndash;wardens of Doriath. It is here where you will prove your mettle by standing against those who would seek the destruction of Menegroth and all that is fair and light...</p>");
            AddHtml2("Preparing-for-Battle-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Set the Unscated, Deeds of Daring, and Mighty in Arms objectives aside, out of play. Set Azrat, Weapon of Morgoth, and all copies of Orc Raiding Party aside, out of play. Each player searches the top 10 cards of his deck for an attachment and places it faceup, if able. The first player chooses one faceup attachment and attaches it to an eligible hero. Shuffle all other faceup attachments back into their respective decks. Then, advance to a random stage 2A.</p>");
            AddHtml("Repel-the-Incursion-TUtM", "<p class='flavor-text'>A war party of Orcs is mounting a large assault on one of the main fortifications of the marches. You must repel their advance and prevent them from breaking through.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Choose one of the remaining set aside objectives and attach it to the quest. Discard cards from the top of th encounter deck until X enemies are discarded. X is equal to the number of players in the game. Add each enemy discarded this way to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'>If there are no enemies in the staging area at the end of the quest phase, discard cards from the encounter deck until an enemy is discarded. Add that enemy to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After the first player discards any number of cards from the raid keyword, place 1 damage on this stage. If there are 6 damage tokens on this stage, the players have lost the game.</p><p class='main-text'>While these is at least 1 enemy in play, the players cannot defeat this stage. When the players defeat this stage, remove it from play and advance to a random stage 2A. If only one stage 2 quest remains, adsvance to stage 3A, instead.</p>");
            AddHtml("Rescue-the-Settlement-TUtM", "<p class='flavor-text'>A band of Orcs has launched a raid against a settlement of Thingol's people on the edge of Doriath. You must rescue those who live there from a terrible fate of death or slavery.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Choose one of the remaining set aside objectives and attach it to the quest. Each player must add 1 copy of Orc Raiding Party to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Rescue-the-Settlement-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Encounter Action:</b> Discard 5 progress tokens from this stage to engage 1 copy of Orc Raiding Party in the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After a player discards at least 1 ally from the raid keyword, deal 1 Corruption to a hero controlled by that player.</p><p class='main-text'>While there is at least 1 Orc Raiding Party in play, the players cannot defeat this stage. If there are no copies of Orc Raiding Party in play, immediately remove this stage from play and advance to a random stage 2A. If only one stage 2 quest remains, advance to stage 3A, instead.</p>");
            AddHtml("Destroy-the-War-Engine-TUtM", "<p class='flavor-text'>Scouts have reported that a huge engine of war has been brought down from Angband. This weapon could bring untold destruction to Doriath and the lands around. You must find this weapon and destroy it at all costs.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Choose one of the remaining set aside objectives and attach it to the quest. Add Weapon of Morgoth to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Destroy-the-War-Engine-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After the players quest successfully, Weapon of Morgoth gains the text: &quot;The first player may declare attacks against Weapon of Morgoth during the combat phase as if it were an enemy. When making attacks this way, treat its{Threat} as{Defense} Limit 5 damage per round. When Weapon of Morgoth takes damage equal to or greater than its quest points, it is destroyed and removed from the game.&quot; This effect lasts until the end of the the round.</p><p class='main-text'>After Weapon of Morgoth is destroyed, advance to the next stahe. When the players defeat this stage, remove it from play and advance to a random stage 2A. If only one stage 2 quest remains, advance to stage 3A, instead.</p>");
            AddHtml("A-Final-Proving-TUtM", "<p class='flavor-text'>The march&ndash;wardens speak of one Orc warrior with fear, a veteran of countless battles who has claimed many Elven lives over the years: Azrat. This orc has come to command a large band of Orcs and they have set their sights on eliminating the march&ndash;wardens once and for all...</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Choose one of the remaining set aside objective and attach it to the quest. Add Azrat to the staging area. If there are fewer than X enemies in play, discard cards from the top of the encounter deck, add each enemy discarded this way to the staging area, until X enemies are in play. X is the number of players.</p>");
            AddHtml2("A-Final-Proving-TUtM", "<p class='flavor-text'>It appears your own reputation has grown among the Orcs just as Azrat's has among the Elves. The fearsome Orc seeks you out as the battle rages.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round, discard X cards from the top of the encounter deck. X is the number of players in the game. Add each enemy discarded this way to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'>While Azrat is in play, the players cannot defeat this stage. When the players defeat this stage, they have won the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Trial-Upon-the-Marches-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>Raid</p><p class='main-text'>At the end of the round, if one or more encounter cards in the staging have the raid keyword, discard the top X cards from the first player's deck. X is equal to the highest threat among these encounter cards. When an enemy with the raid keyword is engaged with a player at the end of the round, that player must discard the top X cards of his deck. X is equal to the enemy's threat strength. If a player ever has 0 cards left in his deck, he is eliminated from the game.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Trial-Upon-the-Marches-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>Ransom</p><p class='main-text'>When a character with the Ransom keyword enters play, the player who controls it may discard a number of resources from the resource pools of heroes they control equal to the Ransom value. If they choose not to satisfy this requirement, then that player card loses the &quot;ally&quot; trait and gains the &quot;enemy&quot; trait, immediately engaging the player who played it. Its threat is equal to its willpower and its engagement cost is 0. If this enemy is defeated, remove all damage from it and return it to the player's control as an ally.</p><p class='main-text'>Relentless</p><p class='main-text'>An enemy with Relentless cannot have its attack canceled or be prevented from attacking ny any player card effect. It still can be targeted by other effects that do not specifically prevent attacks.</p>");
            AddHtml("Trial-Upon-the-Marches-Campaign-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>You are playing Campaign Mode.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> The players have earned the Curse of Morgoth burden. Attach Curse of Morgoth and Greatness Is In You to a hero. Add Not So High Is Your Destiny to the staging area. Shuffle For Good or For Ill into the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Trial-Upon-the-Marches-Campaign-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Resolution:</b> Add Curse of Morgoth to the campaign pool. If there are 3 or more victory points in the victory display, add Greatness Is In You to the campaign pool. If there are 0 victory points in the victory display, add Not So High If Your Destiny to the campaign pool. If there are 1 or 2 victory points in the victory display, add For Good or For Ill to the campaign pool. Victory points from player cards do not count for this purpose.</p>");
            AddHtml("Beleg-Strongbow-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>Ranged.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Remove a progress token from a location in play or the current quest stage to lower the cost of the next card your play from your hand this round by 1. (Limit once per round.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>...for he dwelt ever on the marches of Doriath, and he was the greatest woodsman of those days.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Outlaw-Scout-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Discard Outlaw Scout to look at the top 2 cards of the encounter deck. You may discard 1 of them.</p>");
            AddHtml("Knight-of-the-Sword-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>Knight of the Sword gets +1 {Attack} when attacking an enemy with an engagement cost lower than your threat.</p>");
            AddHtml("Doriath-Messenger-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Spend 1{sphere:Lore} resource to give control of Doriath Messenger to another player. That player draws 1 card. (Limit once per round.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Household-Guard-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>While a character with the Noble trait is defending, Household Guard gains:<b>&quot;Response:</b> Deal 1 damage to Household Guard to cancel a shadow effect just triggered. (Limit one per game.)&quot;</p>");
            AddHtml("Petty-dwarf-Survivor-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>Raise the cost to play Petty-dwarf Survivor by 1 for each Noldor hero you control.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Nonetheless, as all the Dwarf&ndash;kind, they were far stronger than their stature promised, and they could cling to life in great hardship.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Elven-Training-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero. Limit 1 per hero.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gets +1 {Attack} for each resource token on Elven Training.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Planning Action:</b> Exhaust attached hero and discard a card from your hand to add 1 resource token to Elven Training. (Limit once per round.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Camp-of-the-Faithful-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust attached hero to attach Camp of the Faithful to a non-unique location in play. While attached to a location, Camp of the Faithful gains: &quot;Treat attached location's printed text box as blank, except for traits.&quot;</p>");
            AddHtml("Hardened-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero with Corruption equal to his{Willpower} Limit 1 per hero.Corruption cannot be removed from attached hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a treachery resolves, exhaust Hardened to draw one card.</p>");
            AddHtml("A-Dangerous-Man-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust a hero you control to choose a non-unique enemy worth no victory points engaged with you. If the{Attack} of that enemy is lower than the{Attack} of the exhausted hero, add A Dangerous Man to the victory display to add that enemy to the victory display.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&quot;I am not a chicken&ndash;heart, as men know; but I am not your match&quot;<br>&ndash;Androg, The Children of Húrin</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Curse-of-Morgoth-TUtM", "<p class='main-text'>Permanent.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After the attached hero takes Corruption discard the top card of the encounter deck. If it is a treachery card, the attached hero becomes corrupted until the end of the round.</p><p class='main-text'>If the attached hero leaves play, the players have lost the game.</p>");

        }

        private void AmongTheOutlaws()
        {
            AddHtml("Among-the-Outlaws-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>Dilemma Deck</b></p><p class='main-text'>The 9 objective cards with the Dilemma trait are set aside into a separate deck at the start of the game and shuffled. When players quest unsuccessfully, the top card of the dilemma deck is revealed. Each dilemma card gives the player two options. Carrying out the first option helps the Gaurwaith while carrying out the second option, which adds the card to the victory display, helps the woodmen.</p><p class='main-text'><b> Corruption and Objective Allies</b></p><p class='main-text'>Objective allies are immune to corruption and corruption cannot be placed on objective allies for any reason.</p>");
            AddHtml("Bor-the-Faithful-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Discard 1 Corruption for Bór the Faithful to ready him. He gets +2 {Attack} and +1 {Willpower} until the end of the round. (Limit once per round.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>...and they followed Maedhros and Maglor, and cheated the hope of Morgoth, and were faithful.<br>&ndash;The Silmarillion</p>");
            AddHtml("Brethil-Hound-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Brethil Hound participates in an attack that destroys an enemy, choose a player. That player reduces his threat by 1. (Limit once per phase.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Algund-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> When the discard pile is shuffled back into the encounter deck, deal X Corruption to Algund to choose X cards in the discard pile. These cards are not shuffled back into the encounter deck.</p><p class='flavor-text'>...and others also came from that land: old Algund, the oldest of the fellowship, who had fled from the Nirnaeth...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Fostered-Son-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Discard Fostered Son to reduce the cost of the next unique Edain character you play this phase by 2.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Thus it was that the sons of Galdor were fostered in Brethil by Haldir their uncle, according to the custom of Men in that time...<br>&ndash;The Silmarillion</p>");
            AddHtml("Elder-of-the-Realm-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a treachery is revealed, discard a card from hand (spend 1{sphere:Lore} to discard the top card of your deck instead). If the first letter of the treachery card's title matches that of the discarded card, cancel the &quot;when revealed&quot; effects of the revealed card. (Limit once per game.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Wolf-man-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>Ransom 4.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust Wolf-man to immediately declare him as an attacker (and resolve his attack) against an engaged enemy with one hit point remaining.</p>");
            AddHtml("Neithan-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to Túrin Turambar. Limit 1 Name in play.</p><p class='main-text'>Resource on Neithan can be discard to satisfy the ransom keyword.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> When an enemy with the ransom keyword is defeated, add 2 resources to Neithan.</p>");
            AddHtml("Forge-of-Belegost-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a Dwarf character.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust Forge of Belegost and attached character to heal X damage on a character. X is the number of Item attachments on that character.</p><p class='flavor-text'>...yet in the tempering of steel alone of all crafts the Dwarves were never outmatched even by the Noldor...<br>&ndash;The Silmarillion</p>");
            AddHtml("Angrist-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero with the House of House of B‰or trait. Restricted.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gets +1 {Attack}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust Angrist and the attached hero to choose a facedown enemy. Turn that enemy faceup and deal 4 damage to it.</p><p class='flavor-text'>...and from the iron claws that held it he cut a Silmaril.<br>&ndash;The Silmarillion</p>");
            AddHtml("Song-of-Parting-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After an encounter card with at least 3{Threat} is revealed from the encounter deck, choose and ready a character. That character gets +2 {Willpower} +2 {Attack} and +2 {Defense} until the end of the round.</p><p class='flavor-text'>...for he believed that he must now say farewell to both love and light.<br>&ndash;The Silmarillion</p>");
            AddHtml("None-Shall-Break-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Ready each character with an Oath attached. (Lower the cost of None Shall Break by 2 if each character that readies takes 1 Corruption.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>For so sworn, good or evil, an oath may not be broken, and it shall pursue oathkeeper and oathbreaker to the world's end.<br>&ndash;The Silmarillion</p>");
            AddHtml("Fellowship-with-the-Outlaws-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After the 3rd Dilemma objective is added to the victory display, advance to stage 2A and remove{sphere:Fellowship} With The Outlaws from the game.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After the players quest unsuccessfully, reveal the top card of the dilemma deck.</p><p class='main-text'>If there are 7 cards in the dilemma deck discard pile, the player lose the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Forweg-Enemy-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>Relentless.</p><p class='main-text'>Allies cannot attack or defend against Forweg.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Forweg makes his first attack each round, he engages the next player and makes an immediate attack (discard and deal a new shadow card for this attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Forweg-Objective-Ally-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>The first player gains control of Forweg.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> Forweg declares and resolves an attack against a random Woodmen enemy engaged with the first player at the end of the combat phase.</p><p class='main-text'>If Forweb leaves play, the players lose the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Androg-Enemy-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>Androg gets +1 {Attack} for each hero you control with at least 1 Corruption.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&quot;The hardest of heart was one named Androg...&quot;<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Androg-Objective-Ally-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>The first player gains control of Androg.</p><p class='main-text'>Each Woodmean enemy gets -5 engagemet cost for each Corruption on heroes the first player controls.</p><p class='main-text'>If Androg leaves play, the players lose the game.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&quot;Outlaws know no law but their needs. Look to your own, Neithan, and leave us to mind ours.&quot;<br>&ndash;Androg, The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Larnach's-Daughter-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Forweg declares an attack on Larnach's Daughter. The first player may declare an eligible defender against this attack. If not character is destroyed by this attack, add Larnach's Daughter the the victory display. If no defender is declared, each player deal 3 Corruption among characters he controls.</p><p class='flavor-text'>A young woman is running for her life. Will you interfere with the man pursuing her or leave her to her fate?</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Teiglin-Hunter-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>While Teiglin Hunter is engaged with a player, all enemies engaged with that player get +1 {Attack}</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> All enemies engaged with the defending player get +1 {Attack} until the end of the phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Hound-of-the-Woodmen-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the start of the encounter phase, discard cards from the top of the encounter deck until an enemy is discarded. Add that enemy to the staging area. This ability does not stack with other copies of Hound of the Woodmen.</p><p class='flavor-text'>But they earned less gratitude so from the outlaws than from beasts and birds, and they were saved rather by their dogs and their fences...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Homestead-Defender-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>While Homestead Defender is engaged with a player, Woodmen enemies engaged with that player not named Homestead Defender cannot be attacked by non-objective characters.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> All enemies engaged with the defending player get +2 {Defense} until the end of the phase.</p>");
            AddHtml("Desperate-Outlaw-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After an attack against Desperate Outlaw resolves, Desperate Outlaw makes an immediate attack against the defending player.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy makes an additional attack after this one.</p>");
            AddHtml("Cruel-Robber-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Cruel Robber attack, discard 1 attachment the defending player controls.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Discard 1 attachment from the defending character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Driven-Outcast-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Driven Outcast attacks, deal 1 damage to a defending character.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> After this attack resolves, deal 1 damage to the defending character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Forest-Clearing-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>(Stage 1B)<b>Response:</b> After Forst Clearing is explored, reduce each player's threat by 2.</p><p class='main-text'><b>(Stage 2B):</b> While Forest Clearing is the active location, the first Gaurwaith enemy revealed each round gains surge.</p>");
            AddHtml("Scattered-Homestead-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>While Scattered Homestead is in the staging area, discard cards from the encounter deck at the end of the round until an enemy is discarded. Add that enemy to the staging area.</p><p class='flavor-text'>...they were of Haleth's folk for the most part, but owned no lord, and they lived both by hunting and husbandry...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Tilled-Field-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>(Stage 1B)<b>Response:</b> After Tilled Field is explored, add 1 resource to each hero's resource pool.</p><p class='main-text'>(Stage 2B) Whne<b>Revealed:</b> Each player must exhaust a hero he controls.</p>");
            AddHtml("Hedge-and-Stockade-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>(Stage 1B):</b> While Hedge and Stockade is the active location, all Woodmen enemies get +2 {Defense} and 0 engagement cost.</p><p class='main-text'><b>(Stage 2B):</b> While Hedge and Stockage is the active location, all Gaurwaith enemies -1{Attack} and 0 engagement cost.</p>");
            AddHtml("Woods-of-Teiglin-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'>(Stage 1B)<b>Response:</b> After Wood of Teiglin is explored, each player draws 1 card.</p><p class='main-text'><b>(Stage 2B):</b> While Woods of Teiglin is in the staging area, all Gaurwaith enemies get +1 {Threat} +1 {Attack} and +1 {Defense}</p>");
            AddHtml("Dogs-and-Fences-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must choose: Either deal X damage among heroes he controls, where X is equal to the number of engaged Woodmen enemies plus 2, or treat the printed text bost of each non-objective character he controls as if it were blank, except for keywords and Traits, until the end of the round.</p><p class='flavor-text'>But when spring was come it was perilous for the Gaurwaith to linger so near the houses of the woodmen...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Horn-calls-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must search the encounter deck and discard pile for a Woodmen enemy and put it into play engaged with hum. Then, each engaged Woodmen enemy makes an immediate attack.</p><p class='flavor-text'>...and there were paths from stead to stead, and men could summon help at need by horn&ndash;calls.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("No-Law-But-Their-Needs-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Either each player must immediately exhaust and commit 1 hero to the quest, or raise each player's threat by 4.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Deal 1 damage to the attacking enemy. If that enemy is destroyed, deal 1 Corruption to the defending character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Wolf-men-of-the-Winter-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player engaged with a Gaurwaith enemy must discard all resources he controls. If a player did not discard at least 3 resources, deal 1 damage to each character he controls.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The defending player must pay 1 resource of the attacking enemy gets +3{Attack}</p>");
            AddHtml("Banded-Attack-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player deals X damage among characters he controls, where X is the number of Gaurwaith enemies engaged with that player.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} for each enemy engaged with the defending player.</p>");
            AddHtml("Blood-Upon-the-Grass-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must choose: Either raise his threat by 1 for each Corruption on characters he controls, or choose character he controls with at least 1 Corruption. That character is immediately corrupted.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Exhaust all characters the defending player controls with at least 1 Corruption.</p>");
            AddHtml("An-Evil-and-Dangerous-Way-AtO", "<p class='flavor-text'>After several years of service on the marches you have been forced to leave Doriath after a quarrel with Saeros, one of Thingol's counselors, ended in his death. Staying would have meant facing the king's doom. Wandering aimlessly at first, you have joined a band of outlaws led by Forweg. These desperate men are called Gaurwaith by the woodmen.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Set all enemy and treachery cards with the Gaurwaith trait aside, out of play. Shuffle all Dilemma cards together into a dilemma deck. Add{sphere:Fellowship} with the Outlaws to the staging area. Put Forweg and Androg into play, ally side faceup. Each player searches the encounter deck for a different location and adds it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("An-Evil-and-Dangerous-Way-AtO", "<p class='flavor-text'>The Gaurwaith raid the woodmen relentless in the winter. You must choose: restrain their evil deeds or take part in them.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> The players must travel to a location during the travel phase, if able.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After a location is explored, deal X Corruption among characters the first player controls. X is the{Threat} of that location.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After a Woodmen enemy is destroyed, deal 1 Corruption to each character that participated in the attack. (If Forweg or Androg participated in the attack, deal 1 Corruption to each hero controlled by the engaged player.)</p>");
            AddHtml("To-Govern-the-Fellowship-AtO", "<p class='flavor-text'>You have defended the woodmen and shed the blood of some of the outlaws. Now, you must win their respect through force of arms or persuasion and seize control of the fellowship if you hope to survive.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Flip Forweg and Androg to their enemy sides, remove all tokens from them, and place them in the staging area. Discard all Woodmen enemies. Remove all enemy and treachery cards with the Woodmen trait from the encounter deck and discard pile and set them aside, out of play. Shuffle the set aside enemy and treachery cards with the Gaurwaith trait into the encounter deck. Reveal 1 encounter card per player.</p>");
            AddHtml2("To-Govern-the-Fellowship-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>Gaurwaith enemies may be attacked with{Willpower} instead of{Attack} If an enemy would be damaged this way, place progress tokens on it instead of damage token. When an enemy has progress equal to its hit points, add it to the victory display and place those progress tokens on the quest.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Place 5 progress tokens on this quest stage for each card in the discard pile of the dilemma deck.</p><p class='main-text'>The players cannot defeat this stage while Forweg is in play. If the players defeat this stage, they have won the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Cull-the-Weak-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Either each player must discard the character he controls with the fewest hit points to remove all damage from one character he controls, or add Cull the Weak to the victory display and each player must deal 3 damage to a hero he controls.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The weak are viewed as a hindrance by the outlaws. Will you defend the weakest among you or give in to the idea that only the strong should survive?</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Punish-the-Trespassers-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Either each player must exhaust a character he controls to discard a Woodmen enemy from play, or add Punish the Trespassers to the victory display and each player must search the encounter deck and discard pile for a Woodmen enemy and put it into play engaged with him. One of these must be Hound of the Woodmen if able.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The Gaurwaith do not allow outsiders to tread on their land. Will you join them in waylaying the trespasser or will you speak for mercy?</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Raid-the-Homestead-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Either each player deals X Corruption to a hero he controls to add X resources to that heroe's resource pool, or add Raid the Homestead to the victory display and discard all resources from play (any hero that does not discard a resource takes 2 damage).</p><p class='flavor-text'>In the bitter winter, the Gaurwaith steal food and supplies from the woodmen. Will you help them take from those who are also struggling to survive?</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Turn-a-Blind-Eye-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Either each player must deal 1 Corruption to a hero he controls to reduce his threat by 3, or add Turn a Blind Eye to the victory display and exhaust all heroes in play.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The Gaurwaith are hardened men and have committed deplorable acts in their latest ranging. Will you ignore their misdeeds or challenge them?</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Cruel-of-Heart-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach to the hero with Curse of Morgoth attached. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text:<b>&quot;Forced:</b> After an ally enters play, exhaust attached hero to deal 1 damage to that ally.&quot;)</p><p class='flavor-text'>...but many took to robbert and became cruel.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Bitterness-of-Exile-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Remove each character with at least 1 Corruption from the quest.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Reveal the top card of the encounter deck. It it is an eney or location, add it to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Craft-In-Wood-and-Field-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to the hero with Curse of Morgoth attached.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After the players travel to a location, choose a player and exhaust attached hero to reduce that player's threat by the{Threat} of the active location.</p>");
            AddHtml("Hardship-of-the-Wild-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>Permanent.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gets +1 {Defense} and +1 hit point.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> Add Hardship of the Wild to the victory display, and remove it from the campaign pool, to cancel 2 points of damage just deal to attached hero.</p>");
            AddHtml("Among-the-Outlaws-Campaign-AtO", "<p class='main-text'>You are playing Campaign Mode.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> Discard the top card of the dilemma deck to cancel the &quot;when revealed&quot; effects of a card that was just revealed from the encounter deck. (Limit once per game.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>There before the Nirnaeth many men had dwelt in scattered homesteads; they were of Haleth's folk for the most part, but owned no lord, and they lived both by hunting and husbandry, keeping swine in the mast&ndash;lands, and tilling clearings in the forest which were fenced from the wild. But most were now destroyed, or had fled into Brethil, and all that region lay under the feat of Ores, and of outlaws.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml2("Among-the-Outlaws-Campaign-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>Resolution:</b> Add Bitterness of Exile to the campaign pool. If there is at least 1 card in the dilemma deck discard pule, add Cruel of Heart to the campaign pool. These burdens have been earned by the players. Each player may attach a copy of Hardship of the Wild to a hero he controls. If there are no cards in the dilemma deck discard pule, add Craft In Wood And Field to the campaign pool. These boons have been earned by the players.</p><p class='flavor-text'>All were silent. Then Turin spike again. &quot;Do you take me to be your captain? Then I will lead you first away into the wild, far from the homes of Men. There we may find better fortune, or not; but at least we shall earn less hatred of our own kind.&quot;<br>Then all those that were of the Poeple of Hador gathered to him, and took him as their captain; and the others with less good will agreed.<br>And at once he led them away out of that country.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml2("Among-the-Outlaws-AtO", "<p class='main-text'><b>Ransom</b></p><p class='main-text'>When a character with the Ransom keyword enters play, the player who controls it may discard a number of resources from the resource pools of heroes they control equal to the Ransom value. If they choose not to satisfy this requirement, then that player card loses the &quot;ally&quot; card type and gains the &quot;enemy&quot; card type, immediately engaging the player who played it. Its {Threat} is equal to its {Willpower} and its engagement cost is 0. If this enemy is defeated, remove all damage from it and return it its owner's control as an ally.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Relentless</b></p><p class='main-text'>An enemy with the Relentless keyword cannot have its attack canceled or be prevented from attacking by player card effects. It can still be targeted by other effects which do no specifically prevent attacks.</p>");
        }

        private void TheBetrayalOfMim()
        {
            AddHtml("Orc-Scout-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Orc Scout engages a player, either add 1 encounter card to a random non-unique location or Orc Scout makes an immediate attack.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Either discard 2 cards from your hand or the attacking enemy makes an additional attack after this one.</p>");
            AddHtml("Poison-Archer-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>Archery 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Poison Archer damages a character, that character cannot ready until the end of the round.</p><p class='flavor-text'>...and in that foray he was struck by a poisoned orc&ndash;arrow, and was brought back dying in pain...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Angband-Spy-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After an ally is played from hand, either add 1 encounter card to the staging area of a random non-unique location or raise each player's threat by 1.</p><p class='flavor-text'>...and ere long Amon R–dh was surrounded by spies, lurking unobserved in the wilderness...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Wolf-sentinel-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>X is equal to the number of characters committed to the quest by the first player.</p><p class='flavor-text'>...the Orcs made their encampment in a bare dale, and set wolf&ndash;sentinels all about its rim.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Angband-Warrior-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Angband Warrior destroys a character, either add 1 encounter card to the staging area of a random non-unique location or reveal an encounter card.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} (+2 {Attack} instead if the quest stage is 2B).</p>");
            AddHtml("Amon-Rudh-Discovered-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of the encounter phase, discard the top X cards of the encounter deck. Each player adds an enemy discarded from this effect to the staging area. X is 2 more than the number of players in the game.</p><p class='flavor-text'>...but that steep as were its sides men could reach the summit by climbing a stair cut into the rock...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Amon-Rudh-Hidden-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>While Amon R–dh is the active location, it gains: &quot;After a character readies during the refresh phase, heal 1 damage from the character.&quot;</p><p class='flavor-text'>&quot;We have seen it, but never nearer...&quot;<br>&ndash;Androg, The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Gate-of-the-Garth-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After an encounter card is added to the staging area of Gate of the Garth outside of the quest phase, each player raises he threat by 2.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Gate of the Garth is explored, reduce each player's threat by 5.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&quot;Not the door of the house, but the gate of the garth...&quot;<br>&ndash;MŒm, The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Stony-Heath-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Stony Heath is the active location, enemies get +1 {Attack}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Stony Heath is explored, add 1 resource to the resource pool of each hero.</p><p class='flavor-text'>They passed over the tumbled stones, and began to climb; for Amon R–dh stood upon the eastern edge of the high moorlands that rose between the vales of Sirion and Narog...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Broken-Land-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Broken Lands is the active location, it gainsd,<b>&quot;Forced:</b> After any amount of progress is placed on Broken Lands, deal 1 damage to each questing character.&quot;</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Broken Land is explored, each player draws 3 cards.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Upon the eastern side a broken land climbed slowly up to the high ridges among knots of birch and rowan, and ancient thorn&ndash;tress rooted in rock.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Holly-thicket-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Holly-thicket is the active location, the player attack step of the combat phase happens first.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Each player must discard an attachment he controls.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Soon after, it chanced that as the grey light of a day of rain was falling Túrin and his men were sheltering in a holly&ndash;thicket...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Dark-Dells-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Dark Dells is the active location, each non-objective ally's text box is treated as if it were blank, except for traits.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Dark Dells is explored, you may look at the facedown encounter cards in an adjacent location's staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Secret-Stair-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach to an enemy in play. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text: &quot;Limit 1 per enemy. Each enemy in play gains relentless.&quot;)</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack destroys a character, add 1 encounter card to the staging area of a random non-unique location.</p>");
            AddHtml("Rains-Out-of-Season-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each non-objective character gets -1{Willpower} -1{Attack} -1{Defense} until the end of the round. You may cancel this effect on a character if you immediately deal 1 damage to that character.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The defending character gets -2{Defense}</p>");
            AddHtml("Steep-Slopes-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Steep Slopes is the active location, it gains:<b>&quot;Forced:</b> When a character or an enemy takes damage, discard the top card of the encounter deck. If it is a treachery, double the damage dealt.&quot;</p><p class='flavor-text'>...the land ran down into wastes of great stones with falls and holes masked by bramble and thorn.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("More-Hunted-Than-Hunters-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> End the quest phase without resolving the quest. Treat the engagement cost of all enemies as 0 until the end of the round. If it is stage 2B, search the encounter deck and discard pile for an enemy and add it to the staging area.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Until the end of the phase, reveal an encounter card after this enemy is destroyed.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ill-content-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Deal 1 Corruption to each character with at least 1 damage. If no Corruption is dealt by this effect, Ill-content gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack destroys a character, deal X Corruption among heroes the defending player controls (X is equal to the cost of the destroyed character).</p>");
            AddHtml("Captive-Son-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> If MŒm's objective side is faceup, add 1 progress token to MŒm if this is the first copy of Captive Son revealed this round. Then, if the number of progress tokens on MŒm is equal to or greater than his{Willpower} flip him.</p><p class='flavor-text'>It was the capture of his son and their threat to torture him that led MŒm to his treachery.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Sleepless-Eyes-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must choose and exhaust X non-objective characters, where X is the number of Grievance objectives attached to MŒm (if it is stage 2B, treat X as 3 instead). Deal 1 damage to each character exhausted in this way.</p><p class='flavor-text'>And those who were on the watch saw him sitting on through the night silent and still as a stone, save for his sleepless eyes that glinted as they roved in the dark.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Curse-of-a-Dwarf-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach to the hero with the highest printed{Attack} (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text: &quot;Limit 1 per hero.<b>Forced:</b> After the attached hero destroys an enemy, deal damage to the attached hero equal to that hero's printed{Attack} Then, discard Curse of a Dwarf.&quot;)</p>");
            AddHtml("Sack-of-Roots-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Attach Sack of Roots to MŒm to choose and discard a Condition attachment from play. Any player may trigger this action.</p><p class='flavor-text'>But he marked, and others also, that MŒm set more store by the sack and his load than it seemed worth to the eye.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Bound-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>While Bound is attached to MŒm, it gains, &quot;Ignore the forced effect on the attached character. The attached character cannot ready.&quot;</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Attach Bound to MŒm and exhaust him, if able. Any player may trigger this action.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Then MŒm opened his eyes and pointed to his bonds; and when he was released he spoke fiercely. 'Learn this, fools!' he said. 'Do not put bonds on a Dwarf! He will not forgive it.'<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Khim-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. The first player gains control of KhŒm.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the combat phase, raise your threat by 2. You may declare an attack against KhŒm with a non-objective character as a response. If that attack deals damage, cancel this effect.</p><p class='main-text'>Forced; After KhŒm is destroyed, attach KhŒm to MŒm.</p>");
            AddHtml("Unfading-Grief-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach to the hero with Curse of Morgoth attached. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text: &quot;The cost of the first card you play each round is increased by one.&quot;)</p><p class='flavor-text'>...and that grief was graven on the face of Túrin and never faded.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Chest-of-Stone-and-Wood-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>Guarded.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Shuffle Chest of Stone and Wood into the encounter deck.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust a hero to claim this attachment when its free of encounters.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Discard Chest of Stone and Wood to either draw 2 cards or add 2 resources to attached hero's resource pool.</p>");
            AddHtml("Mim-Enemy-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>MŒm engages the first player.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After MŒm is flipped, remove all damage from MŒm and remove the Grievance objectives from the game. If it is stage 1B, add 1 encounter card to the staging area of each non-unique location, ignoring any damage tokens.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When a character you control delcares an attack, deal 1 damage to that character.</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Mim-Objective-Ally-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>The first player gains control of MŒm.</p><p class='main-text'>MŒm gets -1{Willpower} for each attached Grievance objective. If his{Willpower} is 0, flip MŒm.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the refresh phase, add 1 encounter card to the staging area of a random non-unique location.</p><p class='main-text'>If MŒm is destroyed, flip MŒm.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Land-of-Bow-and-Helm-TBoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>The Gaurwaith have accepted your leadership, and you have led them away from the homes of Men. However, the ways of the outlaws are not easily changed. Even worse, the weather has been merciless and the Orcs have come down from the North in ever&ndash;growing numbers. By chance one day, your scouts capture a strange group of Petty&ndash;dwarves, led by one called MŒm. He is indignant at first and protests his captivity, but eventually offers to show you a place of rest and refuge as ransom.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Set up the Dor-Cúarthol area (see rules). The first player takes control of MŒm, as an ally. Place the 3 Grievance objectives in the staging area. (They are considered to be in every location's staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Land-of-Bow-and-Helm-TBoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>You have made the House of Ransom a heart of resistance against the forces of Morgoth. But danger lurks, as the Enemy's servants seeks to find this secret haven, and it is only a matter of time before it is discovered. Even worse, the loyalty of MŒm is ever uncertain...</p><p class='main-text'>Time 6.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the refresh phase, add 1 encounter card to a random non-unique location for each player in the game. A location may not have a number of encounter cards greater than its{Threat} plus the number of players.</p><p class='main-text'>When the last time counter is removed, advance to the next stage.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Wrath-of-Angband-TBoM", "<p class='flavor-text'>By fate or treachery, the Orcs of Morgoth have discovered the location of Bar&ndash;en&ndash;Danwedh, the House of Ransom. Now you must fight for your very life against the tide of foes suddenly at your door.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Flip Amon R–dh and make it the active location. If MŒm's objective side is faceup, flip him.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Wrath-of-Angband-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>Skip the staging step of the quest phase. Encounter cards cannot be added to the staging area of non-unique locations. Players cannot travel.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of the quest phase, move all cards in a location's staging are one location to the left, if able.</p><p class='main-text'>If there are no encounter cards in a staging area and non enemies engaged with a player, the players have won the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Betrayal-of-Mim-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>Creating the Dor-Cúarthol Area</p><p class='main-text'>To create the Dor-Cúarthol area, place Amon R–dh (Hidden side faceup) in the staging area. Then, place Gate of Garth immediately to its right. Then, shuffle the remaining locations and place them in a sequence to the right of Gate of Garth. Finally, choose one location to be the active location.</p><p class='main-text'>A resource token is placed on a location to indicate that it is the active location. The active location contributes its threat to the staging area. Each location has its own staging area. Only the encounter cards added to a staging area of the active location are considered to be in the staging area. When you are instructed to add a card to the staging area of a location, place an encounter card facedown underneath it.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Betrayal-of-Mim-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>If a location is the active location when an encounter card is added to its staging area, immediately reveal and resolve that card during staging. During the staging step of the quest phase, any cards revealed are considered to be added to the active location's staging area.</p><p class='main-text'>You may place progress on the active location as normal through questing. When a number of progress tokens are placed on the active location equal to its quest points, it is considered to be explored. Place a damage token on it. A location with a damage token can no longer have progress added or removed from it.</p><p class='main-text'>During the travel phase, the players may travel to any location, even if the current active location has not been explored. Similarly, you may remain at a location that has already been explored. Player card effects that discard or switch locations cannot be used. When the players travel to a location, first place any cards in the staging are facedown underneath the old active location. Then, immediately reveal and resolve any facedown encounter cards under the new active location.</p><p class='main-text'>If a location has a damage token on it, encounter cards cannot be added to its staging area (any encounter cards already in the staging area of a location when it is explored remain in play). Note that this applies to the staging step of questing as well (since treacheries are not added to the staging area, they will still resolve as normal). Since cards cannot be added to such a location's staging area, when adding a card to a random non-unique location, do not add a card to a location with a damage token if it is randomly selected.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Betrayal-of-Mim-Campaign-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>You are playing Campaign Mode.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Discard a hero you control to discard 2 facedown encounter cards from the staging area of a location. Any player may trigger this action. (Limit once per game.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>So it was that MŒm came into the Tale of the Children of Húrin. For he stumbled up on his knees before Túrin's feet and begged for his life. 'I am old,' he said, 'and poor. Only a Dwarf, as you say, not an Orc. MŒm is my name. Do not let them slay me, master, for no cause, as Orcs would.'<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Betrayal-of-Mim-Campaign-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Resolution:</b> If no Grievance objectives were attached to MŒm, the players may either remove one burden from the campaign pool or add Chest of Stone and Wood to the campaign pool. If only one Grievance objective was attached to MŒm you may add Chest of Stone and Wood to the campaign pool. If more than one Grievance objective was attached to MŒm, add Unfading Grief to the campaign pool.</p><p class='flavor-text'>When morning came the storm was passed away eastward over Lothlann, and the sun of autumn rose hot and bright; but the Orcs hating this almost as much as thunder, and believing that Túrin would have fled far from that place and all trace of his flight be washed away, they departed in haste, eager to return to Angband. Far off Gwindor saw them marching northward over the steaming sands of Anfauglith. Thus it came to pass that they returned to Morgoth empty&ndash;handed, and left behind them the son of Húrin, who sat crazed and unwitting on the slopes of Taur&ndash;nu&ndash;Fuin, bearing a burden heavier than their bonds.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Galadriel-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>X is the{Threat} of the active location.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After an encounter card is revealed from the encounter deck, deal 3 Corruption to Galadriel to cancel its effects and add it the the victory display.</p><p class='flavor-text'>...for she yearned to see the wide unguarded landed and to rule there a realm at her own will.<br>&ndash;The Silmarillion</p>");
            AddHtml("Gaurwaith-Watchman-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>Ransom 3.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Quest Action:</b> Deal 1 Corruption to Gaurwaith Watchman to name an encounter card type. Until the end of the phase, when the first card of that type is revealed, shuffle it back into the encounter deck and reveal the next encounter card.</p>");
            AddHtml("Soldier-of-the-Fountain-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>Reduce the cost to play Soldier of the Fountain if you are engaged with an enemy with printed hit points of 5 or more.</p><p class='flavor-text'>There shinning fountains played, and in the courts of Turgon stood images of the Trees of old...<br>&ndash;The Silmarillion</p>");
            AddHtml("Elf-maiden-of-Nargothrond-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Discard the top 2 cards of your deck. Then, if any of the discarded cards do not have a{sphere:Spirit} resource icon, Elf-maiden of Nargothrond gets -1{Willpower} until the end of the phase. Otherwise, place 1 progress token on a location and Elf-maiden of Nargothrond gets +1 {Willpower} until the end of the phase. (Limit once per round.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Gwindor-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After an ally you control is destroyed, exhaust Gwindor to add +1 {Attack} to each character you control until the end of the phase. (Limit once per round.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>Now his wrath was kindled to madness, and he leapt forth on horseback, and many riders with him...<br>&ndash;The Silmarillion</p>");
            AddHtml("Ulfang-the-Black-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round, discard the top card of your deck. Then, if the top card of your discard pile is an ally, deal 1 Corruption to Ulfang the Black.</p><p class='flavor-text'>In this hour the plots of Ulfang were revealed.<br>&ndash;The Silmarillion</p>");
            AddHtml("Feanorian-Lamp-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a Noldor hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust F‰anorian Lamp to choose a non-unique location. That location gets -2{Threat} until the end of the round. (Discard F‰anorian Lamp to also treat the location's text box as blank until the end of the round.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>...for they were made of old in Valinor, and neither wind nor water could quench them...<br>&ndash;Unfinished Tales</p>");
            AddHtml("Gorthol-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to Túrin Turambar. Limit 1 Name in play.</p><p class='main-text'>Túrin Turambar gains a{sphere:Leadership} resource icon.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Raise your threat by 2 to ready an ally. (Limit once per round.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Smoking-Axe-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'>Restricted. May be played without a resource match for 1 additional resource.</p><p class='main-text'>Attach to an enemy in play.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gets +1 {Attack}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After the attached enemy is destroyed, attach it to a hero that participated in the attack and ready that hero.</p>");
            AddHtml("Trained-to-Wariness-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Quest Action:</b> Exhaust a character with the Ranger trait. Then, until the end of the phase, after the first enemy is revealed from the encounter deck, lower your threat by X, where X is the{Threat} of the revealed enemy.</p><p class='flavor-text'>But Túrin, trained in the wild to wariness, saw him from the corner of his eye...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Hounding-to-his-Death-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Combat Action:</b> Choose a character you control. That character deals X damage to an enemy engaged with you. X is the character's printed{Attack} Then, that chracter becomes corrupted.</p><p class='flavor-text'>..but Túrin came after him like a hound, and however he ran, or swerved, still the sword was behind him to egg him on.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Arts-of-the-Enemy-TBoM", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> Deal 1 Corruption to a hero to cancel a shadow effect just triggered during combat. Move that shadow card to a character. When that character attacks, apply the shadow effect, applying any text that refers to &quot;attacking enemy&quot; to the attacking character and any text that refers to the &quot;defending character&quot; to the defending enemy, if able.</p>");
        }

        private void TheFallOfNargothrond()
        {
            AddHtml("The-Fall-of-Nargothrond-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>Glaurung Deck</p><p class='main-text'>Take all treacheries with the Glaurung trait and shuffle them together to form the Glaurung deck.</p><p class='main-text'>Additional Setup</p><p class='main-text'>All of the non-unique enemies from the Trial Upon the Marches set are included in the encounter deck for this scenario.</p><p class='main-text'>Raid</p><p class='main-text'><b>Note:</b> Raid in this scenario works slightly differently than it did in Trial Upon the Marches.</p><p class='main-text'>At the end of the round, if one or more encounter cards in the staging area have the raid keyword, discard the top X cards from the encounter deck. X is equal to the highest threat among these encounter cards. When an enemy with the raid keyword is engaged with a player at the end of the round, that player must discard the top X cards of the encounter deck. X is equal to the enemy's threat strength.</p><p class='main-text'>Relentless</p><p class='main-text'>An enemy with Relentless cannot have its attack canceled or be prevented from attacking by any player card effect. It still can be targeted by other effects that do not specifically prevent attacks.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Fall-of-Nargothrond-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>Ransom</p><p class='main-text'>When a character with the Ransom keyword enters play, the player who controls it may discard a number of resources from the resource pools of heroes they control equal to the Ransom value. If they choose not to satisfy this requirement, then that player card loses the &quot;ally&quot; trait and gains the &quot;enemy&quot; trait, immediately engaging the player who played it. Its threat is equal to its willpower and its engagement cost is 0. If this enemy is defeated, remove all damage from it and return it to the player's control as an ally.</p>");
            AddHtml("Glaurung-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Indestructible.} {keyword:Raid.} {keyword:Relentless.}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Glaurung attacks, reveal the top card of the Glaurung deck.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Remove X damage from Glaurung to remove an attached Innocent objective and place it under The Hopes of Nargothrond. X is 5 times the number of players. Any player may trigger this action.</p>");
            AddHtml("Only-In-Secrecy-Lies-Hope-TFoN", "<p class='flavor-text'>After surviving MŒm's betrayal, you have made your way to the Elven kingdom of Nargothrond. It is one of the three protected fortresses of the Elves, and Morgoth is seeking ever to find and destroy it. The ruler of Nargothrond, Orodreth, seeks your counsel. Should the Elves of Nargothrond continue to hide and ambush the Enemy only when prudent? Or should they gather arms and boldly assault the Enemy?</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Create the Glaurung deck (see rules). Set Glaurung Deep River Mighty Bridge The Hopes of Nargothrond and The Ruin of Nargothrond aise, out of play. Shuffle the 10 Innocent objectives into a separate innocent deck. The first player must choose: either trust to secrecy and advance to stage 1B, or take an aggressive approach and advance to stage 2A.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Only-In-Secrecy-Lies-Hope-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>You have advised Orodreth to keep his forces out of sight and only strike when necessary. With this approach, you hope to delay the hour of the Enemy's arrival. Still, his forces gather and the hammer will fall soon on Nargothrond. Hopefully, the natural defenses of the fortress will hold.</p><p class='main-text'>Skip the quest and combat phase this round.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Reduce each player's threat by 10. Add Deep River to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round, advance to stage 3A.</p>");
            AddHtml("Arms-Are-The-Only-Wall-TFoN", "<p class='flavor-text'>&quot;If you do nothing to halt him, all Beleriand will fall under his shadow before many years are passed, and then one by one he will smoke you out of your earths. And what then? A pitiable remnant will fly south and west, to cover on the shores of the Sea, caught between Morgoth and Osse. Better then to win a time of glory, though it be short&ndash;lived; for the end will be no worse. You speak of secrecy, and say that therein lies the only hope; but could you ambush and waylay every scout and spy of Morgoth to the last and least, so that none came every back with tidings to Angband, yet from that he would learn that you lived and guess where.<br>&ndash;Túrin Turambar, The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml2("Arms-Are-The-Only-Wall-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>Following your advice, Orodreth has ordered the construction of a large bridge spanning the river Narog. With this in place, the armies of Nargothrond now freely make war against the Orcs of Morgoth, drawing the enemies attention to this one spot in Beleriand...</p><p class='main-text'>Skip the quest and combat phase this round.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player may search the top 15 cards of their deck for one Weapon or Armor attachment and one ally. These cards may be immediately played for no cost. Add Mighty Bridge to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round, advance to stage 3A.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Doors-of-Felagund-TFoN", "<p class='flavor-text'>Five years have passed since you came to Nargothrond. In that time, small victories against the forces of Morgoth have been won. However, as the year turns to autumn, reports of a great host reach your ears.<br>Morgoth has finally loosed the army he has long prepared. At the head of this army is Glaurung, the Father of Dragons. The warriors of Nargothrond are valiant, but they are vastly outnumbered. The proud Elven host begins to fall back upon the field of Tumhalad. Even worse, Glaurung is a fearsome force of death, beyond terror and beyond comprehension. None can withstand his approach. You must defend the Doors of Felagund to buy time for the innocent to escape.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The first player adds Glaurung The Hopes of Nargothrond and The Ruin of Nargothrond to the staging area. Each other player searches the encounter deck and discard pile for a copy of Great Host and adds it to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Doors-of-Felagund-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>when resolving the raid keyword, divide the enemy's{Threat} in half (rounding up).</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round, add 1 damage to this stage (add 2 damage instead if there are more non-unique enemies in play than the number of players). If the number of damage tokens is equal to or greater than 5, advance to stage 4A.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round, if there are fewer non-unique enemies in play than the number of players, search the encounter deck and discard pile for 1 enemy and add it to the staging area, if able.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Sack-of-Nargothrond-TFoN", "<p class='flavor-text'>The Doors of Felagund have falles, and the host of Morgoth has begun pouring into Nargothrond. As the great halls and chambers are ransacked, you see Orcs herding those maidens and children that have survived into a crowd. They are destined to be slaves enduring unbearable torment in Angband unless you can rescue them from their fate.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Return Glaurung to the staging area if he is engaged with a player. Glaurung makes an immediate attack against each playe, in turn order (do not deal a shadow card or trigger the forced effect on Glaurung for this attack).</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Sack-of-Nargothrond-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>Glaurung cannot leave the staging area and is considered to be engaged with each player.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round, add 1 damage to this stage (add 2 damage instead if there are more non-unique enemies in the staging area than the number of players). If the number of damage tokens is equal to or greater than 6, the players lose.</p><p class='main-text'>If the players complete the victory condition on The Hopes of Nargothrond they win.</p>");
            AddHtml("Great-Host-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Raid.}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Great Host engages a player, exhaust the ready character they control with the highest{Defense}</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The defending player exhausts a character they control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Mighty-Bridge-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. The players cannot travel to Mighty Bridge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After an enemy engages a player, that enemy gets +1 {Attack} and +1 {Defense} until the end of the round.</p><p class='flavor-text'>...for it was great and mightily made and could not swiftly be destroyed, and thus the enemy came readily over the deep river...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Field-of-Tumhalad-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>While Field of Tumhalad is in the staging area, each enemy gets +1 {Threat}</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The attacking enemy gets +X{Attack} where X is equal to its{Threat}</p><p class='flavor-text'>The Elves were driven back and defeated on the field of Tumhalad; and there all the pride and host of Nargothrond withered away.<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Ruin-of-Nargothrond-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After one or more cards with an (Innocent) icon are discarded by the raid keyword on an enemy, reveal the top card of the innocent deck and attach it to that enemy as a guarded objective.</p><p class='main-text'>If there are 6 or more Innocent objectives under The Ruin of Nargothrond the players lose the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Deep-River-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. The players cannot travel to Deep River.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When any number of damage tokens would be placed on the quest stage, cancel that damage and remove Deep River from the game instead.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The doors of Nargothrond opened onto the gorge of the river...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Hopes-of-Nargothrond-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Remove 10 progress from the main quest to reveal the top card of the innocent deck and place it beneath The Hopes of Nargothrond. Any player may trigger this effect.</p><p class='main-text'>If there are 6 or more Innocent objective under The Hopes of Nargothrond the players win the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Retreating-Soldiers-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Retreating Soldiers is explored as the active location, the first player takes control of this card as an ally with 1{Willpower} 3{Attack} 3{Defense} and 3 hit points.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Then Túrin sped back to Nargothrond, mustering such of the rout as he met with on the way...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Unmanned-Ballista-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Unmanned Ballista is explored as the active location, attach it to a hero controlled by the first player. While attached to a hero, Unmanned Ballista gains: &quot;Combat<b>Action:</b> Exhaust Unmanned Ballista and attached hero to deal 2 damage to an enemy in play.&quot;</p>");
            AddHtml("Leaderless-Archers-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Leaderless Archers is explored as the active location, ignore the raid keyword on enemies until the end of the round.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The defending player may spend 2{sphere:Tactics} resources to deal 2 damage to the attacking enemy.</p>");
            AddHtml("Besieged-Defenses-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Besieged Defenses is explored as the active location, each character gets +2 {Defense} until the end of the round.</p><p class='flavor-text'>...and they were even then ransacking the great halls and chambers, plundering and destroying...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Not-All-Can-Fight-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>Doomed 2.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Either deal 1 damage to each Innocent objective in play or deal 1 damage to each character in play.</p><p class='main-text'>(Innocent)</p>");
            AddHtml("Your-Shadow-Lies-Upon-Them-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must deal 1 Corruption to a character they control. Then, each palyer must assign X Corruption among characters they control, where X is the number of corruption tokens they control with the most Corruption.</p><p class='main-text'>(Innocent)</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The defending player must either deal 1 Corruption to the defending character or reveal the top card of the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Hate-of-Morgoth-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>Doomed 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player exhaust a character and discards the top card of the encounter deck. If the{Threat} of the discarded card is greater than the{Willpower} of the exhausted character, that character becomes immediately corrupted.</p><p class='main-text'>(Innocent)</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The defending character must either take 1 Corruption or take 1 damage.</p>");
            AddHtml("Driven-Back-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The first player discards cards from the top of the encounter deck until an enemy is discarded, and adds that enemy to the staging area. Then, the players must remove X characters from the quest, where X is the number of enemies in the staging area.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} If this attack destroys a character, remove 5 progress from the quest.</p>");
            AddHtml("Mustered-Strength-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Discard cards from the top of the encounter deck until an enemy is discarded. Put the discarded enemy into play engaged with the last player and attach Mustered Strength to it. Mustered Strength gains,<b>&quot;Forced:</b> When a character is declared as an attacker against this enemy, deal 1 damage to that character.&quot;</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> The attacking enemy makes an additional attack after this one.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dreadful-Spell-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach Dreadful Spell to a hero controlled by the defending player. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text: &quot;The attached character cannot ready. At the end of the round, discard the top card of the encounter. If the{Threat} of the discarded card is lower than the attached character's{Willpower} discard Dreadful Spell.&quot;)</p><p class='flavor-text'>...he was yet held by the eyes of Glaurung in torment of mind...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Full-Fire-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Deal 1 damage to each ally controlled by the defending playuer. The defending player may exhaust a character to cancel the damage dealt to that character.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Fell-Voice-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Randomly select 1 ally controlled by the defending player, if able. Discard the top card of the encounter deck. If the{Threat} of the discarded card is greater than the{Willpower} of the selected ally, that ally is immediately corrupted. If no ally is selected by this effect, Fell Voice gains doomed 3.</p><p class='flavor-text'>And Túrin being under the spell of Glaurung hearkened to his words, and he saw himself as in a mirror reshaped by malice...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Coiling-Swiftly-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Glaurung gets +2 {Defense} until the end of the phase.</p><p class='flavor-text'>But Túrin drawing back his sword stabbed at his eyes, and Glaurung coiling back swiftly toward above him...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Maiden-of-Nargothrond-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the refresh phase, place a damage token on Maiden of Nargothrond if she is attached to an enemy. If Maiden of Nargothrond is destroyed, place her under The Ruin of Nargothrond.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Maiden of Nargothrond is free of encounters, place it under The Hopes of Nargothrond.</p>");
            AddHtml("Finduilas-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the refresh phase, place a damage token on Finduilas if she is attached to an enemy. If Finduilas is destroyed, place her under The Ruin of Nargothrond and place 1 Corruption on each hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Finduilas is free of encounters, place her under The Hopes of Nargothrond.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dark-Doom-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>Fate -1. Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The first player must either deal X Corruption among heroes they control or deal X damage among heroes they control (X is the number of damage tokens on Doom Mastered).</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Resolve the keywords on this card.</p>");
            AddHtml("Fateful-Words-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>Fate -1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach this card to the hero with the highest threat cost. (Counts as a Condition attachment with the text:<b>&quot;Forced:</b> After a character is destroyed, deal 1 Corruption to the attached hero.&quot;)</p><p class='flavor-text'>&quot;Evil have been all you ways, son of Húrin<br>&ndash;Glaurung, The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Doom-Mastered-Objective-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>At the end of the game, record the number of damage or progress tokens on Doom Mastered in the campaign log.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Place the number of damage or progress tokens on Doom Mastered equal to the total listed in the campaign log from the previous quest.</p><p class='flavor-text'>A Túrin Turambar...<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml("Finarfin-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'>While Finarfin is defending, he gains:<b>&quot;Response:</b> Cancel a shadow effect just triggered. Then, cancel all damage dealt to the attacking enemy until the end of the round. (Limit once per round.)&quot;</p><p class='flavor-text'>But Finarfin spoke softly, as was his wont, and sought to calm the Noldor, persuading them to pause and ponder ere deeds were done that could not be undone...<br>&ndash;The Silmarillion</p>");
            AddHtml("Guard-of-the-Druedain-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After an enemy engages you, exhaust Guard of the Drúedain to lower that enemy's{Attack} by 1 until the end of the phase (lower its{Attack} by 2 instead if the attacking enemy is an Orc.) The targeted enemy cannot be targeted again by the ability of a Guard of the Drúedain this round.</p><p class='flavor-text'>...nothing passed or came near that was not marked and remembered.<br>&ndash;Unfinished Tales</p>");
            AddHtml("Shieldmaiden-of-Haleth-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Shieldmaiden of Haleth quests successfully, place 1 resource token on it.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a hero is damaged by an enemy attack, exhaust Shieldmaiden of Haleth and remove 3 progress tokens from it to cancel all damage from that attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Noldor-Oathkeeper-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>If each hero you control has at least 1 Corruption Noldor Oathkeeper does not exhaust to defend.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> When you play Noldor Oathkeeper from your hand, place 1 Corruption on a hero you control to reduce its cost by 1.</p>");
            AddHtml("Amon-Ethir-Sentry-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Amon Ethir Sentry enters play, choose an enemy in the staging area. Then, you may either engage that enemy or that enemy does not make engagement checks until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Andvir-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>Ransom 3.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a treachery is revealed, exhaust Andvír to choose an ally. That ally readies and gets +1 {Willpower} until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Gilded-Mask-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero. Restricted.</p><p class='main-text'>While the attached hero is committed to the quest, Gilded Mask gains,<b>&quot;Response:</b> When an enemy with lower{Threat} than the number of Corruption tokens on the attached hero is revealed from the encounter deck, exhaust Gilded Mask to discard that enemy (canceling all of its effects). Reveal the next card of the encounter deck instead.&quot;</p>");
            AddHtml("Hidden-Way-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a location.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After attached location is explored, reduce the first player's threat by X, where X is the attached location's printed quest points (up to a limit of 5.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Seal-of-the-Queen-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gets +1 {Willpower}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust Seal of the Queen and name a number to search the top 3 cards of your deck. You may choose one of those cards with cost equal to the named number and add it to your hand. Shuffle the rest back into your deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Unnumbered-Tears-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a character is destroyed, ready each character you control that shares a trait with that character.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Then in the plain of...<br>&ndash;The Simlarillion</p>");
            AddHtml("Friend-of-Birds-and-Beasts-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Place the top 3 cards of the encounter deck facedown under this card. Each facedown card acts as an ally with 1{Willpower} 1{Attack} 1{Defense} 1 hit point, and the Creature trait. Discard this card and call facedown cards underneath it at the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Kingly-Judgement-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Choose a character with at least 1 Corruption and choose one: deal 1 damage to that character to remove 1 Corruption from that character to play an attachment of X cost or lower on that character for free, where X is the number of Corruption tokens on that character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Silmaril-of-the-Sky-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero with at least 1 Corruption. Limit 1 per deck.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust Silmaril of the Sky and deal 1 Corruption to a character you control to (choose 1): discard a shadow card from a non-unique enemy, choose an enemy to get -2{Attack} until the end of the phase, or ready attached hero.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Fall-of-Nargothrond-Campaign-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>You are playing Campaign mode.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Shuffle Fateful Woords and Dark Doom into the encounter deck. Add Doom Mastered to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Finduilas is placed beneath The Hopes of Nargothrond the players gain 1 fate.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Remove X damage from Glaurung to gain 1 fate for the players. X is equal to 5 times the number of players. Any player may trigger this action.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&quot;In the autumn of the year, biding his hour, Morgoth loosed upon the people of Narog the great host that he had long prepared...&quot;<br>&ndash;The Children of Húrin</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Fall-of-Nargothrond-Campaign-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Resolution:</b> Follow the instructions on Doom Mastered and record the number of damage or progress tokens on that card. If at least 1 damage is recorded, then add Dark Doom to the the campaign pool. If at least 2 damage is recorded, then add both Dark Doom and Fateful Words to the campaign pool.</p>");
            AddHtml("A-Grave-Wound-TFoN", "<p class='flavor-text'>One of your allies has been laid low upon the battlefield. You must decide whether to tend to their wounds or continue to rescue the innocents of Nargothrond.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The first player loses control of their highest cost ally and places it underneath this stage. That ally has been &quot;wounded.&quot; When this stage is defeated, the first player takes control of the &quot;wounded&quot; ally. If no allies are placed underneath this card by this effect, discard A Grave Wound and it gains surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round, deal 1 damage to the &quot;wounded&quot; ally. If that ally leaves play, discard a Grave Wound.</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Child-of-Nargothrond-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the refresh phase, place a damage token on Child of Nargothrond if he is attached to an enemy. If Child of Nargothrond is destroyed, place him under The Ruin of Nargothrond.</p>");
            AddHtml("Favor-of-Indis-TFoN", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a House of Fingolfin or House of Finarfin hero. Limit 1 per hero.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gains +1 {Defense} for each resource on Favor of Indis.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> At the end of the combat phase, add 1 resource to Favor of Indis if you are engaged with an enemy and did not destroy an enemy this phase. (Limit 3 resources on Favor of Indis.)</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After you destroy an enemy, remove 1 resource from Favor of Indis.</p>");
        }

        private void ChildrenOfEorl()
        {
            AddHtml("A-History-of-Strife-CoE", "<p class='flavor-text'>The Dunlendings bear an ancient grudge against outsiders. They seek to catch you unawares, plundering your supplies before leaving you for dead.</p><p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'>Each <b><i>Dunland</i></b> enemy gains “<b>Forced:</b> After this enemy engages you, discard a resource from a hero you control.”</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Abandoned-Mill-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Doomed 1. Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Abandoned Mill leaves play as an explored location, discard cards from the encounter deck until an enemy is discarded. Add that enemy to the staging area.</p><p class='flavor-text'>You’ve got to have grist before you can grind; and there was no more. —The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Ambush-CoE", "<p class='flavor-text'>You have battled into the heart of the encampment, but the brigands rally about their leader and launch a vicious attack.</p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed:</b> End the current phase. Add Brigand Ringleader to the staging area. Each player not engaged with an enemy searches the encounter deck and discard pile for an enemy to put into play and engages it. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Ambush-CoE", "<p class='main-text'> <b>Forced:</b> After an enemy enters play, it makes engagement checks.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Planning Action:</b> Remove 5 progress from this stage to choose a card in a loot pile. The owner of that card may either discard it or play it for no cost. Limit four times per round for the group.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Brigand Ringleader is defeated, the players win the game.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Another-Wave-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Surge. Doomed 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> If the players control the beacon, either deal 2 damage to Erelas Beacon or reveal an encounter card.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Either the attacking enemy makes an additional attack or deal 1 damage to Erelas Beacon.</p>");
            AddHtml("Assault-Upon-Erelas-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The first player chooses an enemy engaged with a player and returns it to the staging area. If no enemy was returned to the staging area this way, either deal 1 damage to Erelas Beacon or Assault Upon Erelas gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Either raise your threat by 4 or deal 1 damage to Erelas Beacon.</p>");
            AddHtml("Bald-Hill-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>While the players control the beacon, Bald Hill gets +3 {Threat}.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> If the players control the beacon, deal 2 damage to Erelas Beacon.</p><p class='flavor-text'>At last they reached the crest of the grey hill, and a sudden breeze blew in their hair and stirred their cloaks: the chill wind of dawn. —The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Battle-for-the-Hill-CoE", "<p class='flavor-text'>Dunlendings and traitorous Rohirrim have captured the beacon at Erelas. Reclaim the hill at any cost!</p><p class='main-text'> <b>Setup:</b> Set Host of Rohan aside, out of play. Add Erelas Beacon and 1{PerPlayer} Enraged Dunlendings to the staging area. Add the double-sided side quest to the staging area, Reclaim the Beacon side faceup. Search the encounter deck for 1 copy of Surrounding Grassland and make it the active location. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Battle-for-the-Hill-CoE", "<p class='main-text'> <b>Forced:</b> After placing any amount of progress on this stage, each player must choose: either exhaust a character you control or deal 1 damage to Erelas Beacon.</p><p class='main-text'><b>This stage cannot be completed while the Dunlendings control the beacon.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Black-Land-Scouts-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of the combat phase, either raise each player’s threat by 1 or deal 4 damage among characters in play.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Deal 2 damage among characters you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Bridle-biter-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Bridle-biter engages the player who controls the most <b><i>Mount</i></b> objectives.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Put Bridle-biter into play engaged with you and deal it a shadow card.</p>");
            AddHtml("Brigand-Ringleader-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Looter 3. Immune to player card effects. Cannot take more than 5 damage each round.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round, the engaged player adds the top card of their deck to Brigand Ringleader’s loot pile and heals 1 damage from Brigand Ringleader for each different card cost in its loot pile.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Brightmane-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Guarded (location). Restricted.</p><p class='main-text'>The location or enemy guarding Brightmane gets +1 {Threat}.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gets +1 {Willpower}.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Quest Action:</b> Exhaust Brightmane to look at the top card of the encounter deck. If it is a location, you may discard it.</p>");
            AddHtml("Celador-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Ranged.</p><p class='main-text'>Reduce the total {Threat} in the staging area by 1 for each unattached <b><i>Trap</i></b> you control.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a <b><i>Trap</i></b> card you control is attached to an enemy, either ready Celador or reduce your threat by 1.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Wise man trusts not to chance-meeting on the road in this land.”<br/>—Faramir, The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Chaos-in-the-Hills-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Return the engaged enemy with the highest engagement cost to the staging area. If no enemy was returned to the staging area this way, Chaos in the Hills gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> After this attack, attacking enemy engages the next player and makes an immediate attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Cold-from-the-Mountains-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player that controls more than 2 allies must discard an ally they control (discard 2 instead if they control more than 5).</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Exhaust a character you control.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Let those call it the wind who will.”<br/>—Boromir, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Crimson-Banner-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'>While attached to an enemy, counts as a <b><i><b><i>Condition</i></b></i></b> attachment with the text: “<b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round, each player raises their threat by 1 for each <b><i>Orc</i></b> enemy in play.”</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach to the non-unique <b><i>Orc</i></b> enemy with the highest engagement cost.</p>");
            AddHtml("Crossroads-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Shuffle the encounter discard pile into the encounter deck and discard cards until an enemy is discarded. Put that enemy into play engaged with the first player.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +X {Attack}, where X is the number of different spheres among cards in its loot pile.</p>");
            AddHtml("Deadly-Defector-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the combat phase, if Deadly Defector is in the staging area, it makes an immediate attack against the last player.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If attacking enemy is in the staging area, it makes an additional attack after this one.</p>");
            AddHtml("Deeping-Bowman-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Devoted. Ranged.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Discard Deeping Bowman to choose an enemy. Until the end of the phase, that enemy does not count its {Defense} while determining combat damage.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“We loosed every arrow that we had, and filled the Dike with Orcs.” —The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Deeping-Defender-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Devoted.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Deeping Defender defends an attack, return the attacking enemy to the staging area and deal 1 damage to it.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The sunset gilded their spears and helmets, and glinted in their pale flowing hair. —The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Drive-them-Away-CoE", "<p class='flavor-text'>Along the Great West Road, you come upon a Rohirrim camp in the shadow of the green, bald beacon hill of Erelas. But the quiet of your journey is interrupted by a sudden attack from the shadows! The clash of steel and the cries of men soon reach your ears. You must drive them away and free the camp from further destruction!</p><p class='main-text'> <b>Setup:</b> Set Brigand Ringleader aside, out of play. Add Plundered Goods to the staging area. Each player searches the encounter deck for a different enemy and adds it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Drive-them-Away-CoE", "<p class='main-text'> <b>Forced:</b> After an enemy is destroyed, place 1 resource token here.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Encounter Action:</b> Remove 5 progress from this stage to choose a card in a loot pile and discard it. Limit once per round per player.</p><p class='main-text'><b>The players cannot advance unless there are X resource tokens on this stage, where X is equal to 1, plus 2{PerPlayer} (2 per player).</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Dunland-Chieftain-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Dunland Chieftain engages you, discard 1 random card from your hand. Then, discard each other copy of that card that is in your hand or under your control.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“They hate us, and they are glad.”<br/>—Gamling, The Two Towers</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Dunlending-Berserker-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Dunlending Berserker engages you, deal 1 damage to a hero you control and 1 damage to a non-unique enemy engaged with you.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“They will not give way now for dusk or dawn.”<br/>—Gamling, The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Endless-Grasslands-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Vast.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the travel phase, if the active location is not vast, each player exhausts an ally they control.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If the active location is vast, the attacking enemy makes an additional attack after this one.</p>");
            AddHtml("Enraged-Dunlending-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Enraged Dunlending engages you, deal 1 damage to Erelas Beacon.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Any damage dealt to the defending character by this attack is instead dealt to Erelas Beacon.</p>");
            AddHtml("Erelas-Beacon-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the combat phase, deal 1 damage to Erelas Beacon for each enemy in the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Erelas Beacon has X hit points, where X is equal to 2, plus 3{PerPlayer}. If Erelas Beacon has no hit points remaining, the players lose the game.</b></p><p class='flavor-text'>All the lands were grey and still; and ever the shadow deepened before them, and hope waned in every heart.<br/>—The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Erelas-Gates-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Each player must choose an enemy and add the top card of their deck to that enemy’s loot pile.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Raise your threat by 1 for each card in the attacking enemy’s loot pile.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Twisted and leaning pillars reared their splintered stems.<br/>—The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Erelas-Stables-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Return an enemy engaged with a player to the staging area.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If attacking enemy is non-unique, return it to the staging area after this attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Exhausting-Winds-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Deal 1 damage to each character with more than 1 remaining hit point. Exhaust each character not damaged this way.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> After this attack, deal X damage to the defending character. X is 1 less than the character’s remaining hit points.</p>");
            AddHtml("Exposed-to-the-Elements-CoE", "<p class='flavor-text'>Your party finds itself at the mercy of rain, sleet, and hunger. You must seek shelter to find even the barest hint of respite.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the staging step, discard cards from the encounter deck until a treachery card is discarded. Reveal that card.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Feast-of-Plenty-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Feast of Plenty’s resource cost must be paid from a single hero’s resource pool.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Ready up to 3 heroes and add 1 resource to each of their resource pools. Only 1 copy of Feast of Plenty can be played by the players each round.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The feast was merry and the food all that his hunger could desire. —The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Felarof-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Guarded (enemy). Restricted.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When the enemy guarding Felaróf attacks, deal it 2 additional shadow cards.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Combat Action:</b> Exhaust Felaróf to discard a facedown shadow card from play.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“There is another that strides ahead: a very great horse. I have not seen his like before.”<br/>—Legolas, The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Flinthoof-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Guarded (enemy). Restricted.</p><p class='main-text'>The enemy guarding Flinthoof gets +1 {Attack}.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gets +1 {Attack}.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Combat Action:</b> Exhaust Flinthoof to deal 1 damage to an enemy in play.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Their long tails flowed in the wind, their manes were braided on their proud necks.<br/>—The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("From-All-Sides-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must choose: either deal 1 damage to 4 different characters you control or deal 1 damage to Erelas Beacon.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> After this attack, either discard the defending character or deal 1 damage to Erelas Beacon.</p>");
            AddHtml("Grasping-Slaver-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Looter 2.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After an ally is damaged or destroyed by Grasping Slaver’s attack, add that ally to Grasping Slaver’s loot pile.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Grasping Slaver attacks, deal X damage among characters you control. X is the number of ally cards in Grasping Slaver’s loot pile.</p>");
            AddHtml("Herubrand-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Herubrand gets +1 {Willpower} for each hero you control with at least 1 restricted attachment.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After an enemy in the staging area is destroyed, draw 1 card.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“What burden do you bear, Men of Rohan?”<br/>—Imrahil, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Hillman-Scout-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Archery 2.}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Hillman Scout engages you, exhaust the ready ally you control with the highest printed cost.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Exhaust a character you control with 3 or more {Attack}.</p>");
            AddHtml("Hold-the-Hilltop-CoE", "<p class='flavor-text'>As your foes gather for another assault on the beacon, you can spot the torchlights of Gálmód’s troops massing amid the hills below.</p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed:</b> Place progress on Defend the Beacon (bypassing the active location) until it has X progress on it, where X is equal to 2, plus 1{PerPlayer}. Shuffle the encounter discard pile into the encounter deck. Each player discards cards from the top of the encounter deck until an enemy is discarded and adds that enemy to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Hold-the-Hilltop-CoE", "<p class='main-text'> Time 3.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round, deal 1 damage to Erelas Beacon (2 damage instead if there are 3 or more players in the game). Then, if there are no time counters on this stage, immediately advance to stage 3.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Defend the Beacon is chosen as the current quest, reveal an encounter card.</p><p class='main-text'><b>If the Dunlendings control the beacon, the players lose the game.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Horse-Lord's-Lodge-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>When faced with the option to travel, the players must travel to a non-vast location.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Horse Lord’s Lodge leaves play as an explored location, if there are fewer than 1{PerPlayer} locations in play, discard cards from the top of the encounter deck until a location is discarded. Add that location to the staging area.</p>{victory:2}");
            AddHtml("Horse-Thieves'-Hovel-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>When faced with the option to travel, the players must travel to a non-vast location.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Horse Thieves’ Hovel leaves play as an explored location, if there are fewer than 1{PerPlayer} enemies in play, discard cards from the top of the encounter deck until an enemy is discarded. Add that enemy to the staging area.</p>{victory:2}");
            AddHtml("Host-of-Rohan-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> The players as a group may spend 2 resources to ready Host of Rohan. (Limit once per phase.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>“War is abroad, and the Rohirrim, the Horse-lords, do not sleep.”<br/>—Gandalf, The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Humpbacked-Downs-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Vast.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the travel phase, if the active location is not vast, each player raises their threat by 1.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If the active location is vast, raise your threat by 2.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ingold-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a <b><i>Gondor</i></b> or <b><i>Warrior</i></b> ally enters play under your control, draw 1 card. Then, either spend 1 resource from Ingold’s pool or raise your threat by 1. (Limit once per phase.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>“We wish for no strangers in the land at this time, unless they be mighty men of arms in whose faith and help we can trust.” —The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("It-Should-Be-Spared-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a <b><i>Trap</i></b> card you control attaches to an enemy, return it to your hand. Then, play it from your hand for no cost.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“But I do not slay man or beast needlessly, and not gladly even when it is needed.”<br/>—Faramir, The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Light-footed-Steed-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a <b><i>Rohan</i></b> hero. Restricted.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a character you control leaves play, exhaust Light-footed Steed to ready attached hero. Then, if the character that left play was unique, attached hero gets +1 {Attack} until the end of the round.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“…and don’t forget their horses! They can see the night-breeze, or so it’s said.” —Ugluk, The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Live-Bait-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Play only if you control an unattached <b><i>Trap</i></b> attachment.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Choose a non-unique enemy in play. Until the end of the round, treat the chosen enemy’s printed text box as if it were blank (except for <b><i>Traits</i></b>). Then, attach an unattached <b><i>Trap</i></b> attachment you control to that enemy.</p>");
            AddHtml("Looted-Weapons-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>While attached to an enemy, counts as a <b><i><b><i>Condition</i></b></i></b> attachment with the text: “Attached enemy gets +1 {Threat} and +1 {Attack} for each attachment in its loot pile.”</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach to the enemy in play with the highest engagement cost. Then, each player adds an <b><i>Item</i></b> attachment they control to that enemy’s loot pile, if able. If there are no enemies in play, Looted Weapons gains surge.</p>");
            AddHtml("Morwen-Steelsheen-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Put Morwen Steelsheen into play from your hand. Then, discard a <b><i>Rohan</i></b> or <b><i>Gondor</i></b> ally you control.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a <b><i>Rohan</i></b> or <b><i>Gondor</i></b> ally leaves play, exhaust Morwen Steelsheen to either heal 2 damage from a character or reduce your threat by 1.</p>");
            AddHtml("Narrow-Stair-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Each player cannot declare more than 1 attack and cannot declare more than 1 attacker each phase.</p><p class='main-text'>While Narrow Stair is the active location, each player cannot defend more than 1 attack each phase (other attacks are undefended).</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Either attacking enemy gets +3 {Attack} or deal 1 damage to Erelas Beacon.</p>");
            AddHtml("Need-Brooks-No-Delay-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Reduce the cost to play Need Brooks No Delay by 1 for each <b><i>Rohan</i></b> hero you control.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Planning Action:</b> Search the top 10 cards of your deck for a card with printed cost 2 or less (3 or less if it is unique) and set it aside. Shuffle your deck. Then, play the set aside card for no cost as if it were in your hand.</p>");
            AddHtml("Old-Farmhouse-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Old Farmhouse leaves play as an explored location, discard cards from the encounter deck until a location is discarded. Add that location to the staging area.</p><p class='flavor-text'>About a furlong from the main road, they met a stout barrier of old farm-carts upturned. That halted them.<br/>—The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Open-the-Gates-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Search the top 5 cards of your deck for an ally that shares a <b><i>Trait</i></b> with each of your heroes and put it into play. Shuffle your deck. At the end of the phase, if that ally did not leave play, add it to your hand.</p><p class='flavor-text'>It seemed that word of their coming had gone before them; and at once they were admitted, silently, and without question. —The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Orc-Battalion-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Orc Battalion cannot take combat damage while being attacked by fewer than 3 characters.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After a character is declared as an attacker against Orc Batallion, deal 1 damage to that character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Orcish-Horse-butcher-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Orcish Horse-butcher deals damage to a character, either discard an attachment from that character or raise the engaged player’s threat by 1.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Either discard an attachment you control or raise your threat by 3.</p>");
            AddHtml("Overburdened-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player who controls more than 2 attachments must discard 1 attachment they control, if able (discard 2 attachments instead, if able, if they control more than 5 attachments). If no attachments were discarded this way, Overburdened gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Discard 1 random card from your hand.</p>");
            AddHtml("Pillaging-Swordsman-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Looter 1.</p><p class='main-text'>Pillaging Swordsman gets +X {Attack}, where X is the highest printed cost among cards in its loot pile.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Add the top 2 cards of your deck to the attacking enemy’s loot pile.</p>");
            AddHtml("Plundered-Goods-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Add 1 to the total {Threat} in the staging area for each card in Plundered Goods’ loot pile.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When an enemy leaves play, add 1 card from its loot pile to Plundered Goods’ loot pile, then add another card from its loot pile to its owner’s hand. Discard the rest.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The brigands raided the village stockpile of spear and shield, and turned the weapons on the villagers.</p>");
            AddHtml("Pommel-pouncer-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>While Pommel-pouncer is in the staging area without a <b><i>Mount</i></b> objective attached, it gains: “<b>Forced:</b> When a player would gain control of a <b><i>Mount</i></b> objective, attach that <b><i>Mount</i></b> objective to Pommel-pouncer as a guarded objective instead.”</p>");
            AddHtml("Rammas-Lookout-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Devoted.</p><p class='main-text'>While each hero you control has at least 1 resource in its resource pool, Rammas Lookout gets +1 {Willpower} and does not exhaust to quest.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Whatever betide, you have come to the end of the Gondor that you have known. Let me pass!”<br/>—Gandalf, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Rammas-Sentry-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Devoted.</p><p class='main-text'>While each hero you control has at least 1 resource in its resource pool, Rammas Sentry gains: “<b>Response:</b> Cancel 1 point of damage just dealt to a <b><i>Gondor</i></b> character. (Limit once per phase.)”</p><p class='flavor-text'>“For if we fall, who shall stand?”<br/>—Beregond, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Reclaim-the-Beacon-CoE", "<p class='flavor-text'>Seize the beacon, lest the Dunlendings deface it, or worse.</p><p class='main-text'>The Dunlendings control the beacon. Enemies in the staging area cannot be optionally engaged or take damage.</p><p class='main-text'>Cannot have more than X progress, where X is equal to 2, plus 1{PerPlayer}. If Reclaim the Beacon has X progress on it, flip it over (keeping all progress).</p>");
            AddHtml("Recreant-Rider-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Recreant Rider enters the staging area, it makes an immediate attack against the first player.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Return attacking enemy to the staging area after this attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Rein-ripper-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Rein-ripper attacks, deal it two additional shadow cards. You may attach a <b><i>Mount</i></b> objective you control to Rein-ripper as a guarded objective to cancel this effect.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} for each <b><i>Mount</i></b> objective the players control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ride-Through-the-Night-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Exhaust all restricted attachments the players control. If no restricted attachments were exhausted this way, Ride Through the Night gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If the active location is vast, the defending character cannot ready until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Rocky-Slope-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>After an encounter card effect is canceled, deal 1 damage to Erelas Beacon.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> The first player must discard all event cards from their hand.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Either discard all resources from each hero you control or deal 1 damage to Erelas Beacon.</p>");
            AddHtml("Saddle-slasher-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Archery X. X is equal to 2, plus 1 for each <b><i>Mount</i></b> objective the players control.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If you control a <b><i>Mount</i></b> objective, either attach it to the attacking enemy as a guarded objective or discard the defending character after this attack resolves.</p>");
            AddHtml("Servant-of-the-Eye-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Doomed 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Servant of the Eye attacks you, raise your threat by 1.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Raise your threat by 2.</p>");
            AddHtml("Sneaky-Thief-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Looter 0. Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When Sneaky Thief would take any amount of damage, if it has any cards in its loot pile, discard each of those cards instead.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack destroys a character, attacking enemy makes an additional attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Spoiled-Pasture-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>X is equal to 2, plus 2 for each <b><i>Mount</i></b> objective the players control.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After a player loses control of a <b><i>Mount</i></b> objective, raise their threat by 1.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Raise your threat by 1 for each <b><i>Mount</i></b> objective you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Spring-the-Trap-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a <b><i>Trap</i></b> card you control attaches to an enemy, put a <b><i>Ranger</i></b> ally into play from your hand.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“The road may pass, but they shall not! Not while Faramir is Captain.” —Mablung, The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Squire-of-the-Mark-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a <b><i>Rohan</i></b> ally you control is discarded from play, add Squire of the Mark to the victory display to put that ally into play exhausted.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Little service can I offer to your lord, but what I can do, I would do.” —Pippin, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Stockpile-Barricade-CoE", "<p class='flavor-text'>Upturned wagons and carts formed a stiff barricade across the road.</p><p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'>Each enemy gets +1 {Defense} for each attachment in its loot pile.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After resolving the Looter keyword on an enemy, if there are no attachments in that enemy’s loot pile, it makes an immediate attack against the engaged player.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Stolen-Steeds-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b><i>Mount</i></b> objectives cannot be discarded or leave play. If a <b><i>Mount</i></b> objective is not attached, a player must claim it and attach it to a hero they control.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round, add 1 progress to the main quest for each <b><i>Mount</i></b> objective the players control. Then, raise each player’s threat by 1 for each <b><i>Mount</i></b> objective in play the players do not control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Surprise-Attack-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The next enemy engaged this round cannot take damage until the end of the round and returns to the staging area after it attacks this round.</p><p class='flavor-text'>He was cut off by the others that had lain in ambush. He could see them clearly now.<br/>—The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Surrounding-Grassland-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Archery 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After Surrounding Grassland leaves play as an explored location, if there are no copies of Surrounding Grassland in the staging area, return this location to the staging area.</p><p class='flavor-text'>They could see beyond the stream the green fields of Rohan fading into distant grey.<br/>—The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Green-Sea-CoE", "<p class='flavor-text'>The hinterlands are broad and endless, exhausting even the most stalwart horses of the Westfold.</p><p class='main-text'>Vast locations get +3 quest points and are immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of the travel phase, if there are no vast locations in the staging area, discard cards from the top of the encounter deck until a vast location is discarded and add it to the staging area.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("The-King's-Stallion-CoE", "<p class='flavor-text'>The warchief Thruk has arrived at the battle, riding the mighty horse Felaróf and bellowing orders at his hordelings. “Rally!” he cries. “Tonight we feast on horse-flesh!”</p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed:</b> If it is the combat phase, end the phase. Shuffle the encounter discard pile into the encounter deck. The first player adds Thruk to the staging area, guarding Felaróf. Each other player discards cards from the encounter deck until an enemy is discarded and puts that enemy into play engaged with them.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-King's-Stallion-CoE", "<p class='main-text'> Thruk cannot take damage unless there are at least 4 progress tokens on this stage.</p><p class='main-text'><b>This stage cannot be defeated unless the players control 3 <b><i>Mount</i></b> objectives.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("The-Last-Alliance-CoE", "<p class='main-text'> Choose two traits, <b><i>A</i></b> and <b><i>B</i></b>. Each of your starting heroes and each ally in your deck must have either the printed <b><i>A</i></b> or <b><i>B</i></b> trait, but cannot have both. You must have at least 1 starting hero and 10 allies in your deck with each trait.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Flip this card over.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“The strength of the Elves to resist him was greater long ago; and not all Men were estranged from them.”<br/>—Gandalf, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Last-Alliance-CoE", "<p class='main-text'> While you control more <b><i>A</i></b> characters than <b><i>B</i></b> characters, reduce the cost of the first <b><i>B</i></b> ally you play this round by 1, and vice versa.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust The Last Alliance to choose a card in your hand or a card in play under your control. Replace each printed instance of “<b><i>A</i></b>” or “<b><i>B</i></b>” in that card’s ability text with “<b><i>A</i></b> or <b><i>B</i></b>” until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Last-Push-CoE", "<p class='flavor-text'>As Gálmód’s forces ride to flank the enemy, you must steel yourselves for one final melee.</p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed:</b> Remove all progress from Defend the Beacon and flip it over. Put Host of Rohan into play under the first player’s control. Shuffle the encounter discard pile into the encounter deck. Each player discards cards from the encounter deck until an enemy is discarded and adds that enemy to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Last-Push-CoE", "<p class='main-text'> Add 2 to the total {Threat} in the staging area for each damage on Erelas Beacon.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of the combat phase, each engaged enemy makes an immediate attack.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After a character leaves play, deal 1 damage to Erelas Beacon.</p><p class='main-text'><b>At the end of the round, if the Dunlendings control the beacon, the players lose the game, and if the players control the beacon, they win the game.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("The-Sweeping-Tide-CoE", "<p class='flavor-text'>The full might of the Orc-host has answered Thruk’s rallying cry. You must unite yourselves for a final charge to scatter them into the hills.</p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed:</b> If it is the combat phase, end the phase. Shuffle the encounter discard pile into the encounter deck. Search the victory display for Thruk and add him to the staging area. Each player chooses 2 enemies from the set-aside Orc-host encounter cards and puts those enemies into play engaged with them. One of the enemies put into play this way must be Orc Battalion.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Sweeping-Tide-CoE", "<p class='main-text'> Skip the staging step. If the encounter deck is ever empty, shuffle the encounter discard pile into the encounter deck.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When an enemy makes an attack, deal it an additional shadow card.</p><p class='main-text'><b>If a <b><i>Mount</i></b> objective is attached to an enemy, the players lose the game. If there are no enemies in play, the players win the game.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Thengel-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After an ally is discarded from play, that ally’s owner searches the top 5 cards of their deck for an ally that shares a <b><i>Trait</i></b> with the discarded ally, puts it into play exhausted, and shuffles their deck. (Limit once per round.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>“My friend,” said Gandalf, “you had horses, and deeds of arms, and the free fields.” —The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Theodwyn-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After Théodwyn enters play, either draw 1 card or add 1 resource to a <b><i>Noble</i></b> hero’s resource pool.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“She is fearless and high-hearted. All love her. Let her be as lord to Eorlingas while we are gone.”<br/>—Háma, The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Thieves-and-Coursers-CoE", "<p class='flavor-text'>Orcs have invaded the Eastfold, rampaging across the land and capturing King Thengel’s prized warhorses. </p><p class='main-text'> <b>Setup:</b> Add Stolen Steeds to the staging area. Set Thruk, the <b><i>Mount</i></b> objectives, and the 8 enemies from the Orc-host encounter set aside, out of play. Shuffle the encounter deck. The first player reveals Flinthoof and Brightmane and adds them to the staging area. Then, each other player discards cards from the encounter deck until a location or enemy is discarded and adds it to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Thieves-and-Coursers-CoE", "<p class='flavor-text'>If you can recover Flinthoof and Brightmane, you may be able to stop the main Orc-host before they reach Aldburg.</p><p class='main-text'> <b>This stage cannot be defeated unless the players control 2 <b><i>Mount</i></b> objectives.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Thirst-for-Horse-Blood-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player who controls a <b><i>Mount</i></b> objective chooses: either reveal an encounter card, or choose the enemy with the highest engagement cost without an attachment and attach a <b><i>Mount</i></b> objective you control to that enemy as a guarded objective. If no player controls a <b><i>Mount</i></b> objective, Thirst for Horse Blood gains surge.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“We’ll feast on horseflesh yet, or something better.”<br/>—Uglúk, The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Thruk-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Thruk engages the first player.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of the combat phase, if Thruk is not guarding an objective, he makes an immediate attack against the engaged player.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Tired-and-Hungry-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>While attached to a hero, counts as a <b><i><b><i>Condition</i></b></i></b> attachment with the text: “<b>Forced:</b> After a location is explored, exhaust attached hero.”</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Attach to a ready hero without a copy of Tired and Hungry. Otherwise, Tired and Hungry gains surge.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“With foes ahead, behind us dread, beneath the sky shall be our bed.” —The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Vengeful-Bowman-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Looter 2. Archery X.</p><p class='main-text'>X is the number of different player card types in Vengeful Bowman’s loot pile.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If this attack deals damage, add the top card of your deck to attacking enemy’s loot pile.</p>");
            AddHtml("Wealth-of-Adventure-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Search your deck for a card with the <b><i>Skill</i></b> trait and add it to your hand. Shuffle your deck.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“It’s a dangerous business, Frodo, going out of your door,” he used to say. “You step into the Road, and if you don’t keep your feet, there is no knowing where you might be swept off to.”<br/>—Frodo, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("White-Mountain-Reinforcements-CoE", "<p class='flavor-text'>Orcs have begun streaming from their mountain caves, strengthening the attacks of your foes. If you don’t cut them off, they may soon overwhelm you.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player not engaged with an enemy must search the encounter deck and discard pile for an enemy and put it into play engaged with them. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p><p class='main-text'>Each shadow card with no shadow effect gains: “<b>Shadow:</b> Raise your threat by 1.”</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Wild-Country-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Doomed 1. Vast.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the travel phase, if the active location is not vast, each player deals 1 damage to a character they control.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If the active location is vast, deal 1 damage to the defending character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Wild-Ravager-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of the encounter phase, choose a random player. Wild Ravager engages that player.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy cannot take damage until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Windworn-Villages-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>Vast.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the travel phase, if the active location is not vast, each player chooses and discards 1 card from their hand.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If the active location is vast, discard 1 attachment from the defending character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Wooden-Barricade-CoE", "<p class='main-text'>While Wooden Barricade is in the staging area, it gains: “<b>Forced:</b> At the end of the combat phase, deal 1 damage to Erelas Beacon and place 1 progress on Wooden Barricade.”</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Either discard 2 attachments you control or deal 1 damage to Erelas Beacon.</p>");
            AddHtml("Worthy-of-Remembrance-CoE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Combat Action:</b> Discard a <b><i>Rohan</i></b> ally you control to choose an enemy. Deal 2 damage to that enemy (4 damage instead if the ally was unique).</p><p class='flavor-text'>Then the heart of Éowyn changed… suddenly her winter passed, and the sun shone on her.<br/>—The Return of the King</p>");
        }

        private void TheAldburgPlot()
        {
            AddHtml("Fatty-Bolger-TAP", "<p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Reduce your threat by 2.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> Raise your threat by 4 and exhaust {self} to cancel a non-unique enemy just revealed from the encounter deck and add it to the victory display. (Limit once per game for the group.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>Fatty Bolger had not been idle. As soon as he saw the dark shapes creep from the garden, he knew that he must run for it, or perish.<br>&mdash;The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Widfast-TAP", "<p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Search your collection for a {trait:Creature.@Creature} ally and add it to your hand. For the first round, reduce its cost by 2.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel Action:</b> If there is 1 active location, spend 1 resource from {self}'s pool to travel to another location, resolving its <b>Travel</b> effect. (There are now 2 active locations.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Lily-Cotton-TAP", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust {self} to ready a different {trait:Hobbit.@Hobbit} ally and add {self}'s {Willpower}, {Attack}, and {Defense} to that ally's {Willpower}, {Attack}, and {Defense} respectively until the end of the phase. At the end of the phase, if that ally is still in play, return it to its owner's hand (Limit once per phase.)</p><p class='main-text'></p><p class='flavor-text'>There is little or no magic about them, except the ordinary everyday sort which helps them disappear quietly and quickly...<br>&mdash;The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("A-Lesson-in-Caution-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Secrecy 1.}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Draw 1 card. Then, either reduce your threat by 2, or the next card you play this phase gains secrecy 1.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Hobbits go light, and their footprints are not easy even for a Ranger to read...<br>&mdash;The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("There-and-Back-Again-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Secrecy 1.}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a {trait:Hobbit.@Hobbit} ally leaves play, search your hand or discard pile for a copy of that ally and put it into play, under any player's control.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The legal bother, indeed, lasted for years. It was quite a long time before Mr. Baggins was in fact admitted to be alive again.<br>&mdash;The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("Buckland-Shirriff-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Devoted.} {keyword:Ranged.}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After an enemy that shares a <b><i>Trait</i></b> with an enemy in the victory display is added to the staging area, spend 1 {sphere:Lore} resource to put {self} into play from your hand, under your control.</p><p class='flavor-text'></p>");
            AddHtml("Weep-No-More-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>Limit 3 copies of {self} in the victory display.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After a \"when revealed\" effect or a shadow effect on a treachery card resolves, add {self} to the victory display to add that treachery card to the victory display.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&ldquo;At least we may yet be avenged. Let us gird ourselves and weep no more!&rdquo;<br>&mdash;Aragorn, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Fear-Fire-Foes-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Secrecy 1.} Play only if you do not control a {trait:Warrior.@Warrior} hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Choose a non-unique enemy and an attribute ({Threat}, {Attack}, or {Defense}). Until the end of the phase, reduce the chosen attribute of that enemy to 0.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Far away answering horns were heard. The alarm was spreading.<br>&mdash;The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Horn-call-of-Buckland-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a {sphere:Lore} or {trait:Hobbit.@Hobbit} hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After you engage an enemy that shares a <b><i>Trait</i></b> with an enemy in the victory display, exhaust {self} to ready attached hero. Then, that enemy gets -1 {Attack} and -1 {Defense} until the end of the round.</p><p class='flavor-text'></p>");
            AddHtml("Young-Tom-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>During the round that {self} enters play, enemies get +5 engagement cost.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&ldquo;Not all is well there,&rdquo; said Frodo, &ldquo;but certainly gardeners are honoured.&rdquo;<br>&mdash;The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Gavin-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have attachments.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After an encounter card without surge is revealed, exhaust {self} to give that card surge and add 1 resource to the pool of a {trait:Scout.@Scout} hero you control. If the next encounter card revealed is not a location, discard it without resolving its effects.</p>");

            AddHtml("Red-Harvest-TAP", "<p class='flavor-text'>With brutal speed, The Whisperer's men fall upon you. You'll have to fight tooth and nail to make your way to the armoury.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After an enemy engages a player, that player deals 2 damage to a character they control.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After this stage is defeated, shuffle the encounter discard pile into the encounter deck. Each player discards cards from the encounter deck until an enemy is discarded and adds that enemy to the staging area. Add {card:The-Armoury-TAP@The Armoury} to the staging area.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("The-Prisoner-in-White-TAP", "<p class='flavor-text'>In an attempt to cover his tracks, the spy master's agent has infiltrated the prison.</p><p class='main-text'>The players cannot travel to locations or make locations active with player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After this stage is defeated, add {card:Ossian-TAP@Ossian} to the staging area.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("The-Man-with-the-Twisted-Lip-TAP", "<p class='flavor-text'>You've begun to track the secretive spy master of Aldburg, though it's hard to tell which of you is the cat and which is the mouse.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round, raise each player's threat by 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After this stage is defeated, add {card:The-Spy-Master-TAP@The Spy Master} to the staging area.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("A-Fire-Rises-TAP", "<p class='flavor-text'>Something foul is afoot in Aldburg. As you begin putting the pieces together, you see smoke and flame from a nearby building.</p><p class='main-text'>Increase the cost to play each event by 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After this stage is defeated, reveal {card:Spreading-Infero-TAP@Spreading Inferno}.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("A-Case-of-Identity-TAP", "<p class='flavor-text'>The mystery of The Whisperer's true identity remains. You must be on the right trail, judging by her cutthroats skulking in the alleyways.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the staging step, discard cards from the top of the encounter deck until an enemy is discarded. Reveal that enemy.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After this stage is defeated, add {card:Great-Mead-Hall-TAP@Great Mead Hall} to the staging area.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Whisperer-in-the-Darkness-TAP", "<p class='flavor-text'>The tavern was alight with rumors of an assassin called &ldquo;The Whisperer.&rdquo; If you're to unravel this mystery, you will have to seek her out, and stop her before she strikes.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After a location is explored, raise each player's threat by 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After this stage is defeated, add The Whisperer to the staging area.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Spreading-Inferno-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Guarded (location).}</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of the travel phase, discard the attached location, raise each player's threat by 1, and discard the lowest printed cost ally controlled by each player. Reveal {self}.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When the attached location is explored, flip this card over and reveal it.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ruby-Cloak-pin-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>If unattached, attach to a hero with the fewest {trait:Clue.@Clue} objectives attached</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After attached hero readies, discard the top 4 cards of your deck.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Among the ashes, you recognize this pin immediately. It belongs to the cur Gálmód. Queen Morwen's &ldquo;trusted&rdquo; advisor.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Whisperer-TAP", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round, return {self} to the staging area, if able. {self} makes an immediate attack against the first player. Damage that would be dealt by this attack is instead assigned as an increase to the first player's threat.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When {self} is defeated, flip this card over and reveal it.</p>");
            AddHtml("Silver-Dagger-TAP", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add {card:A-Case-of-Identity-TAP@A Case of Identity} and {card:Red-Harvest-TAP@Red Harvest} to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'>If unattached, attach to the hero with the fewest {trait:Clue.@Clue} objectives attached.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After attached hero readies, deal 1 damage to it.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The Whisperer has escaped into the streets of Aldburg, but she has left behind a distinctive, and expensive, weapon.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Spy-Master-TAP", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When {self} is dealt a shadow card with no shadow effect, deal 1 damage to the defending character and deal The Spy Master another shadow card (limit twice per attack).</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When {self} is defeated, flip this card over and reveal it.</p>");
            AddHtml("Prison-Key-TAP", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add {card:A-Fire-Rises-TAP@A Fire Rises} and {card:The-Prisoner-in-White-TAP@The Prisoner in White} to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'>If unattached, attach to the hero with the fewest {trait:Clue.@Clue} objectives attached.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After attached hero readies, discard a non-{trait:Clue.@Clue} objective from it.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Wounded and scrabbling for escape, the Spy Master parts with a key detail: one of his agents is already on the move, and heading for the town prison.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ossian-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. {self} cannot take more than X damage each round, where X is the number of {trait:Clue.@Clue} objectives controlled by the players.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When {self} is defeated, flip this card over and reveal it.</p><p class='flavor-text'>You find Ossian bent over a white-clad corpse. Hearing your approach, he turns.</p>");
            AddHtml("Traitor's-Confession-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>If unattached, attach to the hero with the fewest {trait:Clue.@Clue} objectives attached.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After attached hero readies, discard a card at random from your hand.</p><p class='flavor-text'>With his dying breath, the traitor Ossian reveals Gálmód commanded him to slay one of the members of his own éored: a witness to a terrible betrayal.</p>");
            AddHtml("Garrison-Barracks-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. X is twice the number of {trait:Clue.@Clue} objectives controlled by the players.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Shuffle all set aside {trait:Dunland.@Dunland} enemies into the encounter deck.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When {self} is explored, flip this card over and reveal it.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The city watch has eyes and ears on everything in Aldburg. But who is watching them?</p>");
            AddHtml("Raven-Signet-Ring-TAP", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add {card:The-Man-with-the-Twisted-Lip-TAP@The Man with the Twisted Lip} to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'>If unattached, attach to the hero with the fewest {trait:Clue.@Clue} objectives attached.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After attached hero readies, discard all resources in its resource pool.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The prisoner has told the guards of an operative called &ldquo;the spy master.&rdquo; The only lead presently is this ring, believed to belong to him.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Horse's-Tail-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. X is twice the number of {trait:Clue.@Clue} objectives controlled by the players.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Shuffle all set aside {trait:Garrison.@Garrison} enemies into the encounter deck.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When {self} is explored, flip this card over and reveal it.</p><p class='flavor-text'>It may draw the suspicion of the town watch, but this mystery won't be solved by ordinary means.</p>");
            AddHtml("Rohirric-Coins-TAP", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Add {card:Whisperer-in-the-Darkness-TAP@Whisperer in the Darkness} to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'>If unattached, attach to a hero with the fewest {trait:Clue.@Clue} objectives attached.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After attached hero readies, exhaust another character you control.</p><p class='flavor-text'>An unknown figure bumps inot your table. Apologizing profusely, he stumbles into the night. By the time you notice the sack of coin he left behind, he's already gone.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Armoury-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> Each player must exhaust the ready character they control with the highest {Defense}.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When {self} is explored, flip this card over and reveal it.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The Whisperer wielded a distinctive, familiar-looking dagger. Perhaps the armoury's quartermaster can tell you something about it.</p>");
            AddHtml("Red-Fletched-Arrow-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>If unattached, attach to the hero with the fewest {trait:Clue.@Clue} objectives attached.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After attached hero readies, raise your threat by 1.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The armoury's quartermaster informs you that he personally forged the dagger, as well as this unusual arrow, for Lord Gálmód.</p>");
            AddHtml("Great-Mead-Hall-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel:</b> The players must raise their threat by X where X is the number of enemies in the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> When {self} is explored, flip this card over and reveal it.</p><p class='flavor-text'>You have tracked the Whisperer's agents to the very halls of Marshal Éomund. How deep does this conspiracy run?</p>");
            AddHtml("Letter-from-Dunland-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>If unattached, attach to the hero with the fewest {trait:Clue.@Clue} objectives attached.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After attached hero readies, discard 2 progress from each location and quest card.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Hidden away, you find a sealed letter written in choppy Rohirric, signed &ldquo;Grimrede.&rdquo; It is addresses to a man you thought your friend &mdash; Gálmód</p>");
            AddHtml("Town-Guard-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>If the players control 2 or more {trait:Clue.@Clue} objectives {self} gets +2 {Threat}.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After {self} attacks and destroys a character you control. discard 1 resource from each hero you control with a {trait:Clue.@Clue} objective.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&ldquo;Do I hope in vain that you have been sent to me for a help in doubt and need?&rdquo;<br>&mdash;Éomer, The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Dunlending-Agents-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>If the players control 2 or more {trait:Clue.@Clue} objectives, {self} gets +2 {Attack}.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After {self} attacks and destroys a character you control, deal 1 damage to each hero you control with a {trait:Clue.@Clue} objective.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The Dunlendings and many men of the garrison of the Burg were at work.<br>&mdash;The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Aldburg-Malcontent-TAP", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> If the players control 3 or more {trait:Clue.@Clue} objectives, {self} gains surge.</p>{Shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> If the players control 2 or more {trait:Clue.@Clue} objectives, return attacking enemy to the staging area after this attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Misty-Street-TAP", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Discard all attachments and tokens from the highest cost ally the first player controls and attach that ally facedown under {self}.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> After {self} leaves play, return the attached ally to its owner's control, faceup and ready.</p>{Shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Discard a non-{trait:Clue.@Clue} attachment you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Well-lit-Hall-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>While {self} is in the staging area, no more than 3 progress can be placed on a quest card as a result of questing successfully.</p>{Shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} (+2 {Attack} instead if the defending character has a {trait:Clue.@Clue} attachment).</p>");
            AddHtml("Decrepit-Hovel-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>Ally resource costs must be paid from a single hero's resource pool.</p>{Shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Discard 1 resource from a hero you control.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&ldquo;They go out there roving round, thieving or 'gathering' as they call it.&rdquo;<br>&mdash;Tom Cotton, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Taken-by-the-Night-TAP", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player must discard the lowest printed cost ally they control. If no allies with a printed cost of 2 or higher were discarded this way, {self} gains surge.</p>{Shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} (+2 {Attack} instead if this enemy is attacking from the staging area).</p>");
            AddHtml("False-Lead-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>{keyword:Doomed 1.}</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Each player removes a hero they control with an attached {trait:Clue.@Clue} objective from the quest, if able. Then, each player exhausts a hero they control that is not committed to the quest.</p><p class='flavor-text'>&ldquo;...are you now trying to snare me with a flasehood?&rdquo;<br>&mdash;Frodo Baggins, The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Sudden-Ambush-TAP", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> The first player must choose: either raise your threat by 4, or the topmost enemy in the encounter discard pile engages you and makes an immediate attack. You must declare the ready character you control with the highest {Willpower} as the defender for this attack, if able.</p>{Shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow:</b> Resolve this card's &ldquo;when revealed&rdquo; effect.</p>");
            AddHtml("Evil-Under-the-Moon-TAP", "<p class='flavor-text'>With the knowledge that a faction of rebels has taken up residence in Aldburg, Ealdwulf entreats you to root them out.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Set each encounter side quest, each copy of {card:Town-Guard-TAP@Town Guard}, and each copy of {card:Dunlending-Agents-TAP@Dunlending Agents} aside, out of play. Set each double-sided encounter card aside, out of play, {trait:Clue.@Clue} side facedown. Add {card:Garrison-Barrack-TAP@Garrison Barracks} and {card:The-Horse's-Tail-TAP@The Horse’s Tail} to the staging area. Search the encounter deck for an enemy and add it to the staging area (2 different enemies instead if there are 3 or more players). Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Evil-Under-the-Moon-TAP", "<p class='flavor-text'>Where to begin the hunt? Will you seek the help of the town guards or investigate the criminal underworld as a seedy tavern?</p><p class='main-text'>Enemies cannot be optionally engaged.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round, raise each player's threat by 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>If the players control 1 or more <i>Clue</i> objectives, advance to the next stage.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Gathering-Clues-TAP", "<p class='flavor-text'>The Rohirric town of Aldburg is rife with mystery. Around every corner waits a new riddle, and behind every riddle a sharpened, desperate blade. Before the sun rises, you will have to go deeper to uncover the truth.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Gathering-Clues-TAP", "<p class='flavor-text'>It appears Aldburg is playing host to a twin-headed mystery. If you can only graps a single thread, you may be able to untangle this corrupt and biter web. It is past midnight. Time is drawing thin.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> At the end of the round, if the players contol at least 4 {trait:Clue.@Clue} objectives, they may advance to stage 3A.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Uncertain-Dawn-TAP", "<p class='flavor-text'>As sun breaks over the streets of Aldburg, your cornered foes reveal themselves. You have gathered your clues. Now, bring them to bear as you battle for your lives - and for the soul of Rohan.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed:</b> Remove all {trait:Suspicious.@Suspicious} cards and encounter side quests from the game. Add any set aside {trait:Dunland.@Dunland} or {trait:Garrison.@Garrison} enemies to the staging area, if able.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Uncertain-Dawn-TAP", "<p class='main-text'>The Uncertain Dawn gets -5 quest points for each {trait:Clue.@Clue} objective the players control.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the beginning of the quest phase, discard cards from the top of the encounter deck until an enemy is discarded. Reveal that enemy and add it to the staging area.</p><p class='main-text'><b>This stage cannot be defeated except at the end of the round. If the players defeat this stage, they win the game.</b></p>");
        }

        private void FireOnTheEastemnet()
        {
            AddHtml("Alagos-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have restricted attachments.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After an <b><i>Eagle</i></b> ally enters a player’s play area, add 1 resource to the pool of a hero that player controls. (Limit once per round.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>“What is all this uproar in the forest tonight?”<br/>—The Lord of the Eagles, The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("Box-of-Earth-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Play only if you control a <b><i>Noldor</i></b> or <b><i>Silvan</i></b> hero.</p><p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust Box of Earth to choose a location. Place 1 progress on that location and give it the <b><i>Forest</i></b> trait until the end of the round.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“It will not keep you on your road, nor defend you against any peril; but if you keep it… it may reward you.”<br/>—Galadriel, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Breath-of-Arda-FotE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Encounter Action</b>: Return X <b><i>Eagle</i></b> allies you own (under any player’s control) to your hand. Then, put each of those allies into play under any player’s control, one at a time. Remove Breath of Arda from the game.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“For we have need of speed greater than any wind.” —Gandalf, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Captured-Steeds-FotE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When an enemy leaves play by any means other than being defeated, move all steeds from that enemy onto Captured Steeds.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When a location leaves play by any means other than being explored, move all steeds from that location onto Captured Steeds.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Their horses were of great stature, strong and clean-limbed… —The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Chieftain-of-the-Skies-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Devoted.</p><p class='main-text'>Cannot have restricted attachments.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After Chieftain of the Skies enters your play area, ready an ally you control.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Behind them in long swift lines came all their vassals from the northern mountains. —The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Cracking-Horse-Whip-FotE", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: For each ready character a player controls, they must choose: either exhaust that character, or deal 1 damage to it. If there are more steeds on Wild Steeds than on Captured Steeds, Cracking Horse Whip gains surge.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Where there’s a whip there’s a will, my slugs.”<br/>—The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Eastemnet-Pasture-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Steeds 1{PerPlayer}.</p><p class='main-text'>Progress cannot be placed on locations in the staging area.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The swelling grass-lands rose and fell like a wide grey sea. —The Two Towers</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Entwash-Crossings-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Steeds 3.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel</b>: Search the encounter discard pile for an enemy and put it into play engaged with the first player.</p><p class='flavor-text'>There the herdsmen had wandered much, living in camp and tent, even in winter-time. But now all the land was empty. —The Two Towers</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Exhausted-Pursuit-FotE", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Either each enemy in play captures its steeds, or exhaust each damaged character.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Exhaust a damaged character you control.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Dazed as he was with pain and weariness, Sam woke up… —The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Expanded-Search-FotE", "<p class='flavor-text'>The orcs seem to have picked up some scent, and have begun searching the ground near a place where you once stopped to rest.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After an enemy is engaged, either move a steed from Wild Steeds to Captured Steeds or that enemy gets +3 {Attack} until the end of the round.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Fang-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Limit 1 per deck. Cannot have attachments. Each enemy in play gets +1 engagement cost.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After Fang enters play, search your deck for a <b><i>Creature</i></b> ally and add it to your hand. Until the end of the phase, that ally does not require a resource match. Shuffle your deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Faunith-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have restricted attachments.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Quest Action</b>: Play an <b><i>Eagle</i></b> ally from your hand. Then, you may exhaust that ally to either commit it to the quest or deal 1 damage to an enemy in the staging area.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Straight down upon the Nazgûl they bore, stooping suddenly out of the high airs… —The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Golden-Crown-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to an <b><i>Eagle</i></b> hero. Attached hero gains the <b><i>Noble</i></b> trait.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust Golden Crown to choose an <b><i>Eagle</i></b> ally you own under any player’s control. Either discard that ally from play to add 1 resource to attached hero’s pool, or give control of that ally to a different player.</p>");
            AddHtml("Grip-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Limit 1 per deck. Cannot have attachments. Each enemy in play gets +1 engagement cost.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After Grip enters play, search your deck for a <b><i>Creature</i></b> ally and add it to your hand. Until the end of the phase, that ally does not require a resource match. Shuffle your deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Guided-by-Fate-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: When you would shuffle a set-aside card with the encounter keyword into the encounter deck, shuffle it into the top 5 cards instead.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: If the encounter deck has 5 or more cards in it, exhaust Guided by Fate and raise your threat by 1 to shuffle the top card of the encounter discard pile into the top 5 cards of the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Hidden-Orc-Camp-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Steeds 1.</p><p class='main-text'>Hidden Orc Camp gets +1 {Threat} for each steed on it.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the combat phase, move a steed from a non-<b><i>Camp</i></b> location to Hidden Orc Camp.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel</b>: Each player exhausts a character they control.</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Hidden-Roosts-FotE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: When an <b><i>Eagle</i></b> ally leaves play, that ally’s controller reduces their threat by X, where X is the printed cost of the ally. If X is 2 or less, that player also draws 1 card.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“May the wind under your wings bear you where the sun sails and moon walks.” —Gandalf, The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("Messenger-of-Manwe-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot defend or have restricted attachments.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After Messenger of Manwë enters your play area, give an <b><i>Eagle</i></b> or <b><i>Noble</i></b> hero you control +1 {Willpower} until the end of the round.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After Messenger of Manwë commits to the quest, give control of it to another player.</p>");
            AddHtml("Morgahk-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the beginning of the quest phase, Morgahk makes an immediate attack against the first player.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Morgahk attacks and destroys a character, each enemy in the staging area captures its steeds.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Open-Meadows-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Steeds 2.</p><p class='main-text'>While Open Meadows is in the staging area, it gains: “<b>Forced</b>: At the end of the combat phase, add the topmost enemy in the encounter discard pile to the staging area.”</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Orc-Lookout-FotE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the combat phase, Orc Lookout captures its steeds.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Either the attacking enemy cannot take damage this round, or it captures its steeds.</p>");
            AddHtml("Orcish-Wrangler-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When Orcish Wrangler attacks, move a steed from the active location to Orcish Wrangler.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: If there are more steeds on Wild Steeds than on Captured Steeds, attacking enemy captures its steeds.</p>");
            AddHtml("Panicked-Horses-FotE", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Move a steed from Wild Steeds to each enemy in play. If there are less than 1{PerPlayer} enemies in play, search the encounter deck and discard pile for an enemy and add it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck if searched.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} (+2 {Attack} instead if there are more steeds on Wild Steeds than on Captured Steeds).</p>");
            AddHtml("Pillaged-Stables-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Steeds 4.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the round, if there are any steeds remaining on Pillaged Stables, move 1 steed from Pillaged Stables to Captured Steeds. The first player may raise their threat by 2 to cancel this effect.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: If this attack destroys a character, the attacking enemy captures its steeds.</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Poachers-in-the-Night-FotE", "<p class='flavor-text'>With fire and whip, the orc-host has regrouped to rob Rohan of its prized steeds. </p><p class='main-text'> <b>Setup</b>: Set Shores of Anduin, Orc Battalion, and Morgahk aside, out of play. Make a copy of Pillaged Stables the active location. Add Wild Steeds, Captured Steeds, and 1 copy of Eastemnet Pastures to the staging area. Place 1 plus 3{PerPlayer} steeds on Wild Steeds. Each player searches the encounter deck for a different enemy and adds it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Poachers-in-the-Night-FotE", "<p class='flavor-text'>Setting out from the stables, you attack the horse-thieves head on! Push them back from the fields before they make away with their stolen beasts.</p><p class='main-text'> Steeds 3{PerPlayer}.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the round, move 1{PerPlayer} steed from this stage to Captured Steeds. If there are no steeds remaining here, advance to the next stage.</p>");
            AddHtml("Relentless-Forces-FotE", "<p class='flavor-text'>Raging after the defeat of warchief Thruk, the orc-host masses over the countryside, wreaking havoc. “On, on!” they cry, baying for horse-meat. </p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed</b>: Shuffle the encounter discard pile into the encounter deck. The first player adds Orc Battalion to the staging area. Each other player discards cards from the top of the encounter deck until an enemy is discarded and adds that enemy to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Relentless-Forces-FotE", "<p class='flavor-text'>The orcs will not be satisfied until they reap the fields of stallion and mare. Flank them and scatter them to the east!</p><p class='main-text'> Steeds 3{PerPlayer}.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the round, if there are any enemies in play, move 1{PerPlayer} steeds from this stage to Captured Steeds.</p><p class='main-text'><b>This stage cannot be defeated while Orc Battalion is in play.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Roving-Herbmaster-FotE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After a player reduces their threat, heal 1 damage from a character you control. Then, you may give control of Roving Herbmaster to another player. (Limit once per round.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Crush one in the water, and wash the wound clean, and I will bind it. Now it is your turn.”<br/>—Aragorn, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Shores-of-Anduin-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>While Shores of Anduin is in the victory display, the current quest gains “<b>Response</b>: When an enemy is destroyed, move X steeds from Captured Steeds to Wild Steeds. X is the destroyed enemy’s printed {Threat}.”</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel</b>: Each enemy in the staging area captures its steeds.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("To-the-River-FotE", "<p class='flavor-text'>The last of the orcs rally to their leader, the warchief Morgahk. Now is the moment to break their formation and press them with force of arms and strength of will.</p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed</b>: Shuffle the encounter discard pile into the encounter deck. The first player adds Shores of Anduin and Morgahk to the staging area. Each other player discards cards from the top of the encounter deck until an enemy is discarded and adds that enemy to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("To-the-River-FotE", "<p class='main-text'> Morgahk cannot leave the staging area unless there are at least 15 progress tokens here.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the round, return each engaged enemy to the staging area. If there are more steeds on Wild Steeds than on Captured Steeds, each enemy in the staging area captures its steeds.</p><p class='main-text'><b>The players cannot defeat this stage while Morgahk is in play. After Morgahk is destroyed, if there are more steeds on Wild Steeds than on Captured Steeds, the players win the game. Otherwise, the players lose the game.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Veteran-Eagle-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have restricted attachments.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After Veteran Eagle enters your play area, each copy of Veteran Eagle you control gets +1 {Willpower}, +1 {Attack} and +1 {Defense} until the end of the round.</p><p class='flavor-text'>But eagles have keen eyes and can see small things at a great distance. —The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("White-Mountain-Beastmaster-FotE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After White Mountain Beastmaster engages you, either it makes an immediate attack, or it captures its steeds.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Either the attacking enemy makes an additional attack after this one, or it captures its steeds.</p>");
            AddHtml("Wild-Steeds-FotE", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After an enemy enters play, place a steed from Wild Steeds on that enemy.</p><p class='main-text'><b>At the end of the round, if there are no steeds on Wild Steeds, the players lose the game.</b></p><p class='flavor-text'>“I’ll bet there’s all sorts of good things running wild in this country.” —Sam, The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Wolf-FotE", "<p class='main-text'>Limit 1 per deck. Cannot have attachments. Each enemy in play gets +1 engagement cost.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After Wolf enters play, search your deck for a <b><i>Creature</i></b> ally and add it to your hand. Until the end of the phase, that ally does not require a resource match. Shuffle your deck.</p><p class='flavor-text'>…most ferocious of the three… —The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
        }

        private void TheGapOfRohan()
        {
            AddHtml("A-Dangerous-Pursuit-TGoR", "<p class='flavor-text'>Pressing onward, Gálmód is joined by a small group of fellow rebels. As he rides through, they close ranks behind him to stall your pursuit. </p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed</b>: Add 1 time counter to Gálmód. Shuffle the encounter discard pile into the encounter deck. Discard cards from the top of the encounter deck until 1{PerPlayer} enemies are discarded. Add each discarded enemy to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("A-Dangerous-Pursuit-TGoR", "<p class='flavor-text'>A cruel gale howls through the mountain pass, and even your attackers seem perplexed at the storm’s ferocity. The white haze of wind-whipped snow is blinding as you prepare to face your foes.</p><p class='main-text'> Frostbite 2.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the beginning of the quest phase, deal 1 damage to each exhausted character.</p>");
            AddHtml("A-Stout-Heart-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: Cancel a shadow effect just triggered during an undefended attack. After this attack damages a single hero, the controller of that hero may spend 1 resource from its pool to reduce their threat by 3.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“We come now to the very brink, where hope and despair are akin. To waver is to fall.”<br/>—Aragorn, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Archet-Alekeeper-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'>Devoted.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After an undefended attack damages a hero you control, ready Archet Alekeeper and give it +1 {Attack} until the end of the phase.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Gave me a chance of walking round the country and seeing folk, and hearing the news, and knowing where the good beer was.” —Robin Smallburrow, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Barliman-Butterbur-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After Barliman Butterbur takes damage from an undefended attack, draw 1 card.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“I’m run off my feet; but I’ll see what I can do for you.” —The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Biting-Winds-TGoR", "<p class='flavor-text'>As Gálmód races through the flurry, the brutal weather worsens. He pushes his stallion beyond all limits, determined to escape a traitor’s bloody justice. </p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed</b>: Add 1 time counter to Gálmód. The first player searches the encounter deck, encounter discard pile, and victory display for a copy of Unnatural Cold and attaches it to the main quest. Shuffle the encounter deck. Each other player reveals an encounter card.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Biting-Winds-TGoR", "<p class='flavor-text'>Soon, even your party begins to slow and stagger. If the traitor escapes through the mountain pass, he will be far from Rohan’s reach.</p><p class='main-text'> Frostbite 2.</p><p class='main-text'>Treat the text box of each damaged character as if it were blank (except for <b><i>Traits</i></b>).</p><p class='main-text'>Unnatural Cold is immune to player card effects and gains surge.</p>");
            AddHtml("Bob-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After Bob enters play, search your deck for a <b><i>Mount</i></b> or <b><i>Pony</i></b> card and add it to your hand. Shuffle your deck.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“A poor old half-starved creature it is, but he won’t part with it for less than thrice its worth.”<br/>—The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Bree-Pony-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a <b><i>Bree</i></b> or <b><i>Hobbit</i></b> character. Restricted.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached character gets +1 hit point.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: When attached character takes damage from an undefended attack, exhaust Bree Pony to reduce that damage by 1.</p><p class='flavor-text'>No horse or pony was to be got for love or money in the neighbourhood – except one.<br/>—The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Bree-land-Protector-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'>Devoted.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: Exhaust Bree-land Protector to cancel a shadow effect just triggered during an attack and deal the attacking enemy another shadow card. If this attack deals no damage, return Bree-land Protector to its owner’s hand after the attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dunlending-Rearguard-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the encounter phase, if Dunlending Rearguard is in the staging area, remove 1 time counter from Gálmód.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Death to the Strawheads! Death to the robbers of the North!” —The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Exposed-Ridge-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'>While Exposed Ridge is in the staging area, progress cannot be placed here.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel</b>: Deal 1 damage to each exhausted character controlled by the first player.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“How I do hate looking down from a height! But looking’s better than climbing.”<br/>—Sam Gamgee, The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Frantic-Dunlending-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the round, return Frantic Dunlending to the staging area.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Attacking enemy gets +X {Attack} for this attack. X is the Frostbite value on the main quest.</p>");
            AddHtml("Frozen-Lake-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'>While Frozen Lake is the active location, treat the text box of each copy of Snowbank in the staging area as if it were blank.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Frozen Lake leaves play as an explored location, discard the top card of the encounter deck. If that card is a treachery, each player discards an ally they control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Frozen-Solid-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Exhaust all attachments the players control. Attachments cannot ready until the end of the round. If no attachments were exhausted this way, Frozen Solid gains surge.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Either stop where we are, or go back. It is no good going on.” —Gandalf, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Galmod-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'>Time 7.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When the last time counter is removed from Gálmód, the players lose the game.</b></p><p class='flavor-text'>The oathbreaker has fled westward, into the heart of a raging storm.</p>");
            AddHtml("Galmod's-Escort-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Cannot leave the staging area (except by being destroyed), but is considered to be engaged with each player.</p><p class='main-text'>Damage that would be dealt to Gálmód’s Escort must first be dealt as progress to copies of Snowbank in the staging area, if able.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Gift-of-Foresight-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero with at least 2 printed {Willpower}. Limit 1 per hero.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gets +2 {Defense} if it has not committed to the quest this round.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Do not think that only by singing amid the trees, nor even by the slender arrows of elven-bows, is this land of Lothlórien maintained and defended.”<br/>–Galadriel, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Giving-Chase-TGoR", "<p class='flavor-text'>You have pursued the traitor Gálmód to the Gap of Rohan. However, unseasonable snows have made your passage difficult. </p><p class='main-text'> <b>Setup</b>: Set Gálmód’s Escort aside, out of play. Add Gálmód and 1{PerPlayer} copies of Snowbank to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Giving-Chase-TGoR", "<p class='flavor-text'>As the blizzard closes in, you must capture the treasonous Gálmód at any cost.</p><p class='main-text'> Frostbite 1.</p><p class='main-text'>Characters cannot be readied by player card effects.</p>");
            AddHtml("Half-pint-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a character.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Refresh Action</b>: Discard Half-pint to heal up to 2 damage from attached character. Then, put an <b><i>Item</i></b> attachment in your discard pile on the top of your deck.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“I’ve a drop of good ale on tap, if you and your friends are willing.”<br/>—Farmer Maggot, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Harry-Goatleaf-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: Cancel 1 point of combat damage just dealt to a hero you control. (Limit once per round per hero.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Your business is your own, no doubt, but it’s my business to ask questions after nightfall.”<br/>—The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Nob-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'>Reduce the cost of the first <b><i>Item</i></b> attachment you play on another <b><i>Bree</i></b> or <b><i>Hobbit</i></b> character each round by 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust Nob to draw a card. If that card is an <b><i>Item</i></b> attachment, ready a <b><i>Bree</i></b> character. (Limit once per round.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Where are you, you woolly-footed slow-coach?”<br/>—Barliman Butterbur, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Pint-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'>Play only if you control a unique <b><i>Bree</i></b> character.</p><p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust Pint to heal 1 damage from attached hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Discard Pint to heal 5 damage from attached hero.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Well, my merry folk, will you drink another draught with me before you go?” —Treebeard, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Recapture-the-Traitor-TGoR", "<p class='flavor-text'>As the traitor’s horse stumbles just ahead of the mountain pass, one of Gálmód’s confederates rips him from his saddle. </p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed</b>: Add 1 time counter to Gálmód. The first player adds Gálmód’s Escort to the staging area and attaches Gálmód to it as a guarded objective. Each other player searches the encounter deck, encounter discard pile, and victory display for a copy of Snowbank and adds it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Recapture-the-Traitor-TGoR", "<p class='flavor-text'>Gálmód and his bodyguard have nearly escaped into the wilderness! Soon he will be out of reach entirely.</p><p class='main-text'> Frostbite 3.</p><p class='main-text'>Gálmód’s Escort cannot take damage until Recapture the Traitor has at least 6 progress on it.</p><p class='main-text'><b>The players cannot defeat this stage while Gálmód is guarded by an enemy. When Gálmód is free of encounters, he is captured and the players win the game.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Scheming-Staddler-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After an undefended attack damages a hero you control, deal 1 damage to the attacking enemy. (Limit once per phase.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>“He would sell anything to anybody; or make mischief for amusement.” —Aragorn, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Seasoned-Forager-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero you control. Limit 1 per player.</p><p class='main-text'>Your heroes cannot gain resources from player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust Seasoned Forager to reduce the cost of the next card you play this phase that matches the attached hero’s sphere by 1.</p>");
            AddHtml("Slippery-Hill-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'>X is 1 more than the number of allies controlled by the player with the most allies.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Come after me – you will see the way I go.”<br/>—Gandalf, The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("Snow-Squall-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Add 2 copies of Snowbank from the encounter discard pile to the staging area. If fewer than 2 copies of Snowbank were added to the staging area as a result of this effect, Snow Squall gains surge.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Search the encounter discard pile for 1 copy of Snowbank and add it to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Snowbank-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When progress would be placed on a quest card or on the active location, place it on a copy of Snowbank instead.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Quest Action</b>: Exhaust a hero you control to place X progress on this location, where X is the exhausted hero’s printed {Attack}.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Add Snowbank to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml("Stumble-in-the-Snow-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Each player exhausts a character they control and deals X damage to it, where X is the Frostbite value on the main quest.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Defending character cannot ready until the end of the round.</p>");
            AddHtml("Unnatural-Cold-TGoR", "<p class='main-text'>While attached to a quest, counts as a <b><i><b><i>Condition</i></b></i></b> attachment with the text: “<b>Forced</b>: After an ally or enemy enters play, deal 1 damage to it. If it is an ally, its controller may exhaust it to cancel this effect.”</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Attach to the main quest if it does not have a copy of Unnatural Cold attached.</p>");
            AddHtml("White-Wall-TGoR", "<p class='flavor-text'>The great driving blizzard seems to have no end. The mountain’s great gales and fell winds bring with them vast, implacable walls of snow.</p><p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'>White Wall gets +4{PerPlayer} quest points.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the beginning of the quest phase, search the encounter discard pile for 1 copy of Snowbank and add it to the staging area.</p>{victory:1}");
        }

        private void TheGlitteringCaves()
        {
            AddHtml("Alluring-Paths-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>When faced with the option to travel, the players must travel to Alluring Paths if there is no active location.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Alluring Paths leaves play, if Helm Hammerhand is at a player’s cave, move him to the next player’s cave.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: If you did not move this round, attacking enemy makes an additional attack against you after this one.</p>");
            AddHtml("Balin-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>Devoted.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After a card is discarded from the top of your deck, ready Balin. (Limit once per round.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>The others made no pretense of offering – except old Balin. —The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("Echoes-in-the-Deep-Dark-Pit-TGC", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Move Helm Hammerhand 1 <b>adjacent</b> cave toward the nearest player, if able. Then, Helm Hammerhand makes an immediate attack against the player at his cave with the highest threat. If no attack is made this way, Echoes in the Deep gains surge.</p>{cave:Dark Pit}");
            AddHtml("Echoes-in-the-Deep-Secret-Passage-TGC", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Move Helm Hammerhand 1 <b>adjacent</b> cave toward the nearest player, if able. Then, Helm Hammerhand makes an immediate attack against the player at his cave with the highest threat. If no attack is made this way, Echoes in the Deep gains surge.</p>{cave:Secret Passage}");
            AddHtml("Forgotten-Shade-Fork-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>While making engagement checks against a player that has not moved this round, Forgotten Shade gets –30 engagement cost.</p><p class='main-text'>While engaged with a player that has not moved this round, Forgotten Shade cannot take damage.</p>{cave:Fork}");
            AddHtml("Forgotten-Shade-Dead-End-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>While making engagement checks against a player that has not moved this round, Forgotten Shade gets –30 engagement cost.</p><p class='main-text'>While engaged with a player that has not moved this round, Forgotten Shade cannot take damage.</p>{cave:Dead End}");
            AddHtml("Forgotten-Shade-Tunnel-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>While making engagement checks against a player that has not moved this round, Forgotten Shade gets –30 engagement cost.</p><p class='main-text'>While engaged with a player that has not moved this round, Forgotten Shade cannot take damage.</p>{cave:Tunnel}");
            AddHtml("Gaeronel-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>While there is a top card of your discard pile,</p><p class='main-text'>Gaeronel gets +2 {Willpower} if it is an event;</p><p class='main-text'>Gaeronel gets +2 {Attack} if it is an ally;</p><p class='main-text'>Gaeronel gets +2 {Defense} if it is an attachment.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“I will dwell by the grey shores, guarding the Havens until the last ship sails.” —Círdan, The Silmarillion</p>");
            AddHtml("Glorfindel-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>Glorfindel gets +2 {Attack} while attacking alone.</p><p class='main-text'>Glorfindel gets +2 {Attack} while attacking a unique enemy.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Then Glorfindel leapt forward upon him and his golden armour gleamed strangely in the moon…<br/>—The Fall of Gondolin</p>");
            AddHtml("Guard-the-Entrance-TGC", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Each player raises their threat by X, where X is the number of caves <b>connected</b> to their cave.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Discard a resource from each of your heroes’ pools.</p>");
            AddHtml("Harlond-Lookout-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>Devoted.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After Harlond Lookout is destroyed, ready a character you control.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The fleets passed out of the sight of the watchers in the havens, and their lights faded. —The Silmarillion</p>");
            AddHtml("Helm-Hammerhand-A-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Cannot be engaged.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the combat phase, move {self} 1 <b>adjacent</b> cave toward the nearest player, if able. Then, he makes an immediate attack against each player at his cave. Players at other caves cannot use sentinel characters to defend these attacks.</p>");
            AddHtml("Helm-Hammerhand-B-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Cannot leave the staging area (except by bring destroyed) but is considered to be engaged with each player. Deal {self} an additional shadow card when he attacks.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When {self} is dealt a {trait:Dunland.@Dunland} enemy as a shadow card, cancel its effect (if any) and deal {self} another shadow card.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Helm's-Horn-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>Player tokens cannot move.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Shuffle the encounter discard pile into the encounter deck. If Helm Hammerhand is not at the undamaged cave, move him there. Then, flip Helm Hammerhand over.</p><p class='flavor-text'>One night men heard the horn blowing, but Helm did not return. —The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Killing-With-Fear-Guarded-Hall-TGC", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Each player that is 1 or fewer <b>adjacent</b> caves away from Helm Hammerhand deals 1 damage to each exhausted character they control and each <b><i>Dunland</i></b> enemy engaged with them. Move Helm Hammerhand 1 <b>adjacent</b> cave toward the nearest player.</p>{cave:Guarded Hall}");
            AddHtml("Killing-With-Fear-Stairwell-TGC", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Each player that is 1 or fewer <b>adjacent</b> caves away from Helm Hammerhand deals 1 damage to each exhausted character they control and each <b><i>Dunland</i></b> enemy engaged with them. Move Helm Hammerhand 1 <b>adjacent</b> cave toward the nearest player.</p>{cave:Stairwell}");
            AddHtml("Killing-With-Fear-Cave-Opening-TGC", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Each player that is 1 or fewer <b>adjacent</b> caves away from Helm Hammerhand deals 1 damage to each exhausted character they control and each <b><i>Dunland</i></b> enemy engaged with them. Move Helm Hammerhand 1 <b>adjacent</b> cave toward the nearest player.</p>{cave:Cave Opening}");
            AddHtml("Lay-of-the-Nauglamir-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>Devoted.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Discard the top 10 cards of your deck. Choose up to 2 different <b><i>Noldor</i></b> or <b><i>Dwarf</i></b> allies discarded by this effect and put them into play. Each chosen ally must have a printed cost of 2 or less. You may shuffle any number of the other cards discarded by this effect back into your deck. Remove Lay of the Nauglamír from the game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Legacy-of-Gondolin-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a <b><i>Noldor</i></b> hero you control. Limit 1 per hero.</p><p class='main-text'>You cannot play allies or attachments from your hand unless you have 2 or fewer cards in your hand.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust Legacy of Gondolin to either draw 1 card or discard Legacy of Gondolin.</p>");
            AddHtml("Lurking-Ghul-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>While in the staging area, Lurking Ghûl gains: “<b>Forced</b>: After a player moves, Lurking Ghûl makes an immediate attack from the staging area against that player. (Limit once per round.)”</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Begone, foul dwimmerlaik, lord of carrion! Leave the dead in peace!” —Éowyn, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Onward-Into-Battle-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a <b><i>Warrior</i></b> hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Encounter Action</b>: Exhaust Onward Into Battle to ready attached hero.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“…and though we still hold that a warrior should have more skills and knowledge than only the craft of weapons and slaying, we esteem a warrior, nonetheless, above men of other crafts. Such is the need of our days.” —Faramir, The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Radiant-Caverns-Jewelled-Cavern-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Radiant Caverns is explored, deal it facedown as a shadow card to Helm Hammerhand.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} for each shadow card dealt to it. If this attack destroys a character, raise your threat by 2.</p>{cave:Jewelled Cavern}");
            AddHtml("Radiant-Caverns-Vast-Cave-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Radiant Caverns is explored, deal it facedown as a shadow card to Helm Hammerhand.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} for each shadow card dealt to it. If this attack destroys a character, raise your threat by 2.</p>{cave:Vast Cave}");
            AddHtml("Radiant-Caverns-Crossroads-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Radiant Caverns is explored, deal it facedown as a shadow card to Helm Hammerhand.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} for each shadow card dealt to it. If this attack destroys a character, raise your threat by 2.</p>{cave:Crossroads}");
            AddHtml("Relic-of-Nargothrond-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a <b><i>Noldor</i></b> or <b><i>Dwarf</i></b> character. Restricted. Limit 1 per character. Relic of Nargothrond can be played from your discard pile.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached character gets +1 {Defense}.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Discard Relic of Nargothrond to give attached character +2 {Defense} until the end of the phase.</p><p class='flavor-text'>In that labour Finrod was aided by the Dwarves of the Blue Mountains. —The Silmarillion</p>");
            AddHtml("Salvaged-Supplies-TGC", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: At the end of the refresh phase, if none of your heroes gained any resources from player card effects this round, add 1 resource to the pool of a hero you control.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust a character you control to return Salvaged Supplies from your discard pile to your hand.</p>");
            AddHtml("Search-the-Caves-TGC", "<p class='flavor-text'>Fleeing the violent blizzard, you are pursued by the wraith of Helm Hammerhand. He follows inexorably, seeking to claim the bones of your Dunlending captives. You must navigate the caverns below Helm’s Deep to find Helm’s great warhorn. Sounding it may be your only hope of restoring the wraith’s mind.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup:</b> Set Helm’s Horn aside, out of play. Add Helm Hammerhand to the staging area, <b><i>Stalking</i></b> side faceup. Set up the Caves Map and Clues (see insert).</p>");
            AddHtml2("Search-the-Caves-TGC", "<p class='main-text'> Progress that would be placed here is instead distributed among caves that contain player tokens.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel Action</b>: Any player may remove 4 progress tokens from their current cave to move to a <b>connected</b> cave. There is no limit to the number of times a player may trigger this effect.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When there is exactly 1 undamaged cave remaining, immediately advance to stage 2</b>.</p>");
            AddHtml("Small-Stream-TGC", "<p class='main-text'><b>Travel</b>: Each player must discard a card at random from their hand to travel here.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel Action</b>: If this card is in the victory display, a player at a <b><i>Stream</i></b> cave may remove this card from the game to move to an <b>adjacent</b> cave.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack}. If you did not move this round, deal it another shadow card.</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("The-Horn's-Discovery-TGC", "<p class='flavor-text'>Yet men said that the horn was still heard at times in the Deep and the wraith of Helm would walk among the foes of Rohan and kill men with fear.<br>—The Return of the King</p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed</b>: Attach Helm’s Horn facedown as a clue to the remaining undamaged cave.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Horn's-Discovery-TGC", "<p class='main-text'> All players must be at the undamaged cave before a player can search that cave. Progress that would be placed here is instead distributed among any caves in play (even those without player tokens).</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel Action</b>: Any player may remove 4 progress tokens from their current cave to move to a <b>connected</b> cave. There is no limit to the number of times a player may trigger this effect.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Helm Hammerhand is defeated, the players win the game.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Twisting-Paths-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Attach faceup to a cave in play. Counts as an attachment with the text: “<b>Travel Action</b>: A player at the attached cave may discard Twisting Paths to swap the attached cave (along with its tokens and attachments) with an <b>adjacent</b> cave.”</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Resolve this card’s “when revealed” effect.</p>{cave:Locked Door}");
            AddHtml("Wandering-Spirit-TGC", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot enter play.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: If Wandering Spirit is in your discard pile, move it up or down by 1 or 2 cards. Then, if it is next to a <b><i>Noldor</i></b> ally with a printed cost of 2 or less, you may spend 1 {sphere:Spirit} resource and remove Wandering Spirit from the game to put that ally into play. (Limit once per round.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Wonders-of-Aglarond-TGC", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Wonders of Aglarond leaves play, place 4 progress on any 1 cave without a player token and reveal an encounter card.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Either move Helm Hammerhand 1 <b>adjacent</b> cave toward the nearest player, or raise the defending player’s threat by 2.</p>");

            AddHtml("Cave-Opening-TGC", "<div><p style='float:left'><b>Forced:</b> After you move to this cave, discard an ally or attachment you control with a printed cost of 2 or more.</p><p style='float:right'><b>Travel Action:</b> Raise your threat by 1 for each clue in play to search this cave.</p></div>");
            AddHtml("Crossroads-TGC", "<div><p style='float:left'><b>Forced:</b> After you move to this cave, raise your threat by 3.</p><p style='float:right'><b>Travel Action:</b> Raise your threat by 3 to search this cave.</p></div>");
            AddHtml("Dark-Pit-TGC", "<div><p style='float:left'>Characters at this cave get -1 {Attack} and -1 {Defense} and are removed from the game when they leave play.</p><p style='float:right'><b>Travel Action:</b> Reveal an encounter card to search this cave.</p></div>");
            AddHtml("Dead-End-TGC", "<div><p style='float:left'>While you are at this cave, you cannot draw cards and your heroes cannot gain resources.</p><p style='float:right'><b>Travel Action:</b> Remove all events in your hand and discard pile from the game to search this cave.</p></div>");
            AddHtml("Fork-TGC", "<div><p style='float:left'><b>Forced:</b> After you move to this cave, discard cards from the top of the encounter deck until an enemy is discarded. Engage that enemy.</p><p style='float:right'><b>Travel Action:</b> Discard the ally or attachment you control with the highest printed cost to search this cave.</div>");
            AddHtml("Guarded-Hall-TGC", "<div><p style='float:left'>While you are at this cave, enemies engaged with you are dealt an additional shadow card when then attack.</p><p style='float:right'><b>Travel Action:</b> Engage the topmost enemy in the encounter discard pile to search this cave.</p></div>");
            AddHtml("Jewelled-Cavern-TGC", "<div><p style='float:left'>While you are at this cave, cards you play cost 1 additional matching resource.</p><p style='float:right'><b>Travel Action:</b> Discard all resources from each of your heroes' pools to search this cave.</p></div>");
            AddHtml("Locked-Door-TGC", "<div><p style='float:left'><b>Forced:</b> After you move to this cave, exhaust 2 characters you control.</p><p style='float:right'><b>Travel Action:</b> Name a card type and sphere and discard a card at random from you hand. If the discarded card has the named type and sphere, search this cave.</p></div>");
            AddHtml("Secret-Passage-TGC", "<div><p style='float:left'><b>Forced:</b> After you move to this cave, choose a treachery in the discard pile and reveal it.</p><p style='float:right'><b>Travel Action:</b> Remove 6 progress tokens from this cave to either search this cave or move directly to a cave up to 2 <b>adjacent</b> caves away.</p></div>");
            AddHtml("Stairwell-TGC", "<div><p style='float:left'><b>Forced:</b> After you move to this cave, discard attachments you control until no character you control has more than 2 attachments.</p><p style='float:right'><b>Travel Action:</b> Discard 1 attachment for each character you control with an attachment, if able. Then, search this cave.</p></div>");
            AddHtml("Tunnel-TGC", "<div><p style='float:left'><b>Forced:</b> After you move to this cave, discard characters you control until you control 6 or fewer characters.</p><p style='float:right'><b>Travel Action:</b> Exhaust each ready character you control to search this cave.</p></div>");
            AddHtml("Vast-Cave-TGC", "<div><p style='float:left'>Characters at this cave cannot be readied by player card effects.</p><p style='float:right'><b>Travel Action:</b> Remove 8 progress tokens from this cave to search this cave.</p></div>");
        }

        private void MusteringOfTheRohirrim()
        {
            AddHtml("Aldburg-Provocateur-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Each card played by the engaged player gains Doomed 1.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“There is a third kind: pickers of bones, meddlers in other men’s sorrows, carrion-fowl that grow fat on war.” —Gríma, The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Assassin-at-Edoras-MotR", "<p class='flavor-text'>Under threat of assassination, Thengel has placed Edoras on high alert.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: The first player randomly selects a set aside <b><i>Assassin</i></b> enemy and adds it to the staging area. Each other player reveals an encounter card.</p><p class='main-text'><b><i>Assassin</i></b> enemies are immune to player card effects. While Assassin at Edoras has any remaining quest points, <b><i>Assassin</i></b> enemies cannot take damage.</p><p class='main-text'><b>This stage cannot be defeated while an <b><i>Assassin</i></b> enemy is in play.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Beorn's-Welcome-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Play only if you control a <b><i>Beorning</i></b> hero. Attach to a hero. Limit 1 per hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After you spend any resources from attached hero’s pool for a purpose other than paying to play a card, exhaust Beorn’s Welcome to add 1 resource to attached hero’s pool.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“I am Gandalf,” said the wizard. “Never heard of him,” growled the man. —The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("Beorning-Pony-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have attachments.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After Beorning Pony enters play, discard the top 5 cards of your deck. Then, you may spend 1 {sphere:Tactics} resource to add one of the cards discarded by this effect to your hand.</p><p class='flavor-text'>There was just room to get the ponies through with a squeeze, when they had been unpacked and unsaddled. —The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("Birna-MotR", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust Birna and spend 1 {sphere:Tactics} resource to put a <b><i>Beorning</i></b> ally from your discard pile into play. At the end of the phase, if that ally is still in play or in your discard pile, shuffle it into your deck.</p><p class='flavor-text'>In that last hour Beorn himself had appeared - no one knew how or from where. —The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("Bitter-Betrayal-MotR", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: The highest cost ally each player controls makes an immediate attack against the player that controls it. Until the end of these attacks, each of these cards loses the ally card type and gains the enemy card type. Then, remove those allies from the game. Add Bitter Betrayal to the victory display. This effect cannot be canceled.</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Coup-MotR", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Each player must choose: either raise your threat by 6, or discard a hero you control from play. Add Coup to the victory display. This effect cannot be canceled.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“When I heard that Shadowfax had come back riderless, I rejoiced at the return of the horse, but still more at the lack of the rider.” —Gríma, The Two Towers</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Curuwyn-The-Whisperer-MotR", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the beginning of the encounter phase, Curuwyn The Whisperer engages the player with the highest threat.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Curuwyn The Whisperer attacks, the defending player must either place 1 damage token on Massing at the Isen, or raise their threat by 4.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Cutthroat's-Strike-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'>While attached to an enemy, counts as a <b><i><b><i>Condition</i></b></i></b> attachment with the text: “<b>Forced</b>: When attached enemy attacks, it gets +5 {Attack} for that attack. Then, discard Cutthroat’s Strike.”</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Attach to the enemy in play with the lowest engagement cost without a copy of Cutthroat’s Strike attached.</p>");
            AddHtml("Deeping-stream-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Deeping-stream gets +3{PerPlayer} quest points.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the round, place 1 damage token on Massing at the Isen.</p><p class='flavor-text'>You must ride from your paltry camp beside the Glittering Caves, ere Ealdwulf sunders the kingdom of Rohan with his ambition.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Descendants-of-Beorn-MotR", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: When a <b><i>Beorning</i></b> ally you control leaves play, add 1 resource to a <b><i>Beorning</i></b> hero’s pool for each damage token that was on that ally (up to that ally’s printed hit points).</p><p class='flavor-text'>He tossed wolves and goblins from his path like straws and feathers. —The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("Felberen-Scion-of-Freca-MotR", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the beginning of the encounter phase, Felberen Scion of Freca engages the player with the most cards in hand.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Felberen Scion of Freca attacks, the defending player must either place 1 damage token on Massing at the Isen, or discard their hand.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Halls-of-Ealdwulf-MotR", "<p class='flavor-text'>You return to Aldburg to confront Ealdwulf. The traitor’s war party has already departed, but he has left behind a parting gift: two grimacing assassins, their blades sharp and glinting. </p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed</b>: Place 1{PerPlayer} damage tokens on Massing at the Isen. Add the remaining set aside <b><i>Assassin</i></b> enemies to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Halls-of-Ealdwulf-MotR", "<p class='flavor-text'>Ealdwulf’s assassins fall upon you ferociously, hacking and muttering with a cold sense of hate.</p><p class='main-text'> <b><i>Assassin</i></b> enemies are immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>This stage cannot be defeated while an <b><i>Assassin</i></b> enemy is in play. When this stage is defeated, the players win the game.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Host-of-Rohan-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. {keyword:Sentinel.}</p><p class='main-text'>The first player gains control of {self}.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> The players as a group may spend 2 resources to ready {self}. (Limit once per phase.)</p><p class='main-text'><b>If {self} leaves play, remove it from the game.</b></p><p class='flavor-text'>Safe from harm, the king is now free to dispatch his hosts.</p>");
            AddHtml("Hunting-Dogs-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Devoted. Cannot have attachments.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After a location with an attachment is explored, ready Hunting Dogs.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Hound is hungry, hare is fearful.”<br/>—Treebeard, The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Irensaga-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>Írensaga gets +2{PerPlayer} quest points. While Írensaga is the active location, players cannot play allies.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the round, if Írensaga is in the staging area, place 1 damage token on Massing at the Isen.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Lie-of-the-Land-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a location.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust a <b><i>Scout</i></b> character to place 1 progress on attached location. If that location is not explored by this effect, you may attach Lie of the Land to another location.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“We shall have to scour the lands all round for many long leagues before any move is made.”<br/>—Gandalf, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Massing-at-the-Isen-MotR", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the round, place 1 damage token here.</p><p class='main-text'><b>If there are 5 or more damage tokens here, remove 5 of them and reveal the top card of the Massing deck. If you cannot, the players lose the game.</b></p><p class='flavor-text'>Ealdwulf prepares his army for war on the banks of the Isen River.</p>");
            AddHtml("Oaths-of-the-Rohirrim-MotR", "<p class='flavor-text'>The traitor Ealdwulf is raising an army to usurp the throne of Thengel-King. </p><p class='main-text'> <b>Setup</b>: Shuffle the 5 cards with the <b><i>Massing</i></b> trait together into a Massing deck. Search the encounter deck for Írensaga, Orc-host Remnant, each <b><i>Assassin</i></b> enemy, and each <b><i>Mustering</i></b> side quest and set them aside, out of play. The first player adds Massing at the Isen to the staging area and makes Deeping-stream the active location. Each player searches the encounter deck for a different <b><i>Traitor</i></b> enemy and adds it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Oaths-of-the-Rohirrim-MotR", "<p class='flavor-text'>If you hope to meet Ealdwulf’s challenge, you must spend the coming months rallying the scattered hosts of Rohan. His long-planned conspiracy gives him a head start, but your swift horses may yet carry you across many leagues to bring warning to those lords who remain loyal to Thengel’s banner.</p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed</b>: Each player must choose: either place 1 damage token on Massing at the Isen, or reveal an encounter card.</p>");
            AddHtml("Orator's-Hall-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>The players cannot travel to Orator’s Hall. Progress cannot be placed here by player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Planning Action</b>: Exhaust a hero you control to place progress on Orator’s Hall equal to that hero’s printed {Willpower}. If Orator’s Hall is explored by this effect, remove 1 damage token from Massing at the Isen. Any player may trigger this effect.</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Orc-host-Remnant-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>X is the number of damage tokens on Orc-host Remnant. Cannot have attachments. Only the engaged player may declare attackers or defenders against Orc-host Remnant.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Orc-host Remnant takes any amount of damage, return it to the staging area.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Osbera-SideA-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Reduce the total {Threat} in the staging area by 1 for each damaged <b><i>Beorning</i></b> character you control (limit –5 {Threat}).</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After you engage an enemy, spend 1 resource from Osbera’s pool to flip her.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“I don’t need your service, thank you. But I expect you need mine.” —Beorn, The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("Osbera-SideB-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have restricted attachments. If you are not engaged with an enemy, flip Osbera.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: Deal 1 damage to a <b><i>Beorning</i></b> character you control to cancel 2 points of damage just dealt to a character you control. (Limit once per round.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Not eaten up by Wargs or goblins or wicked bears yet I see.” —Beorn, The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("Pernicious-Plotter-MotR", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the round, place 1 damage token on Massing at the Isen.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Either place 1 damage token on Massing at the Isen, or return attacking enemy to the staging area after this attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Plains-of-Strife-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Vast.</p><p class='main-text'>While Plains of Strife is in the staging area, <b><i>Rohan</i></b> enemies get +1 {Threat}.</p><p class='main-text'>While Plains of Strife is the active location, <b><i>Rohan</i></b> enemies get +1 {Attack}.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: If attacking enemy has the <b><i>Rohan</i></b> trait, it makes an additional attack against you after this one.</p>");
            AddHtml("Raven-Clan-Sharpshooter-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>While any player has 3 or more cards in hand, Raven Clan Sharpshooter gains Archery 3.</p><p class='main-text'>While any player has 5 or more cards in hand, Raven Clan Sharpshooter cannot be optionally engaged.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Attacking enemy gets +2 {Attack}.</p>");
            AddHtml("Raven-Clan-Warchief-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot have attachments.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When Raven Clan Warchief attacks, place 1 damage token on Massing at the Isen.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When Raven Clan Warchief is defeated, shuffle him and the encounter discard pile into the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Road-to-Ruin-MotR", "<p class='flavor-text'>The regrouping orcish warband threatens the embattled horsebreakers on the road.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: The first player adds Orc-host Remnant to the staging area and deals 4 damage to it. Each other player reveals an encounter card.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the round, deal 1 damage to Orc-host Remnant.</p><p class='main-text'><b>This stage cannot be defeated unless Orc-host Remnant is in the victory display.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Rowan-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After you play an attachment on a location, add 1 resource to the pool of a hero you control. (Limit once per round.)</p><p class='main-text'><b>Quest Action</b>: Choose a player to take control of the first player token. Each player can only be chosen once per game.</p>");
            AddHtml("Scattered-to-the-Winds-MotR", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Each player chooses half the non-objective allies they control (rounded up) and shuffles them into their owner’s deck. Add Scattered to the Winds to the victory display. This effect cannot be canceled.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“We shall all be scattered and lost.”<br/>—Aragorn, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Seeking-Support-MotR", "<p class='flavor-text'>As you journey across Rohan, you find her in distress. None may ride to your aid until you locate the éored dispatched to the White Mountains, beseech the aid of Thengel, and rout the orcish horse-thieves marauding the countryside. Wherever you go, Ealdwulf’s agents seek to waylay and beguile you. </p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed</b>: The first player chooses a set aside <b><i>Mustering</i></b> side quest and reveals it.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Seeking-Support-MotR", "<p class='flavor-text'>With each dawn, Ealdwulf’s army grows more prepared. You must make haste.</p><p class='main-text'> Seeking Support cannot be chosen as the current quest during the quest phase.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When a <b><i>Mustering</i></b> side quest is completed, flip it over and reveal it. Then, the first player chooses another set aside <b><i>Mustering</i></b> side quest and reveals it. <b>If the first player is unable to do so, advance to stage 3.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Smeohbrand-Rogue-of-Orthanc-MotR", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the beginning of the encounter phase, Smeóhbrand Rogue of Orthanc engages the player who controls the fewest characters.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Smeóhbrand Rogue of Orthanc attacks for the first time each round, he makes an additional attack. The engaged player may place 1 damage token on Massing at the Isen to cancel this effect.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Sniveling-Courtier-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Indestructible.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Sniveling Courtier makes an undefended attack against you, either place 1 damage token on Massing at the Isen, or raise your threat by 3.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Refresh Action</b>: The engaged player may spend 2 resources to discard Sniveling Courtier.</p>");
            AddHtml("Spiteful-Hunter-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Spiteful Hunter gets +1 {Attack} for each exhausted hero controlled by the defending player.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Either place 1 damage token on Massing at the Isen, or attacking enemy gets +3 {Attack}.</p>");
            AddHtml("Subdued-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a damaged enemy engaged with you. Limit 1 per enemy.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached enemy gets −4 {Attack}.</p><p class='flavor-text'>His miserable enemy lay grovelling on the stones whimpering. —The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Far-Bank-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. The players cannot travel to The Far Bank.</p><p class='main-text'>Enemies in play get +5 engagement cost.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After a player optionally engages an enemy, that enemy makes an immediate attack against them.</p>");
            AddHtml("Traitor's-Redoubt-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel</b>: Each player searches the encounter deck and discard pile for a <b><i>Traitor</i></b> enemy and puts it into play engaged with them.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: When Traitor’s Redoubt leaves play as an explored location, remove 1 damage token from Massing at the Isen.</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Winter-in-Westemnet-MotR", "<p class='flavor-text'>Éomund’s scouts have ranged far and wide in their hunt for Gálmód. News of his capture will surely bring new allies to your cause.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: The first player adds Írensaga to the staging area. Each other player reveals an encounter card.</p><p class='main-text'>Enemies get +1 {Threat} and do not make engagement checks.</p><p class='main-text'><b>This stage cannot be defeated unless Írensaga is in the victory display.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Without-My-Hat-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Limit 1 copy of Without My Hat in the victory display.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Add Without My Hat to the victory display to search your collection for an attachment. If no copy of that attachment was in your deck during setup, add it to your hand.</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Woodmen's-Outpost-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a location. Limit 1 per location.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After attached location is explored, each character controlled by the first player gets +1 {Attack} and +1 {Defense} until the end of the round.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“…even the Wargs dared not attack them if there were many together, or in the bright day.” —The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("Folcwine-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>Attack to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust {self} to either ready attached hero, or give attached hero +1 {Willpower}, +1 {Attack}, and +1 {Defense} until the end of the phase.</p><p class='flavor-text'>The last foal of Felaróf the Mighty, wrested from the clutches of the orcish horde.</p>");
            AddHtml("Devoted-Determination-MotR", "<p class='main-text'>The first ally played by each player each round does not require a resource match.</p><p class='flavor-text'>With the conspirator Gálmód in chains, allies come to honor their oaths.</p>");
        }

        private void BloodInTheIsen()
        {
            AddHtml("A-Fair-Exchange-BitI", "<p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Discard a unique card from your hand that shares a title with a card in play to search your deck for a different unique card and add it to your hand. Shuffle your deck.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“There is nothing like looking, if you want to find something…” —Thorin Oakenshield, The Hobbit</p>");
            AddHtml("Anduril-BitI", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero with 4 or more <b><i>Traits</i></b>.</p><p class='main-text'>Restricted. If attached hero is Aragorn, he gains a {sphere:Leadership} resource icon.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gets +1 {Willpower}, +1 {Attack}, and +1 {Defense}.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust Andúril to ready attached hero.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“You shall not be sheathed again until the last battle is fought.” —Aragorn, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Aragorn-BitI", "<p class='main-text'>Aragorn gains a resource icon matching each <b><i>Title</i></b> attachment attached to him.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup</b>: Search your collection for a <b><i>Title</i></b> attachment with a printed cost of 1 and attach it to Aragorn.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Ready a <b><i>Title</i></b> attachment with a printed cost of 1 attached to Aragorn. (Limit once per round.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Chaos-and-Confusion-BitI", "<p class='flavor-text'>The voices and the clink of weapons and harness were very close. Frodo and Sam loosened their small swords in their sheaths. Flight was impossible.<br>—The Two Towers</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After engaging a <b><i>Dunland</i></b> enemy causes its <b>Forced</b> effect to trigger, resolve that <b>Forced</b> effect a second time. (Limit once per enemy per phase.)</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Chieftain-of-the-North-BitI", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a <b><i>Ranger</i></b> hero or Aragorn. Attached character gains the <b><i>Warrior</i></b> trait.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust Chieftain of the North to choose an attacking ally that shares a <b><i>Trait</i></b> with the attached character. Either ready that ally or give it +1 {Attack} for that attack.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Here is Aragorn son of Arathorn, chieftain of the Dúnedain…” —Faramir, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Contested-Battleground-BitI", "<p class='main-text'>Doomed 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Contested Battleground becomes the active location, either remove 1 resource token from the <b><i>Fords</i></b> objective, or the current quest gains battle until Contested Battleground leaves play.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: After this attack, raise your threat by X, where X is the amount of damage dealt by this attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Coordinated-Assault-BitI", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: The first player must choose 3 different things they control to discard: 1 resource, 1 ally, 1 character attachment, 1 enemy attachment, 1 location attachment, 1 player side quest in the staging area, or 1 random card from their hand.</p>");
            AddHtml("Crossing-the-Fords-BitI", "<p class='flavor-text'>The traitor Ealdwulf has manipulated a host of Dunlendings and traitorous Rohirrim in a bid for the throne of Rohan. His armies have massed on the banks of the Isen where the Dunlendings prepare to ford. </p><p class='main-text'> <b>Setup</b>: Set Ealdwulf aside, out of play. Add the <b><i>Fords</i></b> objective to the staging area, Narrow Crossing side faceup. The first player adds Grimrede and West Bank to the staging area. Each other player searches the encounter deck for a different enemy and adds it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Crossing-the-Fords-BitI", "<p class='flavor-text'>Ealdwulf must be stopped. Now is the time to cross the river and put an end to this foolhardy campaign, lest Rohan be drowned in blood.</p><p class='main-text'> Grimrede cannot be optionally engaged or take damage.</p><p class='main-text'><b>This stage cannot be defeated while West Bank is in play.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Defensive-Outcrop-BitI", "<p class='main-text'><b><i>Dunland</i></b> enemies get +1 {Defense}. This ability does not stack with other copies of Defensive Outcrop.</p><p class='main-text'>While Defensive Outcrop is the active location, <b><i>Dunland</i></b> enemies get +1 {Attack}.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Until the end of the phase, when a character is declared as an attacker against this enemy, deal 1 damage to that character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dunland-Axe-hand-BitI", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Dunland Axe-hand engages you, either remove 1 resource token from the <b><i>Fords</i></b> objective, or deal 2 damage among characters you control.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Attacking enemy gets +3 {Attack}. You may discard X cards from your hand to reduce this amount by X.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ealdwulf-BitI", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>Ealdwulf gets +2 hit points for each resource token on him.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When a resource token would be removed from Hasty Pursuit, move it to Ealdwulf instead.</p>{victory:15}");
            AddHtml("Elendilmir-BitI", "<p class='main-text'>Guarded (location).</p><p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'>Replace each instance of “once per phase” or “once per round” in the attached character’s text box with “twice per phase” or “twice per round” respectively.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust Aragorn to discard the location guarding Elendilmir. Then, attach Elendilmir to Aragorn.</p>");
            AddHtml("Elessar-BitI", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a <b><i>Noble</i></b> hero or Aragorn. Attached character gains the <b><i>Gondor</i></b> trait. If attached character is Aragorn, he gains the <b><i>Noble</i></b> trait.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust Elessar to choose an ally that is defending an attack and shares a <b><i>Trait</i></b> with the attached character. Either ready that ally or give it +1 {Defense} for that attack.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Say not The Lords of Gondor. Say The King Elessar.”<br/>—Prince Imrahil, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Estel-BitI", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a <b><i>Dúnedain</i></b> hero or Aragorn. Attached character gains the <b><i>Noldor</i></b> trait.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust Estel and discard 1 card from your hand to search the top X cards of your deck for 1 card and add it to your hand. Shuffle your deck. X is the number of <b><i>Traits</i></b> on the attached character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Fleet-footed-Dunlending-BitI", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Fleet-footed Dunlending engages you, discard an attachment you control.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Discard the highest cost attachment attached to the defending character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Gilraen-BitI", "<p class='main-text'><b>Setup</b>: You may choose to give Gilraen –2 {Willpower} and up to 2 other <b><i>Dúnedain</i></b> heroes +2 {Willpower} until the end of the game.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Turn a shadow card dealt to an enemy faceup. Then, you may deal that enemy 1 additional faceup shadow card to draw 1 card. (Limit once per phase.)</p><p class='flavor-text'>“I gave Hope to the Dúnedain, I have kept no hope for myself.”<br/>—The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Grey-Companion-BitI", "<p class='main-text'>Sentinel.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: When you play Grey Companion from your hand, exhaust X <b><i>Title</i></b> attachments you control to reduce its cost by X.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“But I did not summon you,” said Aragorn, “save only in wish.” —The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Grimrede-BitI", "<p class='main-text'>X is 1{PerPlayer}. Immune to player card effects. Each player’s threat cannot be reduced by more than 1 each round.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When any number of resource tokens would be placed on the <b><i>Fords</i></b> objective, reduce that number by 1 unless each player deals 1 damage to an undamaged character they control.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Hasty-Pursuit-BitI", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the planning phase, the first player removes 1 resource token from Hasty Pursuit.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After resolving the above <b>Forced</b> effect, if the total printed cost of all cards you control is greater than the number of resource tokens here, raise your threat by the difference. (Each player must resolve this effect.)</p>");
            AddHtml("Heavy-Losses-BitI", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Each player may discard any number of characters they control. Then, each player raises their threat by 1 for each damaged character they control. Each player that did not raise their threat this way must deal 1 damage to 3 different characters they control.</p>");
            AddHtml("Narrow-Crossing-BitI", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the planning phase, the first player places 3 resource tokens on Narrow Crossing.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After resolving the above <b>Forced</b> effect, if the total printed cost of all cards you control is greater than the number of resource tokens here, raise your threat by the difference. (Each player must resolve this effect.)</p>");
            AddHtml("North-South-Road-BitI", "<p class='main-text'><b>Travel</b>: Each player deals 1 damage to a character they control.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After North-South Road leaves play as an explored location, place 1 resource token on the <b><i>Fords</i></b> objective.</p><p class='flavor-text'>…the stream from above passed out, and the road beside it ran down… —The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("Open-Rebellion-BitI", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: The first player deals 1 damage to each hero they control with at least 1 resource in its pool, then raises their threat by 1 for each <b><i>Noble</i></b> hero damaged this way.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack} (+2 {Attack} instead if the defending character is <b><i>Noble</i></b>).</p>");
            AddHtml("Rohan-Renegade-BitI", "<p class='main-text'>While a hero is defending against Rohan Renegade, that hero does not count its {Defense}.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: After this attack, attacking enemy engages the next player, then makes an immediate attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("Spurned-Hillman-BitI", "<p class='main-text'>Doomed 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Spurned Hillman engages you, raise your threat by 1.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Death to the Forgoil!” —The Two Towers</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Battle-is-Joined-BitI", "<p class='flavor-text'>As you wade into the river, your foes attempt to repel you with sling and spear. The Dunlending chieftain Grimrede shoulders his axe and steps before you, growling. “The land of green hills shall be ours again. It was taken from us by iron and flame. So will we reclaim it.”</p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed</b>: Shuffle the encounter discard pile into the encounter deck and discard cards until X enemies are discarded. X is 1 less than the number of players. Add each enemy discarded this way to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Battle-is-Joined-BitI", "<p class='main-text'> Grimrede engages the first player. Enemies get –10 engagement cost and cannot be optionally engaged.</p><p class='main-text'>Narrow Crossing cannot have more than 15 resource tokens on it.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Grimrede cannot be defeated while this stage has any quest points remaining. This stage cannot be defeated unless Grimrede is in the victory display.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("The-Flight-of-Ealdwulf-BitI", "<p class='flavor-text'>As the tide of battle turns, the traitor Ealdwulf wheels in retreat. The warlord rushes toward the wilderness, leaving his men to fight and die for their master’s hopeless crusade. </p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed</b>: End the current phase. The first player adds Ealdwulf to the staging area. Each other player searches the encounter deck and discard pile for a copy of Rohan Renegade and engages it, if able. Shuffle the encounter deck. Flip Narrow Crossing over, keeping any resource tokens on it.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Flight-of-Ealdwulf-BitI", "<p class='flavor-text'>The traitor’s horse is fleet of foot, and battle spills across both banks of the river. Ealdwulf must be captured and brought before King Thengel to face justice.</p><p class='main-text'> Ealdwulf cannot be optionally engaged while this stage has any quest points remaining.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After a player reduces their threat by any amount, that player must distribute an equal amount of damage among characters they control.</p><p class='main-text'><b>This stage cannot be defeated while Ealdwulf is in play. When Ealdwulf is defeated, the players have thwarted the traitor’s plot and win the game.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("The-Renewer-BitI", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a <b><i>Gondor</i></b> hero or Aragorn. Attached character gains the <b><i>Healer</i></b> trait.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust The Renewer to choose a questing ally that shares a <b><i>Trait</i></b> with the attached character. Either ready that ally and heal 1 damage from it or give it +1 {Willpower} until the end of the phase.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“The hands of the king are the hands of a healer.”<br/>—Ioreth, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("West-Bank-BitI", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'>Narrow Crossing cannot have more than 10 resource tokens on it.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the round, raise each player’s threat by 1.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Go not to the Fords of Isen, and do not tarry in the plain!” —Gandalf, The Two Towers</p>{victory:1}");
        }

        private void TheScouringOfTheShire()
        {
            AddHtml("Frodo-Baggins-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response:</b> After {self} commits to the quest, spend 1 resource from his resource pool to ready another unique character committed to the quest. If you quest successfully this phase, reduce your threat by 1.</p>");
            AddHtml("Against-the-Rules-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Exhaust each character with 3 or more printed {Attack}. Each player that exhausted no characters by this effect must choose and exhaust 1 character they control.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: If your threat is higher than the attacking enemy’s engagement cost, the attacking enemy gets +2 {Attack}. Otherwise, raise your threat by 2.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ambush-Sharkey's-Men-TSotS", "<p class='flavor-text'>“I warned you not to come back here. I warn you again: you are standing in the light.” —Merry, The Return of the King</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After a Gang of Ruffians is defeated, flip this card over and reveal it.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the quest phase, if no progress was placed on Ambush Sharkey’s Men this round, search the encounter deck and discard pile for a <b><i>Ruffian</i></b> enemy and add it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Awake-Fire-Foes-Awake-TSotS", "<p class='flavor-text'>He had not gone far when he heard a sudden clear horn-call go up ringing into the sky. Far over hill and field it echoed. —The Return of the King</p><p class='main-text'><b>Encounter Action</b>: Engage a <b><i>Ruffian</i></b> enemy in the encounter discard pile. Any player may trigger this effect.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After the first player destroys an enemy, place 2 progress here.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When this quest is defeated, flip this card over and reveal it.</p>");
            AddHtml("Brandywine-Gate-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Brandywine Gate is explored, each player searches the encounter deck for a Feather-capped Shirriff and engages it. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p><p class='flavor-text'>At either end of the Bridge there was a great spiked gate. —The Return of the King</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("Brick-Building-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>While Brick Building is in the staging area, characters cannot be healed.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Deal 2 damage to the defending character or raise your threat by 2.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Through rows of new mean houses along each side of the road, they saw the new mill in all its frowning and dirty ugliness. —The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Bright-Mail-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gets +1 {Defense} (+2 {Defense} instead if attached hero is a <b><i>Hobbit</i></b>).</p><p class='flavor-text'>“They wouldn’t go for armed folk, with swords and helmets and shields and all. Make them think twice, that would.” —Barliman Butterbur, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Curse-Upon-the-Shire-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Each player must choose: either raise your threat by 1 for each ally you control, or discard 2 allies you control.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Long may your land be short of leaf!”<br/>—Saruman, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("East-Road-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>Peril.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Either raise your threat by 2 or East Road gains surge.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Round a bend, about a furlong from the main road, they met a stout barrier of old farm-carts upturned. That halted them. —The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Escorted-Prisoners-TSotS", "<p class='flavor-text'>After a brief encounter on the road with the disgraced Saruman, Frodo and his companions encounter resistance and hostility from the Shirriffs of the Shire. </p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed</b>: Make Brandywine Gate the active location and add Three-Farthing Stone to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Escorted-Prisoners-TSotS", "<p class='flavor-text'>“It’s the Chief’s orders that you’re to come along quiet. We’re going to take you to Bywater and hand you over to the Chief’s Men.” —The Return of the King</p><p class='main-text'> This stage cannot have more than 12 progress tokens on it.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the quest phase, if no progress was placed here as a result of questing successfully, the first player raises their threat by 3. If more than 3 progress was placed, each player engaged with 2 or more <b><i>Shirriff</i></b> enemies may discard 1 of them.</p><p class='main-text'><b>The players cannot advance while Three-Farthing Stone is in play.</i></b></p>");
            AddHtml("Feather-capped-Shirriff-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>Indestructible. Damage dealt by Feather-capped Shirriff to your characters is instead assigned as an increase to your threat.</p><p class='main-text'>While the engaged player’s threat is higher than Feather-capped Shirriff’s engagement cost, Feather-capped Shirriff gets +1 {Attack}.</p>");
            AddHtml("Find-the-Gaffer-TSotS", "<p class='flavor-text'>“I want to see him. That Boss and that Sharkey, as they spoke of, they might do a mischief up there before the morning.” —Sam, The Return of the King</p><p class='main-text'><b>Travel Action</b>: Exhaust a hero you control to place 2 progress on Find the Gaffer. You cannot declare defenders or attackers this round. Any player may trigger this effect.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When this quest is defeated, flip this card over and reveal it.</p>");
            AddHtml("Escorted-Prisoners-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After Frodo Baggins commits to the quest, spend 1 resource from his resource pool to ready another unique character committed to the quest. If you quest successfully this phase, reduce your threat by 1.</p>");
            AddHtml("Frodo-Baggins-Fellowship-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>The first player gains control of Frodo Baggins.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After Frodo Baggins is declared as a defender, spend 1 [fellowship] resource to reduce your threat by the attacking enemy’s {Threat}. Until the end of the round, that enemy cannot take damage.</p><p class='main-text'><b>If Frodo Baggins leaves play, the players lose the game.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Gang-of-Ruffians-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: When Gang of Ruffians would deal damage during an attack, instead distribute that damage among characters controlled by the defending player.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Gang of Ruffians attacks, if the attack destroyed at least 1 of your characters, discard 1 card at random from your hand and raise your threat by 1.</p>");
            AddHtml("Grima's-Choice-TSotS", "<p class='flavor-text'>“Wormtongue!” called Frodo. “You need not follow him. I know of no evil you have done to me. You can have rest and food here for a while, until you are stronger and can go your own ways.” —The Return of the King</p><p class='main-text'>X is 3{PerPlayer}. This stage cannot be chosen as the current quest while The Very Last Stroke has remaining quest points.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When this stage is defeated, discard Saruman from play.</p>");
            AddHtml("Heightened-Stature-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gains +2 hit points (+3 hit points instead if attached hero is a <b><i>Hobbit</i></b>).</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust Heightened Stature to heal 1 damage from attached hero.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Mortals cannot go drinking ent-draughts and expect no more to come of them than of a pot of beer.”<br/>—Gimli, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Hidden-Blade-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Saruman makes an immediate attack against each player in turn order. Allies cannot defend against Saruman.</p><p class='flavor-text'>A knife flashed in his hand, and he stabbed swiftly.<br/>—The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Highway-Robber-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When Highway Robber attacks you, either discard 1 resource from a hero you control or Highway Robber gets +2 {Attack} for this attack.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Scaring Bree-land peasants, and bullying bewildered hobbits, had been their work. —The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Hobbiton-Road-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Hobbiton Road leaves play, put a <b><i>Ruffian</i></b> enemy in the discard pile into play engaged with a player.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Deal 1 damage to the defending character or raise your threat by 1.</p>");
            AddHtml("Into-the-West-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'> You cannot use this contract unless you have destroyed The One Ring and won <i>The Scouring of the Shire</i> in campaign mode.</p><p class='main-text'>Your deck must contain an equal number of cards with a printed cost of 1, 2, 3, 4, and 5.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup</b>: Search the top 10 cards of your deck for an ally with a printed cost of 3 or less and put it into play. Shuffle your deck and flip this card over.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“I tried to save the Shire, and it has been saved, but not for me.” —Frodo Baggins, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml2("Into-the-West-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'> Into the West is immune to the effects of other cards and cannot leave your control or leave play. Allies you play from your hand cannot have their cost reduced by more than 2.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the beginning of the quest phase, attach Into the West to an ally you control, if able.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the refresh phase, distribute X resources among heroes you control, where X is the attached card’s printed cost. Remove the attached card from the game and draw 1 card.</p>");
            AddHtml("Many-Partings-TSotS", "<p class='flavor-text'>As they came out again into the open country at sundown they overtook an old man leaning on a staff, and he was clothed in rags of grey or dirty white, and at his heels went another beggar, slouching and whining.<br>—The Return of the King </p><p class='main-text'> <b>Setup</b>: Create the Sharkey deck (see insert). Set Saruman, Brandywine Gate, Three-Farthing Stone, and each encounter side quest aside, out of play. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Many-Partings-TSotS", "<p class='flavor-text'>“You don’t care what a beggar lacks, do you? For you have all you want, food and fine clothes, and the best weed for your pipes. Oh yes, I know! I know where it comes from. You would not give a pipeful to a beggar, would you?”<br>—Saruman, The Return of the King</p><p class='main-text'> <b>Action</b>: Exhaust a non-[fellowship] hero and discard a resource token from its pool. Then, add 2 resources to the set-aside Saruman.</p><p class='main-text'><b>At the end of the planning phase, advance to the next quest stage.</i></b></p>");
            AddHtml("Muster-the-Tooks-TSotS", "<p class='flavor-text'>“It’s only fourteen miles or so over the fields. I’ll bring you back an army of Tooks in the morning.” —Pippin, The Return of the King</p><p class='main-text'>X is 4{PerPlayer}. While Muster the Tooks is the current quest, heroes cannot commit to the quest.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When this quest is defeated, flip this card over and reveal it.</p>");
            AddHtml("Once-Beloved-Place-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Each location gets +1 {Threat} until the end of the round. If there are fewer than 1{PerPlayer} locations in the staging area, discard cards from the encounter deck until a location is discarded and add it to the staging area.</p><p class='flavor-text'>All the chestnuts were gone. The banks and hedgerows were broken. —The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("One-Ill-Turn-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Deal 1 damage to each exhausted character. Until the end of the round, characters cannot be healed.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“It would have been a sharper lesson, if only you had given me a little more time.”<br/>—Saruman, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Raise-the-Shire-TSotS", "<p class='flavor-text'>The Shire has fallen under the sway of a gang of ruffians led by a man known as “Sharkey”. Frodo and his friends must prepare Bywater and raise support to contest him. </p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed</b>: Randomly select 3 of the set aside non-<b><i>Doom</i></b> side quests and put them into play (4 side quests instead if there are 3 or 4 players).</p>");
            AddHtml2("Raise-the-Shire-TSotS", "<p class='flavor-text'>As soon as they saw how things were, most of them took off their feathers and joined in the revolt. —The Return of the King</p><p class='main-text'> <b>Forced</b>: After a side quest is defeated, search the encounter deck and discard pile for a <b><i>Shirriff</i></b> enemy and add it to the staging area. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the round, place 1 resource token here and raise each player’s threat by the total number of resource tokens here. Then, the players may choose to advance to the next quest stage.</p>");
            AddHtml("Rouse-the-Cottons-TSotS", "<p class='flavor-text'>“Come on now, lads! Bywater is up! We must be in it!”<br>—Tom Cotton, The Return of the King</p><p class='main-text'>While Rouse the Cottons is the current quest, allies cannot commit to the quest.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When this quest is defeated, flip this card over and reveal it.</p>");
            AddHtml("Roused-Hobbits-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>While attached, counts as a <b><i><b><i>Condition</i></b></i></b> attachment with the text: “Attached card loses indestructible and the enemy card type and gains the ally card type with {Willpower} equal to its {Threat}. If either attached card or Roused Hobbits would leave play, remove both cards from the game.”</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Choose 1 player to take control of a <b><i>Shirriff</i></b> enemy engaged with them and attach Roused Hobbits to it (if there are no engaged <b><i>Shirriff</i></b> enemies, remove Roused Hobbits from the game).</p>");
            AddHtml("Roused-Hobbits-2-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>While attached, counts as a <b><i><b><i>Condition</i></b></i></b> attachment with the text: “Attached card loses indestructible and the enemy card type and gains the ally card type with {Willpower} equal to its {Threat}. If either attached card or Roused Hobbits would leave play, remove both cards from the game.”</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Choose 1 player to take control of a <b><i>Shirriff</i></b> enemy engaged with them and attach Roused Hobbits to it (if there are no engaged <b><i>Shirriff</i></b> enemies, remove Roused Hobbits from the game).</p>");
