            AddHtml("Roused-Hobbits-6-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>While attached, counts as a <b><i><b><i>Condition</i></b></i></b> attachment with the text: “Attached card loses indestructible and the enemy card type and gains the ally card type with {Willpower} equal to its {Threat}. If either attached card or Roused Hobbits would leave play, remove both cards from the game.”</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Choose 1 player to take control of a <b><i>Shirriff</i></b> enemy engaged with them and attach Roused Hobbits to it (if there are no engaged <b><i>Shirriff</i></b> enemies, remove Roused Hobbits from the game).</p>");
            AddHtml("Roused-Hobbits-7-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>While attached, counts as a <b><i><b><i>Condition</i></b></i></b> attachment with the text: “Attached card loses indestructible and the enemy card type and gains the ally card type with {Willpower} equal to its {Threat}. If either attached card or Roused Hobbits would leave play, remove both cards from the game.”</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Choose 1 player to take control of a <b><i>Shirriff</i></b> enemy engaged with them and attach Roused Hobbits to it (if there are no engaged <b><i>Shirriff</i></b> enemies, remove Roused Hobbits from the game).</p>");
            AddHtml("Saruman-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>Immune to player card effects. Cannot be engaged. <b><i>Sharkey</i></b> card effects cannot be cancelled.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the staging step, add 1{PerPlayer} resource tokens to Saruman and reveal the top card of the Sharkey deck. Then, put the revealed card on the bottom of the Sharkey deck.</p>");
            AddHtml("Scatha's-Horn-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust Scatha’s Horn to choose an attacking enemy. Until the end of the phase, that enemy gets −1 {Attack} (−2 {Attack} instead if the defending character is a <b><i>Hobbit</i></b> hero).</p><p class='flavor-text'>“He that blows it at need shall set fear in the hearts of his enemies.” —Éowyn, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Set-up-Barriers-TSotS", "<p class='flavor-text'>Others at Merry’s orders were setting up barriers across the road at each end of the village. —The Return of the King</p><p class='main-text'>Players cannot draw cards.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Spend 1{PerPlayer} resources as a group to place 3 progress on Set up Barriers.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When this quest is completed, the first player discards all resources from each hero they control. Then, flip this card over and reveal it.</p>");
            AddHtml("Sharkey's-Men-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Each enemy in play gets +1 {Attack} until the end of the round. If there are fewer than 1{PerPlayer} <b><i>Ruffian</i></b> enemies in play, discard cards from the encounter deck until a <b><i>Ruffian</i></b> enemy is discarded and add it to the staging area.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: If the attacking enemy is a <b><i>Ruffian</i></b>, it makes an additional attack. The defending player may discard an ally they control to cancel this effect.</p>");
            AddHtml("Shirriff-House-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Shirriff House becomes the active location, exhaust each character with 2 or more printed {Attack}.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Shirriff House leaves play, the first player must search the encounter deck and discard pile for a <b><i>Shirriff</i></b> enemy and engage it, if able. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Inside it was damp and cheerless. —The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Star-like-Gem-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>Attach to a hero.</p><p class='main-text'>Attached hero gets +1 {Willpower}.</p><p class='main-text'>If attached hero is a <b><i>Hobbit</i></b>, it does not exhaust to quest.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“When the memory of the fear and the darkness troubles you, this will bring you aid.”<br/>—Arwen, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Take-Him-Lads-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Raise each player’s threat by 4. Then, each player discards an ally they control and reduces their threat by X, where X is the printed cost of their discarded ally.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: If your threat is higher than the attacking enemy’s engagement cost, the attacking enemy gets +2 {Attack}. Otherwise, raise your threat by 2.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Battle-of-Bywater-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed</b>: Shuffle the encounter discard pile into the encounter deck. Remove each <b><i>Shirriff</i></b> enemy in play and in the encounter deck from the game. The first player searches the encounter deck and victory display for 1 copy of Gang of Ruffians and engages it. Then, each player not engaged with a <b><i>Ruffian</i></b> enemy searches the encounter deck for a <b><i>Ruffian</i></b> enemy and engages it. Shuffle the encounter deck. Discard cards from the encounter deck until X enemies are discarded, and add those enemies to the staging area. X is the number of encounter side quests in play. Then, remove those side quests from the game.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Battle-of-Bywater-TSotS", "<p class='flavor-text'>The ruffians could not now be cowed so easily. A few of them obeyed, but were immediately set on by their fellows. A score or more broke back and charged the wagons. —The Return of the King</p><p class='main-text'> While any <b><i>Ruffian</i></b> enemy in play has any remaining hit points, all <b><i>Ruffian</i></b> enemies gain indestructible.</p><p class='main-text'><b>If there are no enemies in play, advance to the next quest stage.</i></b></p>");
            AddHtml("The-Lockholes-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>Peril.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Remove all attachments and discard all tokens from the highest cost ally you control and attach it facedown under The Lockholes.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After The Lockholes is explored, return the attached ally to its owner’s control, faceup and ready.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“Lockholes, as they call ‘em: the old storage-tunnels at Michel Delving that they’ve made into prisons for those as stand up to them.” —Tom Cotton, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Scouring-of-the-Shire-Campaign-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'> You are playing Campaign Mode.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Setup</b>: Each player may change heroes they control without incurring the +1 threat penalty. The players have earned the boon cards Star-like Gem, Bright Mail, Scatha’s Horn, and Heightened Stature. Each player chooses one and adds it to their hand. If any of these boon cards remain unchosen, one player may choose one of them and shuffle it into their deck. Remove any unchosen cards from the game. Remove Gwaihir and all burdens from the campaign pool. Attach Grievous Wound from The Road Darkens to Frodo Baggins.</p><p class='flavor-text'>It was after nightfall when, wet and tired, the travellers came at last to the Brandywine, and they found the way barred.<br/>—The Return of the King </p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Scouring-of-the-Shire-Campaign-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'> <b>Resolution</b>: Each player has earned the Into the West contract card and may now use it in their decks.</p><p class='flavor-text'>Then Elrond and Galadriel rode on; for the Third Age was over, and the Days of the Rings were passed, and an end was come of the story and song of those times. With them went many Elves of the High Kindred who would no longer stay in Middle-earth; and among them, filled with a sadness that was yet blessed and without bitterness, rode Sam, and Frodo, and Bilbo, and the Elves delighted to honour them.<br/>—The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Very-Last-Stroke-TSotS", "<p class='flavor-text'>With Sharkey’s forces scattered, Frodo sets out to confront him. To Frodo’s surprise, he is greeted by none other than Saruman, with Gríma Wormtongue cowering nearby. </p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed</b>: If it is the combat phase, end the phase. Add Saruman and Gríma’s Choice to the staging area.</p>");
            AddHtml2("The-Very-Last-Stroke-TSotS", "<p class='flavor-text'>“You are wise, and cruel. You have robbed my revenge of sweetness, and now I must go hence in bitterness.” —Saruman, The Return of the King</p><p class='main-text'> X is 6{PerPlayer}. This stage cannot have more progress than the number of resource tokens on Saruman.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Exhaust a hero and discard 1 resource token from its pool to add 1 resource to Saruman.</p><p class='main-text'><b>This stage cannot be defeated while Saruman is in play. When this stage is defeated, the players win the game.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Thieving-Ruffian-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When Thieving Ruffian attacks you, raise your threat by 1 for each attachment on the defending character.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“So that’s your tone, is it? Change it, or we’ll change it for you.” —The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Three-Farthing-Stone-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>X is 3{PerPlayer}. Immune to player card effects. The players cannot travel here unless there are 12 progress tokens on Escorted “Prisoners”.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After Three-Farthing Stone leaves play as an explored location, each player reduces their threat by 3.</p><p class='flavor-text'>They were hungry and very footsore and they could not stand the pace. —The Return of the King</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("To-the-Road-Again-Worm-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Discard cards from the encounter deck until a location is discarded and add that location to the staging area. Deal X damage among characters in play. X is twice the number of locations in play (3 times the number of locations in play if there are 3 or more players).</p><p class='flavor-text'>Saruman laughed. “You do what Sharkey says, always, don’t you, Worm?” —The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Voice-of-Saruman-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Randomly select 1 ally controlled by each player, if able. Each player deals X damage to one of their heroes, where X is their chosen ally’s {Attack}, then discards that ally. If a player controls no allies, that player instead discards all attachments from the hero they control with the most attachments.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“He has lost all power, save his voice that can still daunt you and deceive you, if you let it.”<br/>—Frodo Baggins, The Return of the King</p>");
            AddHtml("Watch-the-East-Road-TSotS", "<p class='flavor-text'>“There’s a big band about four miles away… there must be close on a hundred of them; and they’re fire-raising as they come.” —Merry, The Return of the King</p><p class='main-text'>Cannot be chosen as the active quest. X is 1 plus 1{PerPlayer}.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: At the beginning of the staging step, place any number of progress here and reveal an equal number of encounter cards.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When this quest is defeated, flip this card over and reveal it.</p>");
            AddHtml("Wooden-Shed-TSotS", "<p class='main-text'>While Wooden Shed is in the staging area, players cannot reduce their threat by more than 1 each round.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Either raise your threat by 1 or exhaust a character you control.</p><p class='flavor-text'>There were piles of refuse everywhere. The door was scarred; the bell-chain was dangling loose, and the bell would not ring. —The Return of the King</p>");
        }

        private void TheNineAreAbroad()
        {
            AddHtml("Agh-Burzum-ishi-Krimpatul-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>Doomed 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Each player must resolve this card’s shadow effect.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Exhaust 1 character you control. Until the end of the round, your characters cannot be readied by player card effects.</p>");
            AddHtml("Anfalas-Pillager-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>While not engaged, place this card on The Outlands. Anfalas Pillager gets +1 {Defense} for each resource token on it.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Anfalas Pillager attacks, move 1 resource from a hero you control to Anfalas Pillager.</p><p class='main-text'><i><b>Rumor</b>: The first player engages this enemy. Choose either the region southeast or northwest of your current region and place 1 resource token on it.</i></p>");
            AddHtml("Ash-Nazg-Durbatuluk-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>Doomed 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Each player must resolve this card’s shadow effect.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: For each attachment you control, either exhaust it, discard it, or deal 1 damage to its attached character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ash-Nazg-Gimbatul-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>Doomed 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Each player must resolve this card’s shadow effect.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Raise your threat by 2.</p>");
            AddHtml("Ash-Nazg-Thrakatuluk-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>Doomed 1.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Each player must resolve this card’s shadow effect.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Either engage a non-unique enemy on a region other than your current region, or discard the top 3 cards of the encounter deck and engage the topmost non-unique enemy in the encounter discard pile.</p>");
            AddHtml("Barrow-wight-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>While not engaged, place this card on Arnor.</p><p class='main-text'>Characters attacking or defending Barrow-wight use their {Willpower} in place of their {Attack} and {Defense}.</p><p class='main-text'><i><b>Rumor</b>: The first player engages this enemy. Choose either the region east or west of your current region and place 1 resource token on it.</i></p>");
            AddHtml("Birds-of-Ill-Omen-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Place Birds of Ill Omen between Enedwaith and Rohan. Cannot be canceled.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After your group moves between Enedwaith and Rohan, trigger doomed 2.</p>");
            AddHtml("Charter-the-Dream-chaser-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>Surge. Charter the Dream-chaser cannot be chosen as the current quest during the quest phase unless your current region is Harlindon.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Place Charter the Dream-chaser to the west of Harlindon.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Response</b>: After Charter the Dream-chaser is defeated, move your group to any other <b><i>Coastland</i></b> region. If you are in stage 1, place 1 resource token on that region. Otherwise, place 4 progress tokens on a location on that region.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Chief-of-the-Nine-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>The Witch-king gets +5 {Threat}, +2 {Attack}, and its attacks are immune to sentinel. Your group cannot deal it more than 5{PerPlayer} damage per round, and it cannot be defeated while there are other <b><i>Nazgûl</i></b> enemies in play.</p><p class='main-text'>Instead of its printed hit points, the Witch-king has 10 hit points for each group, plus 5 hit points for each player among all groups.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dunedain-Tracker-Standard-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot quest. If Dúnedain Tracker leaves play, remove it from the game.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Planning Action</b>: Exhaust Dúnedain Tracker to reveal the bottommost location in the encounter discard pile.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Discard Dúnedain Tracker to move 1 resource token from your current region to a neighboring region.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dunedain-Tracker-Epic-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>Cannot quest. If Dúnedain Tracker leaves play, remove it from the game.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Planning Action</b>: Exhaust Dúnedain Tracker to reveal the bottommost location in the encounter discard pile.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action</b>: Discard Dúnedain Tracker to move 1 resource token from a region in your map to a copy of that region in another group's map.</p>");
            AddHtml("Dunlending-Warband-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>While not engaged, place this card on Enedwaith.</p><p class='main-text'>X is the number of cards in the hand of the player with the greatest number of cards in their hand.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Deal 1 damage to the defending character.</p>");
            AddHtml("Gladden-Fields-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After this card enters play, place it on Mirkwood. Then, raise each player’s threat by 2.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Gladden Fields is explored, choose a group. If you are in stage 1, place 1 resource token on that group’s Mirkwood region. Then, your group investigates rumors.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack}.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Glorfindel-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Glorfindel exhausts to commit to a quest, raise your threat by 1.</p>");
            AddHtml("Icebay-of-Forochel-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After this card enters play, place it on The Blue Mountains. Then, the first player must discard the highest cost attachment they control.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Icebay of Forochel is explored, choose a group. Reduce each player’s threat in that group by 5. Then, your group investigates rumors.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Johnny-Goblin-fingers-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>While not engaged, place this card on Eriador.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When Johnny Goblin-fingers is defeated, your group investigates rumors.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Reveal Johnny Goblin-fingers.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Late-for-Tea-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Heal 1 damage from each character that shares a <b><i>Trait</i></b> with your current region. Deal 1 damage to each exhausted character that does not.</p><p class='main-text'><i><b>Rumor</b>: Each player deals 3 damage among characters they control. Place 1 resource token on your current region.</i></p>");
            AddHtml("Lost-in-Goblin-Town-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Attach to a hero. Counts as a <b><i><b><i>Condition</i></b></i></b> attachment with the text: “Attached hero cannot quest, attack, defend, or ready. Treat attached hero’s text box as if it were blank, except for <b><i>Traits</i></b>. <b>Response</b>: After the players move between Arnor and Rhovanion, add Lost in Goblin Town to the victory display.”</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Mordor-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>Surge. Mordor is not a map region, and cannot be chosen as the current quest during the quest phase unless your current region is Gondor.</p><p class='main-text'><b><i>Black Speech</i></b> card effects cannot be canceled.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Place Mordor to the east of Gondor.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the round, raise each player’s threat by 1.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Morgul-Scout-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>While not engaged, place this card on Gondor.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Morgul Scout is destroyed, reveal an encounter card.</p><p class='main-text'><i><b>Rumor</b>: The first player engages this enemy. Choose either the region northeast or southwest of your current region and place 1 resource token on it.</i></p>");
            AddHtml("Nameless-Fear-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Place Nameless Fear between Eriador and Mirkwood. Cannot be canceled.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After your group moves between Eriador and Mirkwood, add Nameless Fear to the victory display. Then, deal 5 damage to 1 hero the players control.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Old-North-South-Road-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After this card enters play, place it on a <b><i>Road</i></b> region without a copy of Old North-South Road on it.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Old North-South Road is explored, the first player discards the top 2 cards of their deck and may add 1 of those cards to their hand. Then, your group investigates rumors.</p>");
            AddHtml("Old-Pukel-Land-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After this card enters play, place it on The Outlands. Then, discard 1 resource from each hero in play.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When Old Púkel Land is explored, choose a group. Add 6 progress to that group’s main quest for each player in that group (bypassing any active locations). Then, your group investigates rumors.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Paths-of-the-Dead-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After this card enters play, place it on Rohan. Then, for each non-<b><i>Noble</i></b> hero in play, its controller must either exhaust it or deal 1 damage to it.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Paths of the Dead is explored, choose a group. Deal 2 damage to all enemies engaged with that group’s players. Then, your group investigates rumors.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("Pursuing-Wargs-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>While not engaged, place this card on your current region.</p><p class='main-text'>Pursuing Wargs cannot take combat damage unless it has been dealt a shadow card with a shadow effect this round.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Engage Pursuing Wargs.</p>");
            AddHtml("Rhun-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>Surge. Rhûn is not a map region, and cannot be chosen as the current quest during the quest phase unless your current region is Rohan.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Place Rhûn to the east of Rohan.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: At the end of the round, discard the top card of the encounter deck. If that card is a non-unique enemy, reveal it.</p>{victory:10}");
            AddHtml("Roaming-Easterling-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>While not engaged, place this card on Rhovanion.</p><p class='main-text'>If Roaming Easterling did not enter play this round, it gets +2 {Attack}.</p><p class='main-text'><i><b>Rumor</b>: The first player engages this enemy. Choose either the region north or south of your current region and place 1 resource token on it.</i></p>");
            AddHtml("Search-for-the-Nine-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'> <b>Setup</b>: Assemble the Middle-earth Map. Place 1 progress token on the region that shares a <b><i>Trait</i></b> with the greatest number of heroes. This is your current region. Set Chief of the Nine aside, out of play. Put Shadows of Terror into play, <b><i>Abroad</i></b> side faceup. Choose a player to take control of Dúnedain Tracker, <b><i>Standard</i></b> side faceup. If there are 2 or more groups, flip it to the <b><i>Epic</i></b> side, and familiarize yourself with the treachery called The Nine Are Abroad. Each player searches the encounter deck for a non-unique location and reveals it. Shuffle the encounter deck.</p>");
            AddHtml2("Search-for-the-Nine-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'> <b>Forced</b>: After placing a third resource token on a region, remove 3 resource tokens from it. Then, shuffle the encounter discard pile into the encounter deck and discard cards until a <b><i>Nazgûl</i></b> enemy is discarded and place it on that region. Tell each other group to search their encounter deck and discard pile for the same enemy, place it on their copy of that region, and shuffle their encounter deck. Do not trigger the “when revealed” effects on these enemies.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When the number of <b><i>Nazgûl</i></b> enemies in play matches the number of groups, advance to stage 2A at the end of the current phase.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("Shadows-of-Terror-Abroad-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b><i>Nazgûl</i></b> enemies are immune to player card effects and cannot be optionally engaged.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: The first time a <b><i>Nazgûl</i></b> enemy is revealed each round, the first player must trigger its shadow effect.</p><p class='flavor-text'>“My news is evil.” Then he looked about him, as if the hedges might have ears. “Nazgûl,” he whispered. “The Nine are abroad again.”<br/>—Radagast, The Fellowship of the Ring</p>");
            AddHtml("Shadows-of-Terror-Found-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b><i>Nazgûl</i></b> enemies are immune to player card effects and cannot be optionally engaged. <b><i>Nazgûl</i></b> enemies on your current region are considered to be enegaged with each player.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After a <b><i>Nazgûl</i></b> enemy attacks, it triggers its own shadow effect.</p></p class='main-text'><b>Forced:</b> At the end of the round, each player triggers the Witch-king's shadow effect.</p>");
            AddHtml("Shores-of-Belegaer-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After this card enters play, place it on a <b><i>Coastland</i></b> region without a copy of Shores of Belegaer on it.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After Shores of Belegaer is explored, the first player reduces their threat by 2. Then, your group investigates rumors.</p><p class='flavor-text'>…looking upon Belegaer the Great Sea he was enamoured of it, and the sound of it and the longing for it were ever in his heart and ear… —The Silmarillion</p>");
            AddHtml("South-Downs-Troll-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>While not engaged, place this card on Eriador.</p><p class='main-text'>Excess combat damage dealt by South Downs Troll must be assigned as an increase to your threat.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Attacking enemy gets +1 {Attack}. If this attack destroys a character, attacking enemy makes an additional attack.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Anduin-River-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After this card enters play, place it on a <b><i>River</i></b> region without a copy of The Anduin River on it.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After The Anduin River is explored, the first player shuffles up to 2 cards from their discard pile into their deck. Then, your group must investigate rumors.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Carrock-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: After this card enters play, place it on Rhovanion. Then, each player must exhaust 1 non-<b><i>Creature</i></b> character they control.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When The Carrock is explored, choose a group. That group may move from their current region to any other region in their map. Then, your group investigates rumors.</p>{victory:5}");
            AddHtml("The-Eighth-Rider-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: This card gains surge. Discard this card.</p><p class='main-text'><i><b>Rumor</b>: Each player must trigger this card’s shadow effect. Choose either the region southeast or northwest of your current region and place 1 resource token on it.</i></p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Discard the top card of your deck, then discard 1 copy of that card from play.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Fifth-Rider-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: This card gains surge. Discard this card.</p><p class='main-text'><i><b>Rumor</b>: Each player must trigger this card’s shadow effect. Choose either the region north or south of your current region and place 1 resource token on it.</i></p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Deal 2 damage to a character you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-First-Rider-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: This card gains surge. Discard this card.</p><p class='main-text'><i><b>Rumor</b>: Each player must trigger this card’s shadow effect. Choose either the region east or west of your current region and place 1 resource token on it.</i></p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Raise your threat by 1.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Fourth-Rider-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: This card gains surge. Discard this card.</p><p class='main-text'><i><b>Rumor</b>: Each player must trigger this card’s shadow effect. Choose either the region southeast or northwest of your current region and place 1 resource token on it.</i></p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Discard 1 random card from your hand.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Nine-are-Abroad-Treachery-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>Surge.</p><p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: Announce to all groups, “The Nine are Abroad.” Each player in each group must choose to either deal 1 damage to 1 character they control, or raise their threat by 1. Then, add The Nine are Abroad to the victory display.</p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Resolve this card’s “when revealed” effect.</p>{victory:1}");
            AddHtml("The-Ninth-Rider-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: This card gains surge. Discard this card.</p><p class='main-text'><i><b>Rumor</b>: Each player must trigger this card’s shadow effect. Place 1 resource token on your current region.</i></p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Discard the top card of the encounter deck. If it is a non-unique enemy, engage it.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Second-Rider-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: This card gains surge. Discard this card.</p><p class='main-text'><i><b>Rumor</b>: Each player must trigger this card’s shadow effect. Choose either the region north or south of your current region and place 1 resource token on it.</i></p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Discard 1 resource from the pool of each hero you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Seventh-Rider-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: This card gains surge. Discard this card.</p><p class='main-text'><i><b>Rumor</b>: Each player must trigger this card’s shadow effect. Choose either the region northeast or southwest of your current region and place 1 resource token on it.</i></p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Choose 1 ready ally you control. Exhaust it and deal 1 damage to it.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Sixth-Rider-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: This card gains surge. Discard this card.</p><p class='main-text'><i><b>Rumor</b>: Each player must trigger this card’s shadow effect. Choose either the region east or west of your current region and place 1 resource token on it.</i></p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Discard an attachment you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("The-Third-Rider-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'><b>When Revealed</b>: This card gains surge. Discard this card.</p><p class='main-text'><i><b>Rumor</b>: Each player must trigger this card’s shadow effect. Choose either the region northeast or southwest of your current region and place 1 resource token on it.</i></p>{shadow}<p class='shadow-text'><b>Shadow</b>: Exhaust 1 hero you control.</p>");
            AddHtml("To-Mordor-We-Will-Send-Them-TNaA", "<p class='flavor-text'>The rumors were true! The dreaded Witch-king of Angmar once again walks Middle-earth, driven by some fell purpose. </p><p class='main-text'> <b>When Revealed</b>: Remove all resource tokens from each region. Flip Shadows of Terror over, <b><i>Found</i></b> side faceup. Attach the set aside Chief of the Nine objective to the <b><i>Nazgûl</i></b> enemy that entered play last. That enemy is “the Witch-king”. If there are other groups, take a moment to strategize with them about who will handle each <b><i>Nazgûl</i></b> enemy.</p>");
            AddHtml2("To-Mordor-We-Will-Send-Them-TNaA", "<p class='flavor-text'>The Nazgûl cannot be allowed to pursue their aims unhindered. You must disrupt their plans and send them back to their master.</p><p class='main-text'> When calculating the remaining hit points of a <b><i>Nazgûl</i></b> enemy, add up all damage on each copy of that enemy among all groups.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Forced</b>: When you would investigate rumors, each player draws 1 card instead.</p><p class='main-text'><b>If there are no <b><i>Nazgûl</i></b> enemies in play, the players win the game.</b></p>");
            AddHtml("At-the-End-of-All-Things-TNaA", "<p class='main-text'>You can only choose 2 starting heroes. They each get +4 threat cost, +1 {Willpower}, +1 {Attack}, +1 {Defense}, +1 hit point, and they each gain a resource icon matching the other hero’s printed sphere. They cannot gain resources from attachment card effects, and they cannot be healed.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Exhaust {self} to deal 1 damage to one of your starting heroes and ready your other starting hero.</p><p class='main-text'><b>Action:</b> Flip this card over. You cannot trigger this effect during the first 3 rounds.</p>");
